2587 static void AddDrawListToRenderList(ImVector<ImDrawList*>& out_render_list, ImDrawList* draw_list)
2588 {
2589  if (draw_list->CmdBuffer.empty())
2590  return;
2591 
2592  // Remove trailing command if unused
2593  ImDrawCmd& last_cmd = draw_list->CmdBuffer.back();
2594  if (last_cmd.ElemCount == 0 && last_cmd.UserCallback == NULL)
2595  {
2596  draw_list->CmdBuffer.pop_back();
2597  if (draw_list->CmdBuffer.empty())
2598  return;
2599  }
2600 
2601  // Draw list sanity check. Detect mismatch between PrimReserve() calls and incrementing _VtxCurrentIdx, _VtxWritePtr etc. May trigger for you if you are using PrimXXX functions incorrectly.
2602  IM_ASSERT(draw_list->VtxBuffer.Size == 0 || draw_list->_VtxWritePtr == draw_list->VtxBuffer.Data + draw_list->VtxBuffer.Size);
2603  IM_ASSERT(draw_list->IdxBuffer.Size == 0 || draw_list->_IdxWritePtr == draw_list->IdxBuffer.Data + draw_list->IdxBuffer.Size);
2604  IM_ASSERT((int)draw_list->_VtxCurrentIdx == draw_list->VtxBuffer.Size);
2605 
2606  // Check that draw_list doesn't use more vertices than indexable in a single draw call (default ImDrawIdx = unsigned short = 2 bytes = 64K vertices per window)
2607  // If this assert triggers because you are drawing lots of stuff manually, you can:
2608  // A) Add '#define ImDrawIdx unsigned int' in imconfig.h to set the index size to 4 bytes. You'll need to handle the 4-bytes indices to your renderer.
2609  // For example, the OpenGL example code detect index size at compile-time by doing:
2610  // 'glDrawElements(GL_TRIANGLES, (GLsizei)pcmd->ElemCount, sizeof(ImDrawIdx) == 2 ? GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT : GL_UNSIGNED_INT, idx_buffer_offset);'
2611  // Your own engine or render API may use different parameters or function calls to specify index sizes. 2 and 4 bytes indices are generally supported by most API.
2612  // B) If for some reason you cannot use 4 bytes indices or don't want to, a workaround is to call BeginChild()/EndChild() before reaching the 64K limit to split your draw commands in multiple draw lists.
2613  IM_ASSERT(((ImU64)draw_list->_VtxCurrentIdx >> (sizeof(ImDrawIdx)*8)) == 0); // Too many vertices in same ImDrawList. See comment above.
2614 
2615  out_render_list.push_back(draw_list);
2616  GImGui->IO.MetricsRenderVertices += draw_list->VtxBuffer.Size;
2617  GImGui->IO.MetricsRenderIndices += draw_list->IdxBuffer.Size;
2618 }
2619 
2620 static void AddWindowToRenderList(ImVector<ImDrawList*>& out_render_list, ImGuiWindow* window)
2621 {
2622  AddDrawListToRenderList(out_render_list, window->DrawList);
2623  for (int i = 0; i < window->DC.ChildWindows.Size; i++)
2624  {
2625  ImGuiWindow* child = window->DC.ChildWindows[i];
2626  if (!child->Active) // clipped children may have been marked not active
2627  continue;
2628  if ((child->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) && child->HiddenFrames > 0)
2629  continue;
2630  AddWindowToRenderList(out_render_list, child);
2631  }
2632 }

2634 // When using this function it is sane to ensure that float are perfectly rounded to integer values, to that e.g. (int)(max.x-min.x) in user's render produce correct result.
2635 void ImGui::PushClipRect(const ImVec2& clip_rect_min, const ImVec2& clip_rect_max, bool intersect_with_current_clip_rect)

2639  window->ClipRect = window->DrawList->_ClipRectStack.back();

2649 // This is normally called by Render(). You may want to call it directly if you want to avoid calling Render() but the gain will be very minimal.
2650 void ImGui::EndFrame()
2651 {
2652  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
2653  IM_ASSERT(g.Initialized); // Forgot to call ImGui::NewFrame()
2654  IM_ASSERT(g.FrameCountEnded != g.FrameCount); // ImGui::EndFrame() called multiple times, or forgot to call ImGui::NewFrame() again
2655 
2656  // Render tooltip
2657  if (g.Tooltip[0])
2658  {
2659  ImGui::BeginTooltip();
2660  ImGui::TextUnformatted(g.Tooltip);
2661  ImGui::EndTooltip();
2662  }
2663 
2664  // Notify OS when our Input Method Editor cursor has moved (e.g. CJK inputs using Microsoft IME)
2665  if (g.IO.ImeSetInputScreenPosFn && ImLengthSqr(g.OsImePosRequest - g.OsImePosSet) > 0.0001f)
2666  {
2667  g.IO.ImeSetInputScreenPosFn((int)g.OsImePosRequest.x, (int)g.OsImePosRequest.y);
2668  g.OsImePosSet = g.OsImePosRequest;
2669  }
2670 
2671  // Hide implicit "Debug" window if it hasn't been used
2672  IM_ASSERT(g.CurrentWindowStack.Size == 1); // Mismatched Begin()/End() calls
2673  if (g.CurrentWindow && !g.CurrentWindow->Accessed)
2674  g.CurrentWindow->Active = false;
2675  ImGui::End();
2676 
2677  // Click to focus window and start moving (after we're done with all our widgets)
2678  if (g.ActiveId == 0 && g.HoveredId == 0 && g.IO.MouseClicked[0])
2679  {
2680  if (!(g.FocusedWindow && !g.FocusedWindow->WasActive && g.FocusedWindow->Active)) // Unless we just made a popup appear
2681  {
2682  if (g.HoveredRootWindow != NULL)
2683  {
2684  FocusWindow(g.HoveredWindow);
2685  if (!(g.HoveredWindow->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoMove))
2686  {
2687  g.MovedWindow = g.HoveredWindow;
2688  g.MovedWindowMoveId = g.HoveredRootWindow->MoveId;
2689  SetActiveID(g.MovedWindowMoveId, g.HoveredRootWindow);
2690  }
2691  }
2692  else if (g.FocusedWindow != NULL && GetFrontMostModalRootWindow() == NULL)
2693  {
2694  // Clicking on void disable focus
2695  FocusWindow(NULL);
2696  }
2697  }
2698  }
2699 
2700  // Sort the window list so that all child windows are after their parent
2701  // We cannot do that on FocusWindow() because childs may not exist yet
2702  g.WindowsSortBuffer.resize(0);
2703  g.WindowsSortBuffer.reserve(g.Windows.Size);
2704  for (int i = 0; i != g.Windows.Size; i++)
2705  {
2706  ImGuiWindow* window = g.Windows[i];
2707  if (window->Active && (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow)) // if a child is active its parent will add it
2708  continue;
2709  AddWindowToSortedBuffer(g.WindowsSortBuffer, window);
2710  }
2711  IM_ASSERT(g.Windows.Size == g.WindowsSortBuffer.Size); // we done something wrong
2712  g.Windows.swap(g.WindowsSortBuffer);
2713 
2714  // Clear Input data for next frame
2715  g.IO.MouseWheel = 0.0f;
2716  memset(g.IO.InputCharacters, 0, sizeof(g.IO.InputCharacters));
2717 
2718  g.FrameCountEnded = g.FrameCount;
2719 }
2720 
2721 void ImGui::Render()
2722 {
2723  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
2724  IM_ASSERT(g.Initialized); // Forgot to call ImGui::NewFrame()
2725 
2726  if (g.FrameCountEnded != g.FrameCount)
2727  ImGui::EndFrame();
2728  g.FrameCountRendered = g.FrameCount;
2729 
2730  // Skip render altogether if alpha is 0.0
2731  // Note that vertex buffers have been created and are wasted, so it is best practice that you don't create windows in the first place, or consistently respond to Begin() returning false.
2732  if (g.Style.Alpha > 0.0f)
2733  {
2734  // Gather windows to render
2735  g.IO.MetricsRenderVertices = g.IO.MetricsRenderIndices = g.IO.MetricsActiveWindows = 0;
2736  for (int i = 0; i < IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.RenderDrawLists); i++)
2737  g.RenderDrawLists[i].resize(0);
2738  for (int i = 0; i != g.Windows.Size; i++)
2739  {
2740  ImGuiWindow* window = g.Windows[i];
2741  if (window->Active && window->HiddenFrames <= 0 && (window->Flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow)) == 0)
2742  {
2743  // FIXME: Generalize this with a proper layering system so e.g. user can draw in specific layers, below text, ..
2744  g.IO.MetricsActiveWindows++;
2745  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup)
2746  AddWindowToRenderList(g.RenderDrawLists[1], window);
2747  else if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip)
2748  AddWindowToRenderList(g.RenderDrawLists[2], window);
2749  else
2750  AddWindowToRenderList(g.RenderDrawLists[0], window);
2751  }
2752  }
2753 
2754  // Flatten layers
2755  int n = g.RenderDrawLists[0].Size;
2756  int flattened_size = n;
2757  for (int i = 1; i < IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.RenderDrawLists); i++)
2758  flattened_size += g.RenderDrawLists[i].Size;
2759  g.RenderDrawLists[0].resize(flattened_size);
2760  for (int i = 1; i < IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.RenderDrawLists); i++)
2761  {
2762  ImVector<ImDrawList*>& layer = g.RenderDrawLists[i];
2763  if (layer.empty())
2764  continue;
2765  memcpy(&g.RenderDrawLists[0][n], &layer[0], layer.Size * sizeof(ImDrawList*));
2766  n += layer.Size;
2767  }
2768 
2769  // Draw software mouse cursor if requested
2770  if (g.IO.MouseDrawCursor)
2771  {
2772  const ImGuiMouseCursorData& cursor_data = g.MouseCursorData[g.MouseCursor];
2773  const ImVec2 pos = g.IO.MousePos - cursor_data.HotOffset;
2774  const ImVec2 size = cursor_data.Size;
2775  const ImTextureID tex_id = g.IO.Fonts->TexID;
2776  g.OverlayDrawList.PushTextureID(tex_id);
2777  g.OverlayDrawList.AddImage(tex_id, pos+ImVec2(1,0), pos+ImVec2(1,0) + size, cursor_data.TexUvMin[1], cursor_data.TexUvMax[1], IM_COL32(0,0,0,48)); // Shadow
2778  g.OverlayDrawList.AddImage(tex_id, pos+ImVec2(2,0), pos+ImVec2(2,0) + size, cursor_data.TexUvMin[1], cursor_data.TexUvMax[1], IM_COL32(0,0,0,48)); // Shadow
2779  g.OverlayDrawList.AddImage(tex_id, pos, pos + size, cursor_data.TexUvMin[1], cursor_data.TexUvMax[1], IM_COL32(0,0,0,255)); // Black border
2780  g.OverlayDrawList.AddImage(tex_id, pos, pos + size, cursor_data.TexUvMin[0], cursor_data.TexUvMax[0], IM_COL32(255,255,255,255)); // White fill
2781  g.OverlayDrawList.PopTextureID();
2782  }
2783  if (!g.OverlayDrawList.VtxBuffer.empty())
2784  AddDrawListToRenderList(g.RenderDrawLists[0], &g.OverlayDrawList);
2785 
2786  // Setup draw data
2787  g.RenderDrawData.Valid = true;
2788  g.RenderDrawData.CmdLists = (g.RenderDrawLists[0].Size > 0) ? &g.RenderDrawLists[0][0] : NULL;
2789  g.RenderDrawData.CmdListsCount = g.RenderDrawLists[0].Size;
2790  g.RenderDrawData.TotalVtxCount = g.IO.MetricsRenderVertices;
2791  g.RenderDrawData.TotalIdxCount = g.IO.MetricsRenderIndices;
2792 
2793  // Render. If user hasn't set a callback then they may retrieve the draw data via GetDrawData()
2794  if (g.RenderDrawData.CmdListsCount > 0 && g.IO.RenderDrawListsFn != NULL)
2795  g.IO.RenderDrawListsFn(&g.RenderDrawData);
2796  }
2797 }

2799 const char* ImGui::FindRenderedTextEnd(const char* text, const char* text_end)
2800 {
2801  const char* text_display_end = text;
2802  if (!text_end)
2803  text_end = (const char*)-1;
2804 
2805  while (text_display_end < text_end && *text_display_end != '\0' && (text_display_end[0] != '#' || text_display_end[1] != '#'))
2806  text_display_end++;
2807  return text_display_end;
2808 }

2810 // Pass text data straight to log (without being displayed)
2811 void ImGui::LogText(const char* fmt, ...)
2812 {
2813  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
2814  if (!g.LogEnabled)
2815  return;
2816 
2817  va_list args;
2818  va_start(args, fmt);
2819  if (g.LogFile)
2820  {
2821  vfprintf(g.LogFile, fmt, args);
2822  }
2823  else
2824  {
2825  g.LogClipboard->appendv(fmt, args);
2826  }
2827  va_end(args);
2828 }

2830 // Internal version that takes a position to decide on newline placement and pad items according to their depth.
2831 // We split text into individual lines to add current tree level padding
2832 static void LogRenderedText(const ImVec2& ref_pos, const char* text, const char* text_end)
2833 {
2834  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
2835  ImGuiWindow* window = ImGui::GetCurrentWindowRead();
2836 
2837  if (!text_end)
2838  text_end = ImGui::FindRenderedTextEnd(text, text_end);
2839 
2840  const bool log_new_line = ref_pos.y > window->DC.LogLinePosY+1;
2841  window->DC.LogLinePosY = ref_pos.y;
2842 
2843  const char* text_remaining = text;
2844  if (g.LogStartDepth > window->DC.TreeDepth) // Re-adjust padding if we have popped out of our starting depth
2845  g.LogStartDepth = window->DC.TreeDepth;
2846  const int tree_depth = (window->DC.TreeDepth - g.LogStartDepth);
2847  for (;;)
2848  {
2849  // Split the string. Each new line (after a '\n') is followed by spacing corresponding to the current depth of our log entry.
2850  const char* line_end = text_remaining;
2851  while (line_end < text_end)
2852  if (*line_end == '\n')
2853  break;
2854  else
2855  line_end++;
2856  if (line_end >= text_end)
2857  line_end = NULL;
2858 
2859  const bool is_first_line = (text == text_remaining);
2860  bool is_last_line = false;
2861  if (line_end == NULL)
2862  {
2863  is_last_line = true;
2864  line_end = text_end;
2865  }
2866  if (line_end != NULL && !(is_last_line && (line_end - text_remaining)==0))
2867  {
2868  const int char_count = (int)(line_end - text_remaining);
2869  if (log_new_line || !is_first_line)
2870  ImGui::LogText(IM_NEWLINE "%*s%.*s", tree_depth*4, "", char_count, text_remaining);
2871  else
2872  ImGui::LogText(" %.*s", char_count, text_remaining);
2873  }
2874 
2875  if (is_last_line)
2876  break;
2877  text_remaining = line_end + 1;
2878  }
2879 }

2927 // Default clip_rect uses (pos_min,pos_max)
2928 // Handle clipping on CPU immediately (vs typically let the GPU clip the triangles that are overlapping the clipping rectangle edges)
2929 void ImGui::RenderTextClipped(const ImVec2& pos_min, const ImVec2& pos_max, const char* text, const char* text_end, const ImVec2* text_size_if_known, const ImVec2& align, const ImRect* clip_rect)
2930 {
2931  // Hide anything after a '##' string
2932  const char* text_display_end = FindRenderedTextEnd(text, text_end);
2933  const int text_len = (int)(text_display_end - text);
2934  if (text_len == 0)
2935  return;
2936 
2937  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
2938  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
2939 
2940  // Perform CPU side clipping for single clipped element to avoid using scissor state
2941  ImVec2 pos = pos_min;
2942  const ImVec2 text_size = text_size_if_known ? *text_size_if_known : CalcTextSize(text, text_display_end, false, 0.0f);
2943 
2944  const ImVec2* clip_min = clip_rect ? &clip_rect->Min : &pos_min;
2945  const ImVec2* clip_max = clip_rect ? &clip_rect->Max : &pos_max;
2946  bool need_clipping = (pos.x + text_size.x >= clip_max->x) || (pos.y + text_size.y >= clip_max->y);
2947  if (clip_rect) // If we had no explicit clipping rectangle then pos==clip_min
2948  need_clipping |= (pos.x < clip_min->x) || (pos.y < clip_min->y);
2949 
2950  // Align whole block. We should defer that to the better rendering function when we'll have support for individual line alignment.
2951  if (align.x > 0.0f) pos.x = ImMax(pos.x, pos.x + (pos_max.x - pos.x - text_size.x) * align.x);
2952  if (align.y > 0.0f) pos.y = ImMax(pos.y, pos.y + (pos_max.y - pos.y - text_size.y) * align.y);
2953 
2954  // Render
2955  if (need_clipping)
2956  {
2957  ImVec4 fine_clip_rect(clip_min->x, clip_min->y, clip_max->x, clip_max->y);
2958  window->DrawList->AddText(g.Font, g.FontSize, pos, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Text), text, text_display_end, 0.0f, &fine_clip_rect);
2959  }
2960  else
2961  {
2962  window->DrawList->AddText(g.Font, g.FontSize, pos, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Text), text, text_display_end, 0.0f, NULL);
2963  }
2964  if (g.LogEnabled)
2965  LogRenderedText(pos, text, text_display_end);
2966 }

3015 void ImGui::RenderCheckMark(ImVec2 pos, ImU32 col)
3016 {

3018  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
3019 
3020  ImVec2 a, b, c;

3036 // Calculate text size. Text can be multi-line. Optionally ignore text after a ## marker.
3037 // CalcTextSize("") should return ImVec2(0.0f, GImGui->FontSize)
3038 ImVec2 ImGui::CalcTextSize(const char* text, const char* text_end, bool hide_text_after_double_hash, float wrap_width)
3039 {
3040  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3041 
3042  const char* text_display_end;
3043  if (hide_text_after_double_hash)
3044  text_display_end = FindRenderedTextEnd(text, text_end); // Hide anything after a '##' string
3045  else
3046  text_display_end = text_end;
3047 
3048  ImFont* font = g.Font;
3049  const float font_size = g.FontSize;
3050  if (text == text_display_end)
3051  return ImVec2(0.0f, font_size);
3052  ImVec2 text_size = font->CalcTextSizeA(font_size, FLT_MAX, wrap_width, text, text_display_end, NULL);
3053 
3054  // Cancel out character spacing for the last character of a line (it is baked into glyph->XAdvance field)
3055  const float font_scale = font_size / font->FontSize;
3056  const float character_spacing_x = 1.0f * font_scale;
3057  if (text_size.x > 0.0f)
3058  text_size.x -= character_spacing_x;
3059  text_size.x = (float)(int)(text_size.x + 0.95f);
3060 
3061  return text_size;
3062 }

3064 // Helper to calculate coarse clipping of large list of evenly sized items.
3065 // NB: Prefer using the ImGuiListClipper higher-level helper if you can! Read comments and instructions there on how those use this sort of pattern.
3066 // NB: 'items_count' is only used to clamp the result, if you don't know your count you can use INT_MAX
3067 void ImGui::CalcListClipping(int items_count, float items_height, int* out_items_display_start, int* out_items_display_end)
3068 {
3069  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3070  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindowRead();
3071  if (g.LogEnabled)
3072  {
3073  // If logging is active, do not perform any clipping
3074  *out_items_display_start = 0;
3075  *out_items_display_end = items_count;
3076  return;
3077  }
3078  if (window->SkipItems)
3079  {
3080  *out_items_display_start = *out_items_display_end = 0;
3081  return;
3082  }
3083 
3084  const ImVec2 pos = window->DC.CursorPos;
3085  int start = (int)((window->ClipRect.Min.y - pos.y) / items_height);
3086  int end = (int)((window->ClipRect.Max.y - pos.y) / items_height);
3087  start = ImClamp(start, 0, items_count);
3088  end = ImClamp(end + 1, start, items_count);
3089  *out_items_display_start = start;
3090  *out_items_display_end = end;
3091 }

3093 // Find window given position, search front-to-back
3094 // FIXME: Note that we have a lag here because WindowRectClipped is updated in Begin() so windows moved by user via SetWindowPos() and not SetNextWindowPos() will have that rectangle lagging by a frame at the time FindHoveredWindow() is called, aka before the next Begin(). Moving window thankfully isn't affected.
3095 static ImGuiWindow* FindHoveredWindow(ImVec2 pos, bool excluding_childs)
3096 {
3097  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3098  for (int i = g.Windows.Size-1; i >= 0; i--)
3099  {
3100  ImGuiWindow* window = g.Windows[i];
3101  if (!window->Active)
3102  continue;
3103  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoInputs)
3104  continue;
3105  if (excluding_childs && (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) != 0)
3106  continue;
3107 
3108  // Using the clipped AABB so a child window will typically be clipped by its parent.
3109  ImRect bb(window->WindowRectClipped.Min - g.Style.TouchExtraPadding, window->WindowRectClipped.Max + g.Style.TouchExtraPadding);
3110  if (bb.Contains(pos))
3111  return window;
3112  }
3113  return NULL;
3114 }

3171 bool ImGui::IsKeyPressed(int user_key_index, bool repeat)
3172 {
3173  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3174  if (user_key_index < 0) return false;
3175  IM_ASSERT(user_key_index >= 0 && user_key_index < IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.IO.KeysDown));
3176  const float t = g.IO.KeysDownDuration[user_key_index];
3177  if (t == 0.0f)
3178  return true;
3179 
3180  if (repeat && t > g.IO.KeyRepeatDelay)
3181  {
3182  float delay = g.IO.KeyRepeatDelay, rate = g.IO.KeyRepeatRate;
3183  if ((fmodf(t - delay, rate) > rate*0.5f) != (fmodf(t - delay - g.IO.DeltaTime, rate) > rate*0.5f))
3184  return true;
3185  }
3186  return false;
3187 }

3238 bool ImGui::IsMouseDragging(int button, float lock_threshold)
3239 {
3240  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3241  IM_ASSERT(button >= 0 && button < IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.IO.MouseDown));
3242  if (!g.IO.MouseDown[button])
3243  return false;
3244  if (lock_threshold < 0.0f)
3245  lock_threshold = g.IO.MouseDragThreshold;
3246  return g.IO.MouseDragMaxDistanceSqr[button] >= lock_threshold * lock_threshold;
3247 }

3263 ImVec2 ImGui::GetMouseDragDelta(int button, float lock_threshold)
3264 {
3265  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3266  IM_ASSERT(button >= 0 && button < IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.IO.MouseDown));
3267  if (lock_threshold < 0.0f)
3268  lock_threshold = g.IO.MouseDragThreshold;
3269  if (g.IO.MouseDown[button])
3270  if (g.IO.MouseDragMaxDistanceSqr[button] >= lock_threshold * lock_threshold)
3271  return g.IO.MousePos - g.IO.MouseClickedPos[button]; // Assume we can only get active with left-mouse button (at the moment).
3272  return ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f);
3273 }

3419 static bool IsPopupOpen(ImGuiID id)
3420 {
3421  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3422  return g.OpenPopupStack.Size > g.CurrentPopupStack.Size && g.OpenPopupStack[g.CurrentPopupStack.Size].PopupId == id;
3423 }
3424 
3425 // Mark popup as open (toggle toward open state).
3426 // Popups are closed when user click outside, or activate a pressable item, or CloseCurrentPopup() is called within a BeginPopup()/EndPopup() block.
3427 // Popup identifiers are relative to the current ID-stack (so OpenPopup and BeginPopup needs to be at the same level).
3428 // One open popup per level of the popup hierarchy (NB: when assigning we reset the Window member of ImGuiPopupRef to NULL)
3429 void ImGui::OpenPopupEx(const char* str_id, bool reopen_existing)
3430 {
3431  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3432  ImGuiWindow* window = g.CurrentWindow;
3433  ImGuiID id = window->GetID(str_id);
3434  int current_stack_size = g.CurrentPopupStack.Size;
3435  ImGuiPopupRef popup_ref = ImGuiPopupRef(id, window, window->GetID("##menus"), g.IO.MousePos); // Tagged as new ref because constructor sets Window to NULL (we are passing the ParentWindow info here)
3436  if (g.OpenPopupStack.Size < current_stack_size + 1)
3437  g.OpenPopupStack.push_back(popup_ref);
3438  else if (reopen_existing || g.OpenPopupStack[current_stack_size].PopupId != id)
3439  {
3440  g.OpenPopupStack.resize(current_stack_size+1);
3441  g.OpenPopupStack[current_stack_size] = popup_ref;
3442  }
3443 }
3444 
3445 void ImGui::OpenPopup(const char* str_id)
3446 {
3447  ImGui::OpenPopupEx(str_id, false);
3448 }
3449 
3450 static void CloseInactivePopups()
3451 {
3452  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3453  if (g.OpenPopupStack.empty())
3454  return;
3455 
3456  // When popups are stacked, clicking on a lower level popups puts focus back to it and close popups above it.
3457  // Don't close our own child popup windows
3458  int n = 0;
3459  if (g.FocusedWindow)
3460  {
3461  for (n = 0; n < g.OpenPopupStack.Size; n++)
3462  {
3463  ImGuiPopupRef& popup = g.OpenPopupStack[n];
3464  if (!popup.Window)
3465  continue;
3466  IM_ASSERT((popup.Window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) != 0);
3467  if (popup.Window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow)
3468  continue;
3469 
3470  bool has_focus = false;
3471  for (int m = n; m < g.OpenPopupStack.Size && !has_focus; m++)
3472  has_focus = (g.OpenPopupStack[m].Window && g.OpenPopupStack[m].Window->RootWindow == g.FocusedWindow->RootWindow);
3473  if (!has_focus)
3474  break;
3475  }
3476  }
3477  if (n < g.OpenPopupStack.Size) // This test is not required but it allows to set a useful breakpoint on the line below
3478  g.OpenPopupStack.resize(n);
3479 }
3480 
3481 static ImGuiWindow* GetFrontMostModalRootWindow()
3482 {
3483  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3484  for (int n = g.OpenPopupStack.Size-1; n >= 0; n--)
3485  if (ImGuiWindow* front_most_popup = g.OpenPopupStack.Data[n].Window)
3486  if (front_most_popup->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Modal)
3487  return front_most_popup;
3488  return NULL;
3489 }

3491 static void ClosePopupToLevel(int remaining)
3492 {
3493  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3494  if (remaining > 0)
3495  ImGui::FocusWindow(g.OpenPopupStack[remaining-1].Window);
3496  else
3497  ImGui::FocusWindow(g.OpenPopupStack[0].ParentWindow);
3498  g.OpenPopupStack.resize(remaining);
3499 }

3501 static void ClosePopup(ImGuiID id)
3502 {
3503  if (!IsPopupOpen(id))
3504  return;
3505  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3506  ClosePopupToLevel(g.OpenPopupStack.Size - 1);
3507 }
3508 
3509 // Close the popup we have begin-ed into.
3510 void ImGui::CloseCurrentPopup()
3511 {
3512  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3513  int popup_idx = g.CurrentPopupStack.Size - 1;
3514  if (popup_idx < 0 || popup_idx > g.OpenPopupStack.Size || g.CurrentPopupStack[popup_idx].PopupId != g.OpenPopupStack[popup_idx].PopupId)
3515  return;
3516  while (popup_idx > 0 && g.OpenPopupStack[popup_idx].Window && (g.OpenPopupStack[popup_idx].Window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu))
3517  popup_idx--;
3518  ClosePopupToLevel(popup_idx);
3519 }

3521 static inline void ClearSetNextWindowData()
3522 {
3523  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3524  g.SetNextWindowPosCond = g.SetNextWindowSizeCond = g.SetNextWindowContentSizeCond = g.SetNextWindowCollapsedCond = 0;

3528 static bool BeginPopupEx(const char* str_id, ImGuiWindowFlags extra_flags)
3529 {
3530  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3531  ImGuiWindow* window = g.CurrentWindow;
3532  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(str_id);
3533  if (!IsPopupOpen(id))
3534  {
3535  ClearSetNextWindowData(); // We behave like Begin() and need to consume those values
3536  return false;
3537  }
3538 
3539  ImGui::PushStyleVar(ImGuiStyleVar_WindowRounding, 0.0f);
3540  ImGuiWindowFlags flags = extra_flags|ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup|ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar|ImGuiWindowFlags_NoMove|ImGuiWindowFlags_NoResize|ImGuiWindowFlags_NoSavedSettings|ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize;
3541 
3542  char name[20];
3543  if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu)
3544  ImFormatString(name, IM_ARRAYSIZE(name), "##menu_%d", g.CurrentPopupStack.Size); // Recycle windows based on depth
3545  else
3546  ImFormatString(name, IM_ARRAYSIZE(name), "##popup_%08x", id); // Not recycling, so we can close/open during the same frame
3547 
3548  bool is_open = ImGui::Begin(name, NULL, flags);
3549  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders))
3550  g.CurrentWindow->Flags &= ~ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders;
3551  if (!is_open) // NB: is_open can be 'false' when the popup is completely clipped (e.g. zero size display)
3552  ImGui::EndPopup();
3553 
3554  return is_open;
3555 }
3556 
3557 bool ImGui::BeginPopup(const char* str_id)
3558 {
3559  if (GImGui->OpenPopupStack.Size <= GImGui->CurrentPopupStack.Size) // Early out for performance
3560  {
3561  ClearSetNextWindowData(); // We behave like Begin() and need to consume those values
3562  return false;
3563  }
3564  return BeginPopupEx(str_id, ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders);
3565 }

3567 bool ImGui::BeginPopupModal(const char* name, bool* p_open, ImGuiWindowFlags extra_flags)
3568 {
3569  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3570  ImGuiWindow* window = g.CurrentWindow;
3571  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(name);
3572  if (!IsPopupOpen(id))
3573  {
3574  ClearSetNextWindowData(); // We behave like Begin() and need to consume those values
3575  return false;
3576  }
3577 
3578  ImGuiWindowFlags flags = extra_flags|ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup|ImGuiWindowFlags_Modal|ImGuiWindowFlags_NoCollapse|ImGuiWindowFlags_NoSavedSettings;
3579  bool is_open = ImGui::Begin(name, p_open, flags);
3580  if (!is_open || (p_open && !*p_open)) // NB: is_open can be 'false' when the popup is completely clipped (e.g. zero size display)
3581  {
3582  ImGui::EndPopup();
3583  if (is_open)
3584  ClosePopup(id);
3585  return false;
3586  }
3587 
3588  return is_open;
3589 }

3601 // This is a helper to handle the most simple case of associating one named popup to one given widget.
3602 // 1. If you have many possible popups (for different "instances" of a same widget, or for wholly different widgets), you may be better off handling
3603 // this yourself so you can store data relative to the widget that opened the popup instead of choosing different popup identifiers.
3604 // 2. If you want right-clicking on the same item to reopen the popup at new location, use the same code replacing IsItemHovered() with IsItemHoveredRect()
3605 // and passing true to the OpenPopupEx().
3606 // Because: hovering an item in a window below the popup won't normally trigger is hovering behavior/coloring. The pattern of ignoring the fact that
3607 // the item isn't interactable (because it is blocked by the active popup) may useful in some situation when e.g. large canvas as one item, content of menu
3608 // driven by click position.
3609 bool ImGui::BeginPopupContextItem(const char* str_id, int mouse_button)
3610 {
3611  if (IsItemHovered() && IsMouseClicked(mouse_button))
3612  OpenPopupEx(str_id, false);
3613  return BeginPopup(str_id);
3614 }

3633 static bool BeginChildEx(const char* name, ImGuiID id, const ImVec2& size_arg, bool border, ImGuiWindowFlags extra_flags)
3634 {
3635  ImGuiWindow* window = ImGui::GetCurrentWindow();
3636  ImGuiWindowFlags flags = ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar|ImGuiWindowFlags_NoResize|ImGuiWindowFlags_NoSavedSettings|ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow;
3637 
3638  const ImVec2 content_avail = ImGui::GetContentRegionAvail();
3639  ImVec2 size = ImFloor(size_arg);
3640  if (size.x <= 0.0f)
3641  {
3642  if (size.x == 0.0f)
3643  flags |= ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindowAutoFitX;
3644  size.x = ImMax(content_avail.x, 4.0f) - fabsf(size.x); // Arbitrary minimum zero-ish child size of 4.0f (0.0f causing too much issues)
3645  }
3646  if (size.y <= 0.0f)
3647  {
3648  if (size.y == 0.0f)
3649  flags |= ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindowAutoFitY;
3650  size.y = ImMax(content_avail.y, 4.0f) - fabsf(size.y);
3651  }
3652  if (border)
3653  flags |= ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders;
3654  flags |= extra_flags;
3655 
3656  char title[256];
3657  if (name)
3658  ImFormatString(title, IM_ARRAYSIZE(title), "%s.%s.%08X", window->Name, name, id);
3659  else
3660  ImFormatString(title, IM_ARRAYSIZE(title), "%s.%08X", window->Name, id);
3661 
3662  bool ret = ImGui::Begin(title, NULL, size, -1.0f, flags);
3663 
3664  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders))
3665  ImGui::GetCurrentWindow()->Flags &= ~ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders;
3666 
3667  return ret;
3668 }
3669 
3670 bool ImGui::BeginChild(const char* str_id, const ImVec2& size_arg, bool border, ImGuiWindowFlags extra_flags)
3671 {
3672  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
3673  return BeginChildEx(str_id, window->GetID(str_id), size_arg, border, extra_flags);
3674 }
3675 
3676 bool ImGui::BeginChild(ImGuiID id, const ImVec2& size_arg, bool border, ImGuiWindowFlags extra_flags)
3677 {
3678  return BeginChildEx(NULL, id, size_arg, border, extra_flags);
3679 }
3680 
3681 void ImGui::EndChild()
3682 {
3683  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
3684 
3685  IM_ASSERT(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow); // Mismatched BeginChild()/EndChild() callss
3686  if ((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox) || window->BeginCount > 1)
3687  {
3688  ImGui::End();
3689  }
3690  else
3691  {
3692  // When using auto-filling child window, we don't provide full width/height to ItemSize so that it doesn't feed back into automatic size-fitting.
3693  ImVec2 sz = GetWindowSize();
3694  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindowAutoFitX) // Arbitrary minimum zero-ish child size of 4.0f causes less trouble than a 0.0f
3695  sz.x = ImMax(4.0f, sz.x);
3696  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindowAutoFitY)
3697  sz.y = ImMax(4.0f, sz.y);
3698 
3699  ImGui::End();
3700 
3701  window = GetCurrentWindow();
3702  ImRect bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + sz);
3703  ItemSize(sz);
3704  ItemAdd(bb, NULL);
3705  }
3706 }

3726 // Save and compare stack sizes on Begin()/End() to detect usage errors
3727 static void CheckStacksSize(ImGuiWindow* window, bool write)
3728 {
3729  // NOT checking: DC.ItemWidth, DC.AllowKeyboardFocus, DC.ButtonRepeat, DC.TextWrapPos (per window) to allow user to conveniently push once and not pop (they are cleared on Begin)
3730  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3731  int* p_backup = &window->DC.StackSizesBackup[0];
3732  { int current = window->IDStack.Size; if (write) *p_backup = current; else IM_ASSERT(*p_backup == current && "PushID/PopID or TreeNode/TreePop Mismatch!"); p_backup++; } // Too few or too many PopID()/TreePop()
3733  { int current = window->DC.GroupStack.Size; if (write) *p_backup = current; else IM_ASSERT(*p_backup == current && "BeginGroup/EndGroup Mismatch!"); p_backup++; } // Too few or too many EndGroup()
3734  { int current = g.CurrentPopupStack.Size; if (write) *p_backup = current; else IM_ASSERT(*p_backup == current && "BeginMenu/EndMenu or BeginPopup/EndPopup Mismatch"); p_backup++;}// Too few or too many EndMenu()/EndPopup()
3735  { int current = g.ColorModifiers.Size; if (write) *p_backup = current; else IM_ASSERT(*p_backup == current && "PushStyleColor/PopStyleColor Mismatch!"); p_backup++; } // Too few or too many PopStyleColor()
3736  { int current = g.StyleModifiers.Size; if (write) *p_backup = current; else IM_ASSERT(*p_backup == current && "PushStyleVar/PopStyleVar Mismatch!"); p_backup++; } // Too few or too many PopStyleVar()
3737  { int current = g.FontStack.Size; if (write) *p_backup = current; else IM_ASSERT(*p_backup == current && "PushFont/PopFont Mismatch!"); p_backup++; } // Too few or too many PopFont()
3738  IM_ASSERT(p_backup == window->DC.StackSizesBackup + IM_ARRAYSIZE(window->DC.StackSizesBackup));
3739 }
3740 
3741 static ImVec2 FindBestPopupWindowPos(const ImVec2& base_pos, const ImVec2& size, int* last_dir, const ImRect& r_inner)
3742 {
3743  const ImGuiStyle& style = GImGui->Style;
3744 
3745  // Clamp into visible area while not overlapping the cursor. Safety padding is optional if our popup size won't fit without it.
3746  ImVec2 safe_padding = style.DisplaySafeAreaPadding;
3747  ImRect r_outer(GetVisibleRect());
3748  r_outer.Reduce(ImVec2((size.x - r_outer.GetWidth() > safe_padding.x*2) ? safe_padding.x : 0.0f, (size.y - r_outer.GetHeight() > safe_padding.y*2) ? safe_padding.y : 0.0f));
3749  ImVec2 base_pos_clamped = ImClamp(base_pos, r_outer.Min, r_outer.Max - size);
3750 
3751  for (int n = (*last_dir != -1) ? -1 : 0; n < 4; n++) // Last, Right, down, up, left. (Favor last used direction).
3752  {
3753  const int dir = (n == -1) ? *last_dir : n;
3754  ImRect rect(dir == 0 ? r_inner.Max.x : r_outer.Min.x, dir == 1 ? r_inner.Max.y : r_outer.Min.y, dir == 3 ? r_inner.Min.x : r_outer.Max.x, dir == 2 ? r_inner.Min.y : r_outer.Max.y);
3755  if (rect.GetWidth() < size.x || rect.GetHeight() < size.y)
3756  continue;
3757  *last_dir = dir;
3758  return ImVec2(dir == 0 ? r_inner.Max.x : dir == 3 ? r_inner.Min.x - size.x : base_pos_clamped.x, dir == 1 ? r_inner.Max.y : dir == 2 ? r_inner.Min.y - size.y : base_pos_clamped.y);
3759  }
3760 
3761  // Fallback, try to keep within display
3762  *last_dir = -1;
3763  ImVec2 pos = base_pos;
3764  pos.x = ImMax(ImMin(pos.x + size.x, r_outer.Max.x) - size.x, r_outer.Min.x);
3765  pos.y = ImMax(ImMin(pos.y + size.y, r_outer.Max.y) - size.y, r_outer.Min.y);
3766  return pos;
3767 }
3768 
3769 ImGuiWindow* ImGui::FindWindowByName(const char* name)
3770 {
3771  // FIXME-OPT: Store sorted hashes -> pointers so we can do a bissection in a contiguous block
3772  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3773  ImGuiID id = ImHash(name, 0);
3774  for (int i = 0; i < g.Windows.Size; i++)
3775  if (g.Windows[i]->ID == id)
3776  return g.Windows[i];
3777  return NULL;
3778 }
3779 
3780 static ImGuiWindow* CreateNewWindow(const char* name, ImVec2 size, ImGuiWindowFlags flags)
3781 {
3782  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3783 
3784  // Create window the first time
3785  ImGuiWindow* window = (ImGuiWindow*)ImGui::MemAlloc(sizeof(ImGuiWindow));
3786  IM_PLACEMENT_NEW(window) ImGuiWindow(name);
3787  window->Flags = flags;
3788 
3789  if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoSavedSettings)
3790  {
3791  // User can disable loading and saving of settings. Tooltip and child windows also don't store settings.
3792  window->Size = window->SizeFull = size;
3793  }
3794  else
3795  {
3796  // Retrieve settings from .ini file
3797  // Use SetWindowPos() or SetNextWindowPos() with the appropriate condition flag to change the initial position of a window.
3798  window->PosFloat = ImVec2(60, 60);
3799  window->Pos = ImVec2((float)(int)window->PosFloat.x, (float)(int)window->PosFloat.y);
3800 
3801  ImGuiIniData* settings = FindWindowSettings(name);
3802  if (!settings)
3803  {
3804  settings = AddWindowSettings(name);
3805  }
3806  else
3807  {
3808  window->SetWindowPosAllowFlags &= ~ImGuiSetCond_FirstUseEver;
3809  window->SetWindowSizeAllowFlags &= ~ImGuiSetCond_FirstUseEver;
3810  window->SetWindowCollapsedAllowFlags &= ~ImGuiSetCond_FirstUseEver;
3811  }
3812 
3813  if (settings->Pos.x != FLT_MAX)
3814  {
3815  window->PosFloat = settings->Pos;
3816  window->Pos = ImVec2((float)(int)window->PosFloat.x, (float)(int)window->PosFloat.y);
3817  window->Collapsed = settings->Collapsed;
3818  }
3819 
3820  if (ImLengthSqr(settings->Size) > 0.00001f && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoResize))
3821  size = settings->Size;
3822  window->Size = window->SizeFull = size;
3823  }
3824 
3825  if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize) != 0)
3826  {
3827  window->AutoFitFramesX = window->AutoFitFramesY = 2;
3828  window->AutoFitOnlyGrows = false;
3829  }
3830  else
3831  {
3832  if (window->Size.x <= 0.0f)
3833  window->AutoFitFramesX = 2;
3834  if (window->Size.y <= 0.0f)
3835  window->AutoFitFramesY = 2;
3836  window->AutoFitOnlyGrows = (window->AutoFitFramesX > 0) || (window->AutoFitFramesY > 0);
3837  }
3838 
3839  if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoBringToFrontOnFocus)
3840  g.Windows.insert(g.Windows.begin(), window); // Quite slow but rare and only once
3841  else
3842  g.Windows.push_back(window);
3843  return window;
3844 }
3845 
3846 static void ApplySizeFullWithConstraint(ImGuiWindow* window, ImVec2 new_size)
3847 {
3848  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3849  if (g.SetNextWindowSizeConstraint)
3850  {
3851  // Using -1,-1 on either X/Y axis to preserve the current size.
3852  ImRect cr = g.SetNextWindowSizeConstraintRect;
3853  new_size.x = (cr.Min.x >= 0 && cr.Max.x >= 0) ? ImClamp(new_size.x, cr.Min.x, cr.Max.x) : window->SizeFull.x;
3854  new_size.y = (cr.Min.y >= 0 && cr.Max.y >= 0) ? ImClamp(new_size.y, cr.Min.y, cr.Max.y) : window->SizeFull.y;
3855  if (g.SetNextWindowSizeConstraintCallback)
3856  {
3857  ImGuiSizeConstraintCallbackData data;
3858  data.UserData = g.SetNextWindowSizeConstraintCallbackUserData;
3859  data.Pos = window->Pos;
3860  data.CurrentSize = window->SizeFull;
3861  data.DesiredSize = new_size;
3862  g.SetNextWindowSizeConstraintCallback(&data);
3863  new_size = data.DesiredSize;
3864  }
3865  }
3866  if (!(window->Flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow | ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize)))
3867  new_size = ImMax(new_size, g.Style.WindowMinSize);
3868  window->SizeFull = new_size;
3869 }
3870 
3871 // Push a new ImGui window to add widgets to.
3872 // - A default window called "Debug" is automatically stacked at the beginning of every frame so you can use widgets without explicitly calling a Begin/End pair.
3873 // - Begin/End can be called multiple times during the frame with the same window name to append content.
3874 // - 'size_on_first_use' for a regular window denote the initial size for first-time creation (no saved data) and isn't that useful. Use SetNextWindowSize() prior to calling Begin() for more flexible window manipulation.
3875 // - The window name is used as a unique identifier to preserve window information across frames (and save rudimentary information to the .ini file).
3876 // You can use the "##" or "###" markers to use the same label with different id, or same id with different label. See documentation at the top of this file.
3877 // - Return false when window is collapsed, so you can early out in your code. You always need to call ImGui::End() even if false is returned.
3878 // - Passing 'bool* p_open' displays a Close button on the upper-right corner of the window, the pointed value will be set to false when the button is pressed.
3879 // - Passing non-zero 'size' is roughly equivalent to calling SetNextWindowSize(size, ImGuiSetCond_FirstUseEver) prior to calling Begin().
3880 bool ImGui::Begin(const char* name, bool* p_open, ImGuiWindowFlags flags)
3881 {
3882  return ImGui::Begin(name, p_open, ImVec2(0.f, 0.f), -1.0f, flags);
3883 }
3884 
3885 bool ImGui::Begin(const char* name, bool* p_open, const ImVec2& size_on_first_use, float bg_alpha, ImGuiWindowFlags flags)
3886 {
3887  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
3888  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
3889  IM_ASSERT(name != NULL); // Window name required
3890  IM_ASSERT(g.Initialized); // Forgot to call ImGui::NewFrame()
3891  IM_ASSERT(g.FrameCountEnded != g.FrameCount); // Called ImGui::Render() or ImGui::EndFrame() and haven't called ImGui::NewFrame() again yet
3892 
3893  if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoInputs)
3894  flags |= ImGuiWindowFlags_NoMove | ImGuiWindowFlags_NoResize;
3895 
3896  // Find or create
3897  bool window_is_new = false;
3898  ImGuiWindow* window = FindWindowByName(name);
3899  if (!window)
3900  {
3901  window = CreateNewWindow(name, size_on_first_use, flags);
3902  window_is_new = true;
3903  }
3904 
3905  const int current_frame = ImGui::GetFrameCount();
3906  const bool first_begin_of_the_frame = (window->LastFrameActive != current_frame);
3907  if (first_begin_of_the_frame)
3908  window->Flags = (ImGuiWindowFlags)flags;
3909  else
3910  flags = window->Flags;
3911 
3912  // Add to stack
3913  ImGuiWindow* parent_window = !g.CurrentWindowStack.empty() ? g.CurrentWindowStack.back() : NULL;
3914  g.CurrentWindowStack.push_back(window);
3915  SetCurrentWindow(window);
3916  CheckStacksSize(window, true);
3917  IM_ASSERT(parent_window != NULL || !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow));
3918 
3919  bool window_was_active = (window->LastFrameActive == current_frame - 1); // Not using !WasActive because the implicit "Debug" window would always toggle off->on
3920  if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup)
3921  {
3922  ImGuiPopupRef& popup_ref = g.OpenPopupStack[g.CurrentPopupStack.Size];
3923  window_was_active &= (window->PopupId == popup_ref.PopupId);
3924  window_was_active &= (window == popup_ref.Window);
3925  popup_ref.Window = window;
3926  g.CurrentPopupStack.push_back(popup_ref);
3927  window->PopupId = popup_ref.PopupId;
3928  }
3929 
3930  const bool window_appearing_after_being_hidden = (window->HiddenFrames == 1);
3931 
3932  // Process SetNextWindow***() calls
3933  bool window_pos_set_by_api = false, window_size_set_by_api = false;
3934  if (g.SetNextWindowPosCond)
3935  {
3936  const ImVec2 backup_cursor_pos = window->DC.CursorPos; // FIXME: not sure of the exact reason of this saving/restore anymore :( need to look into that.
3937  if (!window_was_active || window_appearing_after_being_hidden) window->SetWindowPosAllowFlags |= ImGuiSetCond_Appearing;
3938  window_pos_set_by_api = (window->SetWindowPosAllowFlags & g.SetNextWindowPosCond) != 0;
3939  if (window_pos_set_by_api && ImLengthSqr(g.SetNextWindowPosVal - ImVec2(-FLT_MAX,-FLT_MAX)) < 0.001f)
3940  {
3941  window->SetWindowPosCenterWanted = true; // May be processed on the next frame if this is our first frame and we are measuring size
3942  window->SetWindowPosAllowFlags &= ~(ImGuiSetCond_Once | ImGuiSetCond_FirstUseEver | ImGuiSetCond_Appearing);
3943  }
3944  else
3945  {
3946  SetWindowPos(window, g.SetNextWindowPosVal, g.SetNextWindowPosCond);
3947  }
3948  window->DC.CursorPos = backup_cursor_pos;
3949  g.SetNextWindowPosCond = 0;
3950  }
3951  if (g.SetNextWindowSizeCond)
3952  {
3953  if (!window_was_active || window_appearing_after_being_hidden) window->SetWindowSizeAllowFlags |= ImGuiSetCond_Appearing;
3954  window_size_set_by_api = (window->SetWindowSizeAllowFlags & g.SetNextWindowSizeCond) != 0;
3955  SetWindowSize(window, g.SetNextWindowSizeVal, g.SetNextWindowSizeCond);
3956  g.SetNextWindowSizeCond = 0;
3957  }
3958  if (g.SetNextWindowContentSizeCond)
3959  {
3960  window->SizeContentsExplicit = g.SetNextWindowContentSizeVal;
3961  g.SetNextWindowContentSizeCond = 0;
3962  }
3963  else if (first_begin_of_the_frame)
3964  {
3965  window->SizeContentsExplicit = ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f);
3966  }
3967  if (g.SetNextWindowCollapsedCond)
3968  {
3969  if (!window_was_active || window_appearing_after_being_hidden) window->SetWindowCollapsedAllowFlags |= ImGuiSetCond_Appearing;
3970  SetWindowCollapsed(window, g.SetNextWindowCollapsedVal, g.SetNextWindowCollapsedCond);
3971  g.SetNextWindowCollapsedCond = 0;
3972  }
3973  if (g.SetNextWindowFocus)
3974  {
3975  ImGui::SetWindowFocus();
3976  g.SetNextWindowFocus = false;
3977  }
3978 
3979  // Update known root window (if we are a child window, otherwise window == window->RootWindow)
3980  int root_idx, root_non_popup_idx;
3981  for (root_idx = g.CurrentWindowStack.Size - 1; root_idx > 0; root_idx--)
3982  if (!(g.CurrentWindowStack[root_idx]->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow))
3983  break;
3984  for (root_non_popup_idx = root_idx; root_non_popup_idx > 0; root_non_popup_idx--)
3985  if (!(g.CurrentWindowStack[root_non_popup_idx]->Flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow | ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup)))
3986  break;
3987  window->ParentWindow = parent_window;
3988  window->RootWindow = g.CurrentWindowStack[root_idx];
3989  window->RootNonPopupWindow = g.CurrentWindowStack[root_non_popup_idx]; // This is merely for displaying the TitleBgActive color.
3990 
3991  // When reusing window again multiple times a frame, just append content (don't need to setup again)
3992  if (first_begin_of_the_frame)
3993  {
3994  window->Active = true;
3995  window->IndexWithinParent = 0;
3996  window->BeginCount = 0;
3997  window->ClipRect = ImVec4(-FLT_MAX,-FLT_MAX,+FLT_MAX,+FLT_MAX);
3998  window->LastFrameActive = current_frame;
3999  window->IDStack.resize(1);
4000 
4001  // Clear draw list, setup texture, outer clipping rectangle
4002  window->DrawList->Clear();
4003  window->DrawList->PushTextureID(g.Font->ContainerAtlas->TexID);
4004  ImRect fullscreen_rect(GetVisibleRect());
4005  if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) && !(flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox|ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup)))
4006  PushClipRect(parent_window->ClipRect.Min, parent_window->ClipRect.Max, true);
4007  else
4008  PushClipRect(fullscreen_rect.Min, fullscreen_rect.Max, true);
4009 
4010  if (!window_was_active)
4011  {
4012  // Popup first latch mouse position, will position itself when it appears next frame
4013  window->AutoPosLastDirection = -1;
4014  if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) != 0 && !window_pos_set_by_api)
4015  window->PosFloat = g.IO.MousePos;
4016  }
4017 
4018  // Collapse window by double-clicking on title bar
4019  // At this point we don't have a clipping rectangle setup yet, so we can use the title bar area for hit detection and drawing
4020  if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoCollapse))
4021  {
4022  ImRect title_bar_rect = window->TitleBarRect();
4023  if (g.HoveredWindow == window && IsMouseHoveringRect(title_bar_rect.Min, title_bar_rect.Max) && g.IO.MouseDoubleClicked[0])
4024  {
4025  window->Collapsed = !window->Collapsed;
4026  if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoSavedSettings))
4027  MarkIniSettingsDirty();
4028  FocusWindow(window);
4029  }
4030  }
4031  else
4032  {
4033  window->Collapsed = false;
4034  }
4035 
4036  // SIZE
4037 
4038  // Save contents size from last frame for auto-fitting (unless explicitly specified)
4039  window->SizeContents.x = (float)(int)((window->SizeContentsExplicit.x != 0.0f) ? window->SizeContentsExplicit.x : ((window_is_new ? 0.0f : window->DC.CursorMaxPos.x - window->Pos.x) + window->Scroll.x));
4040  window->SizeContents.y = (float)(int)((window->SizeContentsExplicit.y != 0.0f) ? window->SizeContentsExplicit.y : ((window_is_new ? 0.0f : window->DC.CursorMaxPos.y - window->Pos.y) + window->Scroll.y));
4041 
4042  // Hide popup/tooltip window when first appearing while we measure size (because we recycle them)
4043  if (window->HiddenFrames > 0)
4044  window->HiddenFrames--;
4045  if ((flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup | ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip)) != 0 && !window_was_active)
4046  {
4047  window->HiddenFrames = 1;
4048  if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize)
4049  {
4050  if (!window_size_set_by_api)
4051  window->Size = window->SizeFull = ImVec2(0.f, 0.f);
4052  window->SizeContents = ImVec2(0.f, 0.f);
4053  }
4054  }
4055 
4056  // Lock window padding so that altering the ShowBorders flag for children doesn't have side-effects.
4057  window->WindowPadding = ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) && !(flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysUseWindowPadding | ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders | ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox | ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup))) ? ImVec2(0,0) : style.WindowPadding;
4058 
4059  // Calculate auto-fit size
4060  ImVec2 size_auto_fit;
4061  if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip) != 0)
4062  {
4063  // Tooltip always resize. We keep the spacing symmetric on both axises for aesthetic purpose.
4064  size_auto_fit = window->SizeContents + window->WindowPadding - ImVec2(0.0f, style.ItemSpacing.y);
4065  }
4066  else
4067  {
4068  size_auto_fit = ImClamp(window->SizeContents + window->WindowPadding, style.WindowMinSize, ImMax(style.WindowMinSize, g.IO.DisplaySize - g.Style.DisplaySafeAreaPadding));
4069 
4070  // Handling case of auto fit window not fitting in screen on one axis, we are growing auto fit size on the other axis to compensate for expected scrollbar. FIXME: Might turn bigger than DisplaySize-WindowPadding.
4071  if (size_auto_fit.x < window->SizeContents.x && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollbar) && (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_HorizontalScrollbar))
4072  size_auto_fit.y += style.ScrollbarSize;
4073  if (size_auto_fit.y < window->SizeContents.y && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollbar))
4074  size_auto_fit.x += style.ScrollbarSize;
4075  size_auto_fit.y = ImMax(size_auto_fit.y - style.ItemSpacing.y, 0.0f);
4076  }
4077 
4078  // Handle automatic resize
4079  if (window->Collapsed)
4080  {
4081  // We still process initial auto-fit on collapsed windows to get a window width,
4082  // But otherwise we don't honor ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize when collapsed.
4083  if (window->AutoFitFramesX > 0)
4084  window->SizeFull.x = window->AutoFitOnlyGrows ? ImMax(window->SizeFull.x, size_auto_fit.x) : size_auto_fit.x;
4085  if (window->AutoFitFramesY > 0)
4086  window->SizeFull.y = window->AutoFitOnlyGrows ? ImMax(window->SizeFull.y, size_auto_fit.y) : size_auto_fit.y;
4087  }
4088  else
4089  {
4090  if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize) && !window_size_set_by_api)
4091  {
4092  window->SizeFull = size_auto_fit;
4093  }
4094  else if ((window->AutoFitFramesX > 0 || window->AutoFitFramesY > 0) && !window_size_set_by_api)
4095  {
4096  // Auto-fit only grows during the first few frames
4097  if (window->AutoFitFramesX > 0)
4098  window->SizeFull.x = window->AutoFitOnlyGrows ? ImMax(window->SizeFull.x, size_auto_fit.x) : size_auto_fit.x;
4099  if (window->AutoFitFramesY > 0)
4100  window->SizeFull.y = window->AutoFitOnlyGrows ? ImMax(window->SizeFull.y, size_auto_fit.y) : size_auto_fit.y;
4101  if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoSavedSettings))
4102  MarkIniSettingsDirty();
4103  }
4104  }
4105 
4106  // Apply minimum/maximum window size constraints and final size
4107  ApplySizeFullWithConstraint(window, window->SizeFull);
4108  window->Size = window->Collapsed ? window->TitleBarRect().GetSize() : window->SizeFull;
4109 
4110  // POSITION
4111 
4112  // Position child window
4113  if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow)
4114  {
4115  window->IndexWithinParent = parent_window->DC.ChildWindows.Size;
4116  parent_window->DC.ChildWindows.push_back(window);
4117  }
4118  if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup))
4119  {
4120  window->Pos = window->PosFloat = parent_window->DC.CursorPos;
4121  window->Size = window->SizeFull = size_on_first_use; // NB: argument name 'size_on_first_use' misleading here, it's really just 'size' as provided by user passed via BeginChild()->Begin().
4122  }
4123 
4124  bool window_pos_center = false;
4125  window_pos_center |= (window->SetWindowPosCenterWanted && window->HiddenFrames == 0);
4126  window_pos_center |= ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Modal) && !window_pos_set_by_api && window_appearing_after_being_hidden);
4127  if (window_pos_center)
4128  {
4129  // Center (any sort of window)
4130  SetWindowPos(window, ImMax(style.DisplaySafeAreaPadding, fullscreen_rect.GetCenter() - window->SizeFull * 0.5f), 0);
4131  }
4132  else if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu)
4133  {
4134  // Child menus typically request _any_ position within the parent menu item, and then our FindBestPopupWindowPos() function will move the new menu outside the parent bounds.
4135  // This is how we end up with child menus appearing (most-commonly) on the right of the parent menu.
4136  IM_ASSERT(window_pos_set_by_api);
4137  float horizontal_overlap = style.ItemSpacing.x; // We want some overlap to convey the relative depth of each popup (currently the amount of overlap it is hard-coded to style.ItemSpacing.x, may need to introduce another style value).
4138  ImRect rect_to_avoid;
4139  if (parent_window->DC.MenuBarAppending)
4140  rect_to_avoid = ImRect(-FLT_MAX, parent_window->Pos.y + parent_window->TitleBarHeight(), FLT_MAX, parent_window->Pos.y + parent_window->TitleBarHeight() + parent_window->MenuBarHeight());
4141  else
4142  rect_to_avoid = ImRect(parent_window->Pos.x + horizontal_overlap, -FLT_MAX, parent_window->Pos.x + parent_window->Size.x - horizontal_overlap - parent_window->ScrollbarSizes.x, FLT_MAX);
4143  window->PosFloat = FindBestPopupWindowPos(window->PosFloat, window->Size, &window->AutoPosLastDirection, rect_to_avoid);
4144  }
4145  else if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) != 0 && !window_pos_set_by_api && window_appearing_after_being_hidden)
4146  {
4147  ImRect rect_to_avoid(window->PosFloat.x - 1, window->PosFloat.y - 1, window->PosFloat.x + 1, window->PosFloat.y + 1);
4148  window->PosFloat = FindBestPopupWindowPos(window->PosFloat, window->Size, &window->AutoPosLastDirection, rect_to_avoid);
4149  }
4150 
4151  // Position tooltip (always follows mouse)
4152  if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip) != 0 && !window_pos_set_by_api)
4153  {
4154  ImRect rect_to_avoid(g.IO.MousePos.x - 16, g.IO.MousePos.y - 8, g.IO.MousePos.x + 24, g.IO.MousePos.y + 24); // FIXME: Completely hard-coded. Perhaps center on cursor hit-point instead?
4155  window->PosFloat = FindBestPopupWindowPos(g.IO.MousePos, window->Size, &window->AutoPosLastDirection, rect_to_avoid);
4156  if (window->AutoPosLastDirection == -1)
4157  window->PosFloat = g.IO.MousePos + ImVec2(2,2); // If there's not enough room, for tooltip we prefer avoiding the cursor at all cost even if it means that part of the tooltip won't be visible.
4158  }
4159 
4160  // Clamp position so it stays visible
4161  if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip))
4162  {
4163  if (!window_pos_set_by_api && window->AutoFitFramesX <= 0 && window->AutoFitFramesY <= 0 && g.IO.DisplaySize.x > 0.0f && g.IO.DisplaySize.y > 0.0f) // Ignore zero-sized display explicitly to avoid losing positions if a window manager reports zero-sized window when initializing or minimizing.
4164  {
4165  ImVec2 padding = ImMax(style.DisplayWindowPadding, style.DisplaySafeAreaPadding);
4166  window->PosFloat = ImMax(window->PosFloat + window->Size, padding) - window->Size;
4167  window->PosFloat = ImMin(window->PosFloat, g.IO.DisplaySize - padding);
4168  }
4169  }
4170  window->Pos = ImVec2((float)(int)window->PosFloat.x, (float)(int)window->PosFloat.y);
4171 
4172  // Default item width. Make it proportional to window size if window manually resizes
4173  if (window->Size.x > 0.0f && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize))
4174  window->ItemWidthDefault = (float)(int)(window->Size.x * 0.65f);
4175  else
4176  window->ItemWidthDefault = (float)(int)(g.FontSize * 16.0f);
4177 
4178  // Prepare for focus requests
4179  window->FocusIdxAllRequestCurrent = (window->FocusIdxAllRequestNext == INT_MAX || window->FocusIdxAllCounter == -1) ? INT_MAX : (window->FocusIdxAllRequestNext + (window->FocusIdxAllCounter+1)) % (window->FocusIdxAllCounter+1);
4180  window->FocusIdxTabRequestCurrent = (window->FocusIdxTabRequestNext == INT_MAX || window->FocusIdxTabCounter == -1) ? INT_MAX : (window->FocusIdxTabRequestNext + (window->FocusIdxTabCounter+1)) % (window->FocusIdxTabCounter+1);
4181  window->FocusIdxAllCounter = window->FocusIdxTabCounter = -1;
4182  window->FocusIdxAllRequestNext = window->FocusIdxTabRequestNext = INT_MAX;
4183 
4184  // Apply scrolling
4185  if (window->ScrollTarget.x < FLT_MAX)
4186  {
4187  window->Scroll.x = window->ScrollTarget.x;
4188  window->ScrollTarget.x = FLT_MAX;
4189  }
4190  if (window->ScrollTarget.y < FLT_MAX)
4191  {
4192  float center_ratio = window->ScrollTargetCenterRatio.y;
4193  window->Scroll.y = window->ScrollTarget.y - ((1.0f - center_ratio) * (window->TitleBarHeight() + window->MenuBarHeight())) - (center_ratio * window->SizeFull.y);
4194  window->ScrollTarget.y = FLT_MAX;
4195  }
4196  window->Scroll = ImMax(window->Scroll, ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f));
4197  if (!window->Collapsed && !window->SkipItems)

4199

4201  if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Modal) != 0 && window == GetFrontMostModalRootWindow())

4203

4205  ImRect title_bar_rect = window->TitleBarRect();

4207  if (window->Collapsed)
4208  {
4209  // Draw title bar only
4210  RenderFrame(title_bar_rect.GetTL(), title_bar_rect.GetBR(), GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_TitleBgCollapsed), true, window_rounding);
4211  }
4212  else
4213  {

4215  const float resize_corner_size = ImMax(g.FontSize * 1.35f, window_rounding + 1.0f + g.FontSize * 0.2f);
4216  if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize) && window->AutoFitFramesX <= 0 && window->AutoFitFramesY <= 0 && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoResize))

4224  resize_col = GetColorU32(held ? ImGuiCol_ResizeGripActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_ResizeGripHovered : ImGuiCol_ResizeGrip);

4232  ApplySizeFullWithConstraint(window, size_auto_fit);

4234  MarkIniSettingsDirty();

4240  ApplySizeFullWithConstraint(window, (g.IO.MousePos - g.ActiveIdClickOffset + resize_rect.GetSize()) - window->Pos);
4241  if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoSavedSettings))

4246  title_bar_rect = window->TitleBarRect();

4251  window->ScrollbarX = (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysHorizontalScrollbar) || ((window->SizeContents.x > window->Size.x - (window->ScrollbarY ? style.ScrollbarSize : 0.0f) - window->WindowPadding.x) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollbar) && (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_HorizontalScrollbar));
4252  window->ScrollbarSizes = ImVec2(window->ScrollbarY ? style.ScrollbarSize : 0.0f, window->ScrollbarX ? style.ScrollbarSize : 0.0f);

4259  else if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip) != 0 || (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) != 0)

4269

4280  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(menu_bar_rect.GetTL(), menu_bar_rect.GetBR(), GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_MenuBarBg), (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) ? window_rounding : 0.0f, ImGuiCorner_TopLeft|ImGuiCorner_TopRight);
4281  }
4282

4284  if (window->ScrollbarX)
4285  Scrollbar(window, true);
4286  if (window->ScrollbarY)
4287  Scrollbar(window, false);
4288 
4289  // Render resize grip
4290  // (after the input handling so we don't have a frame of latency)
4291  if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoResize))
4292  {
4293  const ImVec2 br = window->Rect().GetBR();
4294  window->DrawList->PathLineTo(br + ImVec2(-resize_corner_size, -window->BorderSize));
4295  window->DrawList->PathLineTo(br + ImVec2(-window->BorderSize, -resize_corner_size));
4296  window->DrawList->PathArcToFast(ImVec2(br.x - window_rounding - window->BorderSize, br.y - window_rounding - window->BorderSize), window_rounding, 0, 3);
4297  window->DrawList->PathFillConvex(resize_col);
4298  }
4299 
4300  // Borders
4301  if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders)
4302  {
4303  window->DrawList->AddRect(window->Pos+ImVec2(1,1), window->Pos+window->Size+ImVec2(1,1), GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_BorderShadow), window_rounding);
4304  window->DrawList->AddRect(window->Pos, window->Pos+window->Size, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Border), window_rounding);
4305  if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar))
4306  window->DrawList->AddLine(title_bar_rect.GetBL()+ImVec2(1,0), title_bar_rect.GetBR()-ImVec2(1,0), GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Border));
4307  }
4308  }
4309 
4310  // Update ContentsRegionMax. All the variable it depends on are set above in this function.
4311  window->ContentsRegionRect.Min.x = -window->Scroll.x + window->WindowPadding.x;
4312  window->ContentsRegionRect.Min.y = -window->Scroll.y + window->WindowPadding.y + window->TitleBarHeight() + window->MenuBarHeight();
4313  window->ContentsRegionRect.Max.x = -window->Scroll.x - window->WindowPadding.x + (window->SizeContentsExplicit.x != 0.0f ? window->SizeContentsExplicit.x : (window->Size.x - window->ScrollbarSizes.x));
4314  window->ContentsRegionRect.Max.y = -window->Scroll.y - window->WindowPadding.y + (window->SizeContentsExplicit.y != 0.0f ? window->SizeContentsExplicit.y : (window->Size.y - window->ScrollbarSizes.y));
4315 
4316  // Setup drawing context
4317  window->DC.IndentX = 0.0f + window->WindowPadding.x - window->Scroll.x;
4318  window->DC.GroupOffsetX = 0.0f;
4319  window->DC.ColumnsOffsetX = 0.0f;
4320  window->DC.CursorStartPos = window->Pos + ImVec2(window->DC.IndentX + window->DC.ColumnsOffsetX, window->TitleBarHeight() + window->MenuBarHeight() + window->WindowPadding.y - window->Scroll.y);
4321  window->DC.CursorPos = window->DC.CursorStartPos;
4322  window->DC.CursorPosPrevLine = window->DC.CursorPos;
4323  window->DC.CursorMaxPos = window->DC.CursorStartPos;
4324  window->DC.CurrentLineHeight = window->DC.PrevLineHeight = 0.0f;
4325  window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset = window->DC.PrevLineTextBaseOffset = 0.0f;
4326  window->DC.MenuBarAppending = false;
4327  window->DC.MenuBarOffsetX = ImMax(window->WindowPadding.x, style.ItemSpacing.x);
4328  window->DC.LogLinePosY = window->DC.CursorPos.y - 9999.0f;
4329  window->DC.ChildWindows.resize(0);
4330  window->DC.LayoutType = ImGuiLayoutType_Vertical;
4331  window->DC.ItemWidth = window->ItemWidthDefault;
4332  window->DC.TextWrapPos = -1.0f; // disabled
4333  window->DC.AllowKeyboardFocus = true;
4334  window->DC.ButtonRepeat = false;
4335  window->DC.ItemWidthStack.resize(0);
4336  window->DC.AllowKeyboardFocusStack.resize(0);
4337  window->DC.ButtonRepeatStack.resize(0);
4338  window->DC.TextWrapPosStack.resize(0);
4339  window->DC.ColumnsCurrent = 0;
4340  window->DC.ColumnsCount = 1;
4341  window->DC.ColumnsStartPosY = window->DC.CursorPos.y;
4342  window->DC.ColumnsCellMinY = window->DC.ColumnsCellMaxY = window->DC.ColumnsStartPosY;
4343  window->DC.TreeDepth = 0;
4344  window->DC.StateStorage = &window->StateStorage;
4345  window->DC.GroupStack.resize(0);
4346  window->DC.ColorEditMode = ImGuiColorEditMode_UserSelect;
4347  window->MenuColumns.Update(3, style.ItemSpacing.x, !window_was_active);
4348 
4349  if (window->AutoFitFramesX > 0)
4350  window->AutoFitFramesX--;
4351  if (window->AutoFitFramesY > 0)
4352  window->AutoFitFramesY--;
4353 
4354  // New windows appears in front (we need to do that AFTER setting DC.CursorStartPos so our initial navigation reference rectangle can start around there)
4355  if (!window_was_active && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoFocusOnAppearing))
4356  if (!(flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow|ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip)) || (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup))
4357  FocusWindow(window);
4358 
4359  // Title bar
4360  if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar))
4361  {
4362  if (p_open != NULL)
4363  {
4364  const float pad = 2.0f;
4365  const float rad = (window->TitleBarHeight() - pad*2.0f) * 0.5f;
4366  if (CloseButton(window->GetID("#CLOSE"), window->Rect().GetTR() + ImVec2(-pad - rad, pad + rad), rad))
4367  *p_open = false;
4368  }
4369 
4370  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(name, NULL, true);
4371  if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoCollapse))
4372  RenderCollapseTriangle(window->Pos + style.FramePadding, !window->Collapsed, 1.0f);
4373 
4374  ImVec2 text_min = window->Pos;
4375  ImVec2 text_max = window->Pos + ImVec2(window->Size.x, style.FramePadding.y*2 + text_size.y);
4376  ImRect clip_rect;
4377  clip_rect.Max = ImVec2(window->Pos.x + window->Size.x - (p_open ? title_bar_rect.GetHeight() - 3 : style.FramePadding.x), text_max.y); // Match the size of CloseWindowButton()
4378  float pad_left = (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoCollapse) == 0 ? (style.FramePadding.x + g.FontSize + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x) : style.FramePadding.x;
4379  float pad_right = (p_open != NULL) ? (style.FramePadding.x + g.FontSize + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x) : style.FramePadding.x;
4380  if (style.WindowTitleAlign.x > 0.0f) pad_right = ImLerp(pad_right, pad_left, style.WindowTitleAlign.x);
4381  text_min.x += pad_left;
4382  text_max.x -= pad_right;
4383  clip_rect.Min = ImVec2(text_min.x, window->Pos.y);
4384  RenderTextClipped(text_min, text_max, name, NULL, &text_size, style.WindowTitleAlign, &clip_rect);
4385  }
4386 
4387  // Save clipped aabb so we can access it in constant-time in FindHoveredWindow()
4388  window->WindowRectClipped = window->Rect();
4389  window->WindowRectClipped.Clip(window->ClipRect);
4390 
4391  // Pressing CTRL+C while holding on a window copy its content to the clipboard
4392  // This works but 1. doesn't handle multiple Begin/End pairs, 2. recursing into another Begin/End pair - so we need to work that out and add better logging scope.
4393  // Maybe we can support CTRL+C on every element?
4394  /*
4395  if (g.ActiveId == move_id)
4396  if (g.IO.KeyCtrl && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_C))
4397  ImGui::LogToClipboard();
4398  */
4399  }
4400 
4401  // Inner clipping rectangle
4402  // We set this up after processing the resize grip so that our clip rectangle doesn't lag by a frame
4403  // Note that if our window is collapsed we will end up with a null clipping rectangle which is the correct behavior.
4404  const ImRect title_bar_rect = window->TitleBarRect();
4405  const float border_size = window->BorderSize;
4406  ImRect clip_rect; // Force round to ensure that e.g. (int)(max.x-min.x) in user's render code produce correct result.
4407  clip_rect.Min.x = ImFloor(0.5f + title_bar_rect.Min.x + ImMax(border_size, ImFloor(window->WindowPadding.x*0.5f)));
4408  clip_rect.Min.y = ImFloor(0.5f + title_bar_rect.Max.y + window->MenuBarHeight() + border_size);
4409  clip_rect.Max.x = ImFloor(0.5f + window->Pos.x + window->Size.x - window->ScrollbarSizes.x - ImMax(border_size, ImFloor(window->WindowPadding.x*0.5f)));
4410  clip_rect.Max.y = ImFloor(0.5f + window->Pos.y + window->Size.y - window->ScrollbarSizes.y - border_size);
4411  PushClipRect(clip_rect.Min, clip_rect.Max, true);
4412 
4413  // Clear 'accessed' flag last thing
4414  if (first_begin_of_the_frame)
4415  window->Accessed = false;
4416  window->BeginCount++;
4417  g.SetNextWindowSizeConstraint = false;
4418 
4419  // Child window can be out of sight and have "negative" clip windows.
4420  // Mark them as collapsed so commands are skipped earlier (we can't manually collapse because they have no title bar).
4421  if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow)
4422  {
4423  IM_ASSERT((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) != 0);
4424  window->Collapsed = parent_window && parent_window->Collapsed;
4425 
4426  if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize) && window->AutoFitFramesX <= 0 && window->AutoFitFramesY <= 0)
4427  window->Collapsed |= (window->WindowRectClipped.Min.x >= window->WindowRectClipped.Max.x || window->WindowRectClipped.Min.y >= window->WindowRectClipped.Max.y);
4428 
4429  // We also hide the window from rendering because we've already added its border to the command list.
4430  // (we could perform the check earlier in the function but it is simpler at this point)
4431  if (window->Collapsed)
4432  window->Active = false;
4433  }
4434  if (style.Alpha <= 0.0f)
4435  window->Active = false;
4436 
4437  // Return false if we don't intend to display anything to allow user to perform an early out optimization
4438  window->SkipItems = (window->Collapsed || !window->Active) && window->AutoFitFramesX <= 0 && window->AutoFitFramesY <= 0;
4439  return !window->SkipItems;
4440 }
4441 
4442 void ImGui::End()
4443 {
4444  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
4445  ImGuiWindow* window = g.CurrentWindow;
4446 
4447  if (window->DC.ColumnsCount != 1) // close columns set if any is open
4448  Columns(1, "#CLOSECOLUMNS");
4449  PopClipRect(); // inner window clip rectangle
4450 
4451  // Stop logging
4452  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow)) // FIXME: add more options for scope of logging
4453  LogFinish();
4454 
4455  // Pop
4456  // NB: we don't clear 'window->RootWindow'. The pointer is allowed to live until the next call to Begin().
4457  g.CurrentWindowStack.pop_back();
4458  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup)
4459  g.CurrentPopupStack.pop_back();
4460  CheckStacksSize(window, false);
4461  SetCurrentWindow(g.CurrentWindowStack.empty() ? NULL : g.CurrentWindowStack.back());
4462 }
4463 
4464 // Vertical scrollbar
4465 // The entire piece of code below is rather confusing because:
4466 // - We handle absolute seeking (when first clicking outside the grab) and relative manipulation (afterward or when clicking inside the grab)
4467 // - We store values as normalized ratio and in a form that allows the window content to change while we are holding on a scrollbar
4468 // - We handle both horizontal and vertical scrollbars, which makes the terminology not ideal.
4469 static void Scrollbar(ImGuiWindow* window, bool horizontal)
4470 {
4471  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
4472  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
4473  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(horizontal ? "#SCROLLX" : "#SCROLLY");
4474 
4475  // Render background
4476  bool other_scrollbar = (horizontal ? window->ScrollbarY : window->ScrollbarX);
4477  float other_scrollbar_size_w = other_scrollbar ? style.ScrollbarSize : 0.0f;
4478  const ImRect window_rect = window->Rect();
4479  const float border_size = window->BorderSize;
4480  ImRect bb = horizontal
4481  ? ImRect(window->Pos.x + border_size, window_rect.Max.y - style.ScrollbarSize, window_rect.Max.x - other_scrollbar_size_w - border_size, window_rect.Max.y - border_size)
4482  : ImRect(window_rect.Max.x - style.ScrollbarSize, window->Pos.y + border_size, window_rect.Max.x - border_size, window_rect.Max.y - other_scrollbar_size_w - border_size);
4483  if (!horizontal)
4484  bb.Min.y += window->TitleBarHeight() + ((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_MenuBar) ? window->MenuBarHeight() : 0.0f);
4485  if (bb.GetWidth() <= 0.0f || bb.GetHeight() <= 0.0f)
4486  return;
4487 
4488  float window_rounding = (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) ? style.ChildWindowRounding : style.WindowRounding;
4489  int window_rounding_corners;
4490  if (horizontal)
4491  window_rounding_corners = ImGuiCorner_BottomLeft | (other_scrollbar ? 0 : ImGuiCorner_BottomRight);
4492  else
4493  window_rounding_corners = (((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) && !(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_MenuBar)) ? ImGuiCorner_TopRight : 0) | (other_scrollbar ? 0 : ImGuiCorner_BottomRight);
4494  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(bb.Min, bb.Max, ImGui::GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_ScrollbarBg), window_rounding, window_rounding_corners);
4495  bb.Reduce(ImVec2(ImClamp((float)(int)((bb.Max.x - bb.Min.x - 2.0f) * 0.5f), 0.0f, 3.0f), ImClamp((float)(int)((bb.Max.y - bb.Min.y - 2.0f) * 0.5f), 0.0f, 3.0f)));
4496 
4497  // V denote the main axis of the scrollbar
4498  float scrollbar_size_v = horizontal ? bb.GetWidth() : bb.GetHeight();
4499  float scroll_v = horizontal ? window->Scroll.x : window->Scroll.y;
4500  float win_size_avail_v = (horizontal ? window->Size.x : window->Size.y) - other_scrollbar_size_w;
4501  float win_size_contents_v = horizontal ? window->SizeContents.x : window->SizeContents.y;
4502 
4503  // The grabable box size generally represent the amount visible (vs the total scrollable amount)
4504  // But we maintain a minimum size in pixel to allow for the user to still aim inside.
4505  const float grab_h_pixels = ImMin(ImMax(scrollbar_size_v * ImSaturate(win_size_avail_v / ImMax(win_size_contents_v, win_size_avail_v)), style.GrabMinSize), scrollbar_size_v);
4506  const float grab_h_norm = grab_h_pixels / scrollbar_size_v;
4507 
4508  // Handle input right away. None of the code of Begin() is relying on scrolling position before calling Scrollbar().
4509  bool held = false;
4510  bool hovered = false;
4511  const bool previously_held = (g.ActiveId == id);
4512  ImGui::ButtonBehavior(bb, id, &hovered, &held);
4513 
4514  float scroll_max = ImMax(1.0f, win_size_contents_v - win_size_avail_v);
4515  float scroll_ratio = ImSaturate(scroll_v / scroll_max);
4516  float grab_v_norm = scroll_ratio * (scrollbar_size_v - grab_h_pixels) / scrollbar_size_v;
4517  if (held && grab_h_norm < 1.0f)
4518  {
4519  float scrollbar_pos_v = horizontal ? bb.Min.x : bb.Min.y;
4520  float mouse_pos_v = horizontal ? g.IO.MousePos.x : g.IO.MousePos.y;
4521  float* click_delta_to_grab_center_v = horizontal ? &g.ScrollbarClickDeltaToGrabCenter.x : &g.ScrollbarClickDeltaToGrabCenter.y;
4522 
4523  // Click position in scrollbar normalized space (0.0f->1.0f)
4524  const float clicked_v_norm = ImSaturate((mouse_pos_v - scrollbar_pos_v) / scrollbar_size_v);
4525  ImGui::SetHoveredID(id);
4526 
4527  bool seek_absolute = false;
4528  if (!previously_held)
4529  {
4530  // On initial click calculate the distance between mouse and the center of the grab
4531  if (clicked_v_norm >= grab_v_norm && clicked_v_norm <= grab_v_norm + grab_h_norm)
4532  {
4533  *click_delta_to_grab_center_v = clicked_v_norm - grab_v_norm - grab_h_norm*0.5f;
4534  }
4535  else
4536  {
4537  seek_absolute = true;
4538  *click_delta_to_grab_center_v = 0.0f;
4539  }
4540  }
4541 
4542  // Apply scroll
4543  // It is ok to modify Scroll here because we are being called in Begin() after the calculation of SizeContents and before setting up our starting position
4544  const float scroll_v_norm = ImSaturate((clicked_v_norm - *click_delta_to_grab_center_v - grab_h_norm*0.5f) / (1.0f - grab_h_norm));
4545  scroll_v = (float)(int)(0.5f + scroll_v_norm * scroll_max);//(win_size_contents_v - win_size_v));
4546  if (horizontal)
4547  window->Scroll.x = scroll_v;
4548  else
4549  window->Scroll.y = scroll_v;
4550 
4551  // Update values for rendering
4552  scroll_ratio = ImSaturate(scroll_v / scroll_max);
4553  grab_v_norm = scroll_ratio * (scrollbar_size_v - grab_h_pixels) / scrollbar_size_v;
4554 
4555  // Update distance to grab now that we have seeked and saturated
4556  if (seek_absolute)
4557  *click_delta_to_grab_center_v = clicked_v_norm - grab_v_norm - grab_h_norm*0.5f;
4558  }
4559 
4560  // Render
4561  const ImU32 grab_col = ImGui::GetColorU32(held ? ImGuiCol_ScrollbarGrabActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_ScrollbarGrabHovered : ImGuiCol_ScrollbarGrab);
4562  if (horizontal)
4563  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(ImVec2(ImLerp(bb.Min.x, bb.Max.x, grab_v_norm), bb.Min.y), ImVec2(ImLerp(bb.Min.x, bb.Max.x, grab_v_norm) + grab_h_pixels, bb.Max.y), grab_col, style.ScrollbarRounding);
4564  else
4565  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(ImVec2(bb.Min.x, ImLerp(bb.Min.y, bb.Max.y, grab_v_norm)), ImVec2(bb.Max.x, ImLerp(bb.Min.y, bb.Max.y, grab_v_norm) + grab_h_pixels), grab_col, style.ScrollbarRounding);
4566 }
4567 
4568 // Moving window to front of display (which happens to be back of our sorted list)
4569 void ImGui::FocusWindow(ImGuiWindow* window)
4570 {
4571  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
4572 
4573  // Always mark the window we passed as focused. This is used for keyboard interactions such as tabbing.
4574  g.FocusedWindow = window;
4575 
4576  // Passing NULL allow to disable keyboard focus
4577  if (!window)
4578  return;
4579 
4580  // And move its root window to the top of the pile
4581  if (window->RootWindow)
4582  window = window->RootWindow;
4583 
4584  // Steal focus on active widgets
4585  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) // FIXME: This statement should be unnecessary. Need further testing before removing it..
4586  if (g.ActiveId != 0 && g.ActiveIdWindow && g.ActiveIdWindow->RootWindow != window)
4587  ClearActiveID();
4588 
4589  // Bring to front
4590  if ((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoBringToFrontOnFocus) || g.Windows.back() == window)
4591  return;
4592  for (int i = 0; i < g.Windows.Size; i++)
4593  if (g.Windows[i] == window)
4594  {
4595  g.Windows.erase(g.Windows.begin() + i);
4596  break;
4597  }
4598  g.Windows.push_back(window);
4599 }

4608 static void PushMultiItemsWidths(int components, float w_full)
4609 {
4610  ImGuiWindow* window = ImGui::GetCurrentWindow();
4611  const ImGuiStyle& style = GImGui->Style;
4612  if (w_full <= 0.0f)
4613  w_full = ImGui::CalcItemWidth();
4614  const float w_item_one = ImMax(1.0f, (float)(int)((w_full - (style.ItemInnerSpacing.x) * (components-1)) / (float)components));
4615  const float w_item_last = ImMax(1.0f, (float)(int)(w_full - (w_item_one + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x) * (components-1)));
4616  window->DC.ItemWidthStack.push_back(w_item_last);
4617  for (int i = 0; i < components-1; i++)
4618  window->DC.ItemWidthStack.push_back(w_item_one);
4619  window->DC.ItemWidth = window->DC.ItemWidthStack.back();
4620 }
4621 
4622 void ImGui::PopItemWidth()
4623 {
4624  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
4625  window->DC.ItemWidthStack.pop_back();
4626  window->DC.ItemWidth = window->DC.ItemWidthStack.empty() ? window->ItemWidthDefault : window->DC.ItemWidthStack.back();
4627 }
4628 
4629 float ImGui::CalcItemWidth()
4630 {
4631  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindowRead();
4632  float w = window->DC.ItemWidth;
4633  if (w < 0.0f)
4634  {
4635  // Align to a right-side limit. We include 1 frame padding in the calculation because this is how the width is always used (we add 2 frame padding to it), but we could move that responsibility to the widget as well.
4636  float width_to_right_edge = GetContentRegionAvail().x;
4637  w = ImMax(1.0f, width_to_right_edge + w);
4638  }
4639  w = (float)(int)w;
4640  return w;
4641 }

4649 static void SetCurrentFont(ImFont* font)
4650 {
4651  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
4652  IM_ASSERT(font && font->IsLoaded()); // Font Atlas not created. Did you call io.Fonts->GetTexDataAsRGBA32 / GetTexDataAsAlpha8 ?
4653  IM_ASSERT(font->Scale > 0.0f);
4654  g.Font = font;
4655  g.FontBaseSize = g.IO.FontGlobalScale * g.Font->FontSize * g.Font->Scale;
4656  g.FontSize = g.CurrentWindow ? g.CurrentWindow->CalcFontSize() : 0.0f;
4657  g.FontTexUvWhitePixel = g.Font->ContainerAtlas->TexUvWhitePixel;
4658 }

4797 void ImGui::PopStyleVar(int count)
4798 {
4799  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
4800  while (count > 0)
4801  {
4802  ImGuiStyleMod& backup = g.StyleModifiers.back();
4803  const ImGuiStyleVarInfo* info = GetStyleVarInfo(backup.VarIdx);
4804  if (info->Type == ImGuiDataType_Float) (*(float*)info->GetVarPtr()) = backup.BackupFloat[0];
4805  else if (info->Type == ImGuiDataType_Float2) (*(ImVec2*)info->GetVarPtr()) = ImVec2(backup.BackupFloat[0], backup.BackupFloat[1]);
4806  else if (info->Type == ImGuiDataType_Int) (*(int*)info->GetVarPtr()) = backup.BackupInt[0];
4807  g.StyleModifiers.pop_back();
4808  count--;
4809  }
4810 }
