4921 static void SetWindowPos(ImGuiWindow* window, const ImVec2& pos, ImGuiSetCond cond)
4922 {
4923  // Test condition (NB: bit 0 is always true) and clear flags for next time
4924  if (cond && (window->SetWindowPosAllowFlags & cond) == 0)
4925  return;
4926  window->SetWindowPosAllowFlags &= ~(ImGuiSetCond_Once | ImGuiSetCond_FirstUseEver | ImGuiSetCond_Appearing);
4927  window->SetWindowPosCenterWanted = false;
4928 
4929  // Set
4930  const ImVec2 old_pos = window->Pos;
4931  window->PosFloat = pos;
4932  window->Pos = ImVec2((float)(int)window->PosFloat.x, (float)(int)window->PosFloat.y);
4933  window->DC.CursorPos += (window->Pos - old_pos); // As we happen to move the window while it is being appended to (which is a bad idea - will smear) let's at least offset the cursor
4934  window->DC.CursorMaxPos += (window->Pos - old_pos); // And more importantly we need to adjust this so size calculation doesn't get affected.
4935 }

4955 static void SetWindowSize(ImGuiWindow* window, const ImVec2& size, ImGuiSetCond cond)
4956 {
4957  // Test condition (NB: bit 0 is always true) and clear flags for next time
4958  if (cond && (window->SetWindowSizeAllowFlags & cond) == 0)
4959  return;
4960  window->SetWindowSizeAllowFlags &= ~(ImGuiSetCond_Once | ImGuiSetCond_FirstUseEver | ImGuiSetCond_Appearing);
4961 
4962  // Set
4963  if (size.x > 0.0f)
4964  {
4965  window->AutoFitFramesX = 0;
4966  window->SizeFull.x = size.x;
4967  }
4968  else
4969  {
4970  window->AutoFitFramesX = 2;
4971  window->AutoFitOnlyGrows = false;
4972  }
4973  if (size.y > 0.0f)
4974  {
4975  window->AutoFitFramesY = 0;
4976  window->SizeFull.y = size.y;
4977  }
4978  else
4979  {
4980  window->AutoFitFramesY = 2;
4981  window->AutoFitOnlyGrows = false;
4982  }
4983 }

5283 void ImGui::SetScrollFromPosY(float pos_y, float center_y_ratio)
5284 {
5285  // We store a target position so centering can occur on the next frame when we are guaranteed to have a known window size
5286  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
5287  IM_ASSERT(center_y_ratio >= 0.0f && center_y_ratio <= 1.0f);
5288  window->ScrollTarget.y = (float)(int)(pos_y + window->Scroll.y);
5289  if (center_y_ratio <= 0.0f && window->ScrollTarget.y <= window->WindowPadding.y) // Minor hack to make "scroll to top" take account of WindowPadding, else it would scroll to (WindowPadding.y - ItemSpacing.y)
5290  window->ScrollTarget.y = 0.0f;
5291  window->ScrollTargetCenterRatio.y = center_y_ratio;
5292 }

5299  SetScrollFromPosY(target_y - window->Pos.y, center_y_ratio);

5386 void ImGui::TextUnformatted(const char* text, const char* text_end)
5387 {
5388  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
5389  if (window->SkipItems)
5390  return;
5391 
5392  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5393  IM_ASSERT(text != NULL);
5394  const char* text_begin = text;
5395  if (text_end == NULL)
5396  text_end = text + strlen(text); // FIXME-OPT
5397 
5398  const float wrap_pos_x = window->DC.TextWrapPos;
5399  const bool wrap_enabled = wrap_pos_x >= 0.0f;
5400  if (text_end - text > 2000 && !wrap_enabled)
5401  {
5402  // Long text!
5403  // Perform manual coarse clipping to optimize for long multi-line text
5404  // From this point we will only compute the width of lines that are visible. Optimization only available when word-wrapping is disabled.
5405  // We also don't vertically center the text within the line full height, which is unlikely to matter because we are likely the biggest and only item on the line.
5406  const char* line = text;
5407  const float line_height = GetTextLineHeight();
5408  const ImVec2 text_pos = window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(0.0f, window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset);
5409  const ImRect clip_rect = window->ClipRect;
5410  ImVec2 text_size(0,0);
5411 
5412  if (text_pos.y <= clip_rect.Max.y)
5413  {
5414  ImVec2 pos = text_pos;
5415 
5416  // Lines to skip (can't skip when logging text)
5417  if (!g.LogEnabled)
5418  {
5419  int lines_skippable = (int)((clip_rect.Min.y - text_pos.y) / line_height);
5420  if (lines_skippable > 0)
5421  {
5422  int lines_skipped = 0;
5423  while (line < text_end && lines_skipped < lines_skippable)
5424  {
5425  const char* line_end = strchr(line, '\n');
5426  if (!line_end)
5427  line_end = text_end;
5428  line = line_end + 1;
5429  lines_skipped++;
5430  }
5431  pos.y += lines_skipped * line_height;
5432  }
5433  }
5434 
5435  // Lines to render
5436  if (line < text_end)
5437  {
5438  ImRect line_rect(pos, pos + ImVec2(FLT_MAX, line_height));
5439  while (line < text_end)
5440  {
5441  const char* line_end = strchr(line, '\n');
5442  if (IsClippedEx(line_rect, NULL, false))
5443  break;
5444 
5445  const ImVec2 line_size = CalcTextSize(line, line_end, false);
5446  text_size.x = ImMax(text_size.x, line_size.x);
5447  RenderText(pos, line, line_end, false);
5448  if (!line_end)
5449  line_end = text_end;
5450  line = line_end + 1;
5451  line_rect.Min.y += line_height;
5452  line_rect.Max.y += line_height;
5453  pos.y += line_height;
5454  }
5455 
5456  // Count remaining lines
5457  int lines_skipped = 0;
5458  while (line < text_end)
5459  {
5460  const char* line_end = strchr(line, '\n');
5461  if (!line_end)
5462  line_end = text_end;
5463  line = line_end + 1;
5464  lines_skipped++;
5465  }
5466  pos.y += lines_skipped * line_height;
5467  }
5468 
5469  text_size.y += (pos - text_pos).y;
5470  }
5471 
5472  ImRect bb(text_pos, text_pos + text_size);
5473  ItemSize(bb);
5474  ItemAdd(bb, NULL);
5475  }
5476  else
5477  {
5478  const float wrap_width = wrap_enabled ? CalcWrapWidthForPos(window->DC.CursorPos, wrap_pos_x) : 0.0f;
5479  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(text_begin, text_end, false, wrap_width);
5480 
5481  // Account of baseline offset
5482  ImVec2 text_pos(window->DC.CursorPos.x, window->DC.CursorPos.y + window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset);
5483  ImRect bb(text_pos, text_pos + text_size);
5484  ItemSize(text_size);
5485  if (!ItemAdd(bb, NULL))
5486  return;
5487 
5488  // Render (we don't hide text after ## in this end-user function)
5489  RenderTextWrapped(bb.Min, text_begin, text_end, wrap_width);
5490  }
5491 }
5492 
5493 void ImGui::AlignFirstTextHeightToWidgets()
5494 {
5495  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
5496  if (window->SkipItems)
5497  return;
5498 
5499  // Declare a dummy item size to that upcoming items that are smaller will center-align on the newly expanded line height.
5500  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5501  ItemSize(ImVec2(0, g.FontSize + g.Style.FramePadding.y*2), g.Style.FramePadding.y);
5502  SameLine(0, 0);
5503 }

5505 // Add a label+text combo aligned to other label+value widgets
5506 void ImGui::LabelTextV(const char* label, const char* fmt, va_list args)
5507 {
5508  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
5509  if (window->SkipItems)
5510  return;
5511 
5512  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5513  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
5514  const float w = CalcItemWidth();
5515 
5516  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
5517  const ImRect value_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(w, label_size.y + style.FramePadding.y*2));
5518  const ImRect total_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(w + (label_size.x > 0.0f ? style.ItemInnerSpacing.x : 0.0f), style.FramePadding.y*2) + label_size);
5519  ItemSize(total_bb, style.FramePadding.y);
5520  if (!ItemAdd(total_bb, NULL))
5521  return;
5522 
5523  // Render
5524  const char* value_text_begin = &g.TempBuffer[0];
5525  const char* value_text_end = value_text_begin + ImFormatStringV(g.TempBuffer, IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.TempBuffer), fmt, args);
5526  RenderTextClipped(value_bb.Min, value_bb.Max, value_text_begin, value_text_end, NULL, ImVec2(0.0f,0.5f));
5527  if (label_size.x > 0.0f)
5528  RenderText(ImVec2(value_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, value_bb.Min.y + style.FramePadding.y), label);
5529 }

5539 static inline bool IsWindowContentHoverable(ImGuiWindow* window)
5540 {
5541  // An active popup disable hovering on other windows (apart from its own children)
5542  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5543  if (ImGuiWindow* focused_window = g.FocusedWindow)
5544  if (ImGuiWindow* focused_root_window = focused_window->RootWindow)
5545  if ((focused_root_window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) != 0 && focused_root_window->WasActive && focused_root_window != window->RootWindow)
5546  return false;
5547 
5548  return true;
5549 }
5550 
5551 bool ImGui::ButtonBehavior(const ImRect& bb, ImGuiID id, bool* out_hovered, bool* out_held, ImGuiButtonFlags flags)
5552 {
5553  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5554  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
5555 
5556  if (flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_Disabled)
5557  {
5558  if (out_hovered) *out_hovered = false;
5559  if (out_held) *out_held = false;
5560  if (g.ActiveId == id) ClearActiveID();
5561  return false;
5562  }
5563 
5564  if ((flags & (ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClickRelease | ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClick | ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnRelease | ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnDoubleClick)) == 0)
5565  flags |= ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClickRelease;
5566 
5567  bool pressed = false;
5568  bool hovered = IsHovered(bb, id, (flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_FlattenChilds) != 0);
5569  if (hovered)
5570  {
5571  SetHoveredID(id);
5572  if (!(flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_NoKeyModifiers) || (!g.IO.KeyCtrl && !g.IO.KeyShift && !g.IO.KeyAlt))
5573  {
5574  // | CLICKING | HOLDING with ImGuiButtonFlags_Repeat
5575  // PressedOnClickRelease | <on release>* | <on repeat> <on repeat> .. (NOT on release) <-- MOST COMMON! (*) only if both click/release were over bounds
5576  // PressedOnClick | <on click> | <on click> <on repeat> <on repeat> ..
5577  // PressedOnRelease | <on release> | <on repeat> <on repeat> .. (NOT on release)
5578  // PressedOnDoubleClick | <on dclick> | <on dclick> <on repeat> <on repeat> ..
5579  if ((flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClickRelease) && g.IO.MouseClicked[0])
5580  {
5581  SetActiveID(id, window); // Hold on ID
5582  FocusWindow(window);
5583  g.ActiveIdClickOffset = g.IO.MousePos - bb.Min;
5584  }
5585  if (((flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClick) && g.IO.MouseClicked[0]) || ((flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnDoubleClick) && g.IO.MouseDoubleClicked[0]))
5586  {
5587  pressed = true;
5588  ClearActiveID();
5589  FocusWindow(window);
5590  }
5591  if ((flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnRelease) && g.IO.MouseReleased[0])
5592  {
5593  if (!((flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_Repeat) && g.IO.MouseDownDurationPrev[0] >= g.IO.KeyRepeatDelay)) // Repeat mode trumps <on release>
5594  pressed = true;
5595  ClearActiveID();
5596  }
5597 
5598  // 'Repeat' mode acts when held regardless of _PressedOn flags (see table above).
5599  // Relies on repeat logic of IsMouseClicked() but we may as well do it ourselves if we end up exposing finer RepeatDelay/RepeatRate settings.
5600  if ((flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_Repeat) && g.ActiveId == id && g.IO.MouseDownDuration[0] > 0.0f && IsMouseClicked(0, true))
5601  pressed = true;
5602  }
5603  }
5604 
5605  bool held = false;
5606  if (g.ActiveId == id)
5607  {
5608  if (g.IO.MouseDown[0])
5609  {
5610  held = true;
5611  }
5612  else
5613  {
5614  if (hovered && (flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClickRelease))
5615  if (!((flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_Repeat) && g.IO.MouseDownDurationPrev[0] >= g.IO.KeyRepeatDelay)) // Repeat mode trumps <on release>
5616  pressed = true;
5617  ClearActiveID();
5618  }
5619  }
5620 
5621  // AllowOverlap mode (rarely used) requires previous frame HoveredId to be null or to match. This allows using patterns where a later submitted widget overlaps a previous one.
5622  if (hovered && (flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_AllowOverlapMode) && (g.HoveredIdPreviousFrame != id && g.HoveredIdPreviousFrame != 0))
5623  hovered = pressed = held = false;
5624 
5625  if (out_hovered) *out_hovered = hovered;
5626  if (out_held) *out_held = held;
5627 
5628  return pressed;
5629 }
5630 
5631 bool ImGui::ButtonEx(const char* label, const ImVec2& size_arg, ImGuiButtonFlags flags)
5632 {
5633  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
5634  if (window->SkipItems)
5635  return false;
5636 
5637  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5638  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
5639  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
5640  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
5641 
5642  ImVec2 pos = window->DC.CursorPos;
5643  if ((flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_AlignTextBaseLine) && style.FramePadding.y < window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset) // Try to vertically align buttons that are smaller/have no padding so that text baseline matches (bit hacky, since it shouldn't be a flag)
5644  pos.y += window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset - style.FramePadding.y;
5645  ImVec2 size = CalcItemSize(size_arg, label_size.x + style.FramePadding.x * 2.0f, label_size.y + style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f);
5646 
5647  const ImRect bb(pos, pos + size);
5648  ItemSize(bb, style.FramePadding.y);
5649  if (!ItemAdd(bb, &id))
5650  return false;
5651 
5652  if (window->DC.ButtonRepeat) flags |= ImGuiButtonFlags_Repeat;
5653  bool hovered, held;
5654  bool pressed = ButtonBehavior(bb, id, &hovered, &held, flags);
5655 
5656  // Render
5657  const ImU32 col = GetColorU32((hovered && held) ? ImGuiCol_ButtonActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_ButtonHovered : ImGuiCol_Button);
5658  RenderFrame(bb.Min, bb.Max, col, true, style.FrameRounding);
5659  RenderTextClipped(bb.Min + style.FramePadding, bb.Max - style.FramePadding, label, NULL, &label_size, style.ButtonTextAlign, &bb);
5660 
5661  // Automatically close popups
5662  //if (pressed && !(flags & ImGuiButtonFlags_DontClosePopups) && (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup))
5663  // CloseCurrentPopup();
5664 
5665  return pressed;
5666 }

5684 // Tip: use ImGui::PushID()/PopID() to push indices or pointers in the ID stack.
5685 // Then you can keep 'str_id' empty or the same for all your buttons (instead of creating a string based on a non-string id)
5686 bool ImGui::InvisibleButton(const char* str_id, const ImVec2& size_arg)
5687 {

5690  return false;

5696  if (!ItemAdd(bb, &id))
5697  return false;

5701 
5702  return pressed;
5703 }

5705 // Upper-right button to close a window.
5706 bool ImGui::CloseButton(ImGuiID id, const ImVec2& pos, float radius)
5707 {
5708  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
5709 
5710  const ImRect bb(pos - ImVec2(radius,radius), pos + ImVec2(radius,radius));
5711 
5712  bool hovered, held;
5713  bool pressed = ButtonBehavior(bb, id, &hovered, &held);
5714 
5715  // Render
5716  const ImU32 col = GetColorU32((held && hovered) ? ImGuiCol_CloseButtonActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_CloseButtonHovered : ImGuiCol_CloseButton);
5717  const ImVec2 center = bb.GetCenter();
5718  window->DrawList->AddCircleFilled(center, ImMax(2.0f, radius), col, 12);
5719 
5720  const float cross_extent = (radius * 0.7071f) - 1.0f;
5721  if (hovered)
5722  {
5723  window->DrawList->AddLine(center + ImVec2(+cross_extent,+cross_extent), center + ImVec2(-cross_extent,-cross_extent), GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Text));
5724  window->DrawList->AddLine(center + ImVec2(+cross_extent,-cross_extent), center + ImVec2(-cross_extent,+cross_extent), GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Text));
5725  }
5726 
5727  return pressed;
5728 }

5730 void ImGui::Image(ImTextureID user_texture_id, const ImVec2& size, const ImVec2& uv0, const ImVec2& uv1, const ImVec4& tint_col, const ImVec4& border_col)
5731 {
5732  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
5733  if (window->SkipItems)
5734  return;
5735 
5736  ImRect bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + size);
5737  if (border_col.w > 0.0f)
5738  bb.Max += ImVec2(2,2);
5739  ItemSize(bb);
5740  if (!ItemAdd(bb, NULL))
5741  return;
5742 
5743  if (border_col.w > 0.0f)
5744  {
5745  window->DrawList->AddRect(bb.Min, bb.Max, GetColorU32(border_col), 0.0f);
5746  window->DrawList->AddImage(user_texture_id, bb.Min+ImVec2(1,1), bb.Max-ImVec2(1,1), uv0, uv1, GetColorU32(tint_col));
5747  }
5748  else
5749  {
5750  window->DrawList->AddImage(user_texture_id, bb.Min, bb.Max, uv0, uv1, GetColorU32(tint_col));
5751  }
5752 }
5753 
5754 // frame_padding < 0: uses FramePadding from style (default)
5755 // frame_padding = 0: no framing
5756 // frame_padding > 0: set framing size
5757 // The color used are the button colors.
5758 bool ImGui::ImageButton(ImTextureID user_texture_id, const ImVec2& size, const ImVec2& uv0, const ImVec2& uv1, int frame_padding, const ImVec4& bg_col, const ImVec4& tint_col)
5759 {
5760  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
5761  if (window->SkipItems)
5762  return false;
5763 
5764  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5765  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
5766 
5767  // Default to using texture ID as ID. User can still push string/integer prefixes.
5768  // We could hash the size/uv to create a unique ID but that would prevent the user from animating UV.
5769  PushID((void *)user_texture_id);
5770  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID("#image");
5771  PopID();
5772 
5773  const ImVec2 padding = (frame_padding >= 0) ? ImVec2((float)frame_padding, (float)frame_padding) : style.FramePadding;
5774  const ImRect bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + size + padding*2);
5775  const ImRect image_bb(window->DC.CursorPos + padding, window->DC.CursorPos + padding + size);
5776  ItemSize(bb);
5777  if (!ItemAdd(bb, &id))
5778  return false;
5779 
5780  bool hovered, held;
5781  bool pressed = ButtonBehavior(bb, id, &hovered, &held);
5782 
5783  // Render
5784  const ImU32 col = GetColorU32((hovered && held) ? ImGuiCol_ButtonActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_ButtonHovered : ImGuiCol_Button);
5785  RenderFrame(bb.Min, bb.Max, col, true, ImClamp((float)ImMin(padding.x, padding.y), 0.0f, style.FrameRounding));
5786  if (bg_col.w > 0.0f)
5787  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(image_bb.Min, image_bb.Max, GetColorU32(bg_col));
5788  window->DrawList->AddImage(user_texture_id, image_bb.Min, image_bb.Max, uv0, uv1, GetColorU32(tint_col));
5789 
5790  return pressed;
5791 }

5798  return;

5800 
5801  g.LogEnabled = true;
5802  g.LogFile = stdout;
5803  g.LogStartDepth = window->DC.TreeDepth;
5804  if (max_depth >= 0)
5805  g.LogAutoExpandMaxDepth = max_depth;
5806 }

5808 // Start logging ImGui output to given file
5809 void ImGui::LogToFile(int max_depth, const char* filename)
5810 {
5811  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5812  if (g.LogEnabled)
5813  return;
5814  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindowRead();
5815 
5816  if (!filename)
5817  {
5818  filename = g.IO.LogFilename;
5819  if (!filename)
5820  return;
5821  }
5822 
5823  g.LogFile = ImFileOpen(filename, "ab");
5824  if (!g.LogFile)
5825  {
5826  IM_ASSERT(g.LogFile != NULL); // Consider this an error
5827  return;
5828  }
5829  g.LogEnabled = true;
5830  g.LogStartDepth = window->DC.TreeDepth;
5831  if (max_depth >= 0)
5832  g.LogAutoExpandMaxDepth = max_depth;
5833 }

5850 void ImGui::LogFinish()
5851 {
5852  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5853  if (!g.LogEnabled)
5854  return;
5855 
5856  LogText(IM_NEWLINE);
5857  g.LogEnabled = false;
5858  if (g.LogFile != NULL)
5859  {
5860  if (g.LogFile == stdout)
5861  fflush(g.LogFile);
5862  else
5863  fclose(g.LogFile);
5864  g.LogFile = NULL;
5865  }
5866  if (g.LogClipboard->size() > 1)
5867  {
5868  SetClipboardText(g.LogClipboard->begin());
5869  g.LogClipboard->clear();
5870  }
5871 }

5873 // Helper to display logging buttons
5874 void ImGui::LogButtons()
5875 {
5876  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5877 
5878  PushID("LogButtons");
5879  const bool log_to_tty = Button("Log To TTY"); SameLine();
5880  const bool log_to_file = Button("Log To File"); SameLine();
5881  const bool log_to_clipboard = Button("Log To Clipboard"); SameLine();
5882  PushItemWidth(80.0f);
5883  PushAllowKeyboardFocus(false);
5884  SliderInt("Depth", &g.LogAutoExpandMaxDepth, 0, 9, NULL);
5885  PopAllowKeyboardFocus();
5886  PopItemWidth();
5887  PopID();
5888 
5889  // Start logging at the end of the function so that the buttons don't appear in the log
5890  if (log_to_tty)
5891  LogToTTY(g.LogAutoExpandMaxDepth);
5892  if (log_to_file)
5893  LogToFile(g.LogAutoExpandMaxDepth, g.IO.LogFilename);
5894  if (log_to_clipboard)
5895  LogToClipboard(g.LogAutoExpandMaxDepth);
5896 }
5897 
5898 bool ImGui::TreeNodeBehaviorIsOpen(ImGuiID id, ImGuiTreeNodeFlags flags)
5899 {
5900  if (flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_Leaf)
5901  return true;
5902 
5903  // We only write to the tree storage if the user clicks (or explicitely use SetNextTreeNode*** functions)
5904  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5905  ImGuiWindow* window = g.CurrentWindow;
5906  ImGuiStorage* storage = window->DC.StateStorage;
5907 
5908  bool is_open;
5909  if (g.SetNextTreeNodeOpenCond != 0)
5910  {
5911  if (g.SetNextTreeNodeOpenCond & ImGuiSetCond_Always)
5912  {
5913  is_open = g.SetNextTreeNodeOpenVal;
5914  storage->SetInt(id, is_open);
5915  }
5916  else
5917  {
5918  // We treat ImGuiSetCondition_Once and ImGuiSetCondition_FirstUseEver the same because tree node state are not saved persistently.
5919  const int stored_value = storage->GetInt(id, -1);
5920  if (stored_value == -1)
5921  {
5922  is_open = g.SetNextTreeNodeOpenVal;
5923  storage->SetInt(id, is_open);
5924  }
5925  else
5926  {
5927  is_open = stored_value != 0;
5928  }
5929  }
5930  g.SetNextTreeNodeOpenCond = 0;
5931  }
5932  else
5933  {
5934  is_open = storage->GetInt(id, (flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_DefaultOpen) ? 1 : 0) != 0;
5935  }
5936 
5937  // When logging is enabled, we automatically expand tree nodes (but *NOT* collapsing headers.. seems like sensible behavior).
5938  // NB- If we are above max depth we still allow manually opened nodes to be logged.
5939  if (g.LogEnabled && !(flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_NoAutoOpenOnLog) && window->DC.TreeDepth < g.LogAutoExpandMaxDepth)
5940  is_open = true;
5941 
5942  return is_open;
5943 }
5944 
5945 bool ImGui::TreeNodeBehavior(ImGuiID id, ImGuiTreeNodeFlags flags, const char* label, const char* label_end)
5946 {
5947  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
5948  if (window->SkipItems)
5949  return false;
5950 
5951  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
5952  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
5953  const bool display_frame = (flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_Framed) != 0;
5954  const ImVec2 padding = display_frame ? style.FramePadding : ImVec2(style.FramePadding.x, 0.0f);
5955 
5956  if (!label_end)
5957  label_end = FindRenderedTextEnd(label);
5958  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, label_end, false);
5959 
5960  // We vertically grow up to current line height up the typical widget height.
5961  const float text_base_offset_y = ImMax(0.0f, window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset - padding.y); // Latch before ItemSize changes it
5962  const float frame_height = ImMax(ImMin(window->DC.CurrentLineHeight, g.FontSize + style.FramePadding.y*2), label_size.y + padding.y*2);
5963  ImRect bb = ImRect(window->DC.CursorPos, ImVec2(window->Pos.x + GetContentRegionMax().x, window->DC.CursorPos.y + frame_height));
5964  if (display_frame)
5965  {
5966  // Framed header expand a little outside the default padding
5967  bb.Min.x -= (float)(int)(window->WindowPadding.x*0.5f) - 1;
5968  bb.Max.x += (float)(int)(window->WindowPadding.x*0.5f) - 1;
5969  }
5970 
5971  const float text_offset_x = (g.FontSize + (display_frame ? padding.x*3 : padding.x*2)); // Collapser arrow width + Spacing
5972  const float text_width = g.FontSize + (label_size.x > 0.0f ? label_size.x + padding.x*2 : 0.0f); // Include collapser
5973  ItemSize(ImVec2(text_width, frame_height), text_base_offset_y);
5974 
5975  // For regular tree nodes, we arbitrary allow to click past 2 worth of ItemSpacing
5976  // (Ideally we'd want to add a flag for the user to specify we want want the hit test to be done up to the right side of the content or not)
5977  const ImRect interact_bb = display_frame ? bb : ImRect(bb.Min.x, bb.Min.y, bb.Min.x + text_width + style.ItemSpacing.x*2, bb.Max.y);
5978  bool is_open = TreeNodeBehaviorIsOpen(id, flags);
5979  if (!ItemAdd(interact_bb, &id))
5980  {
5981  if (is_open && !(flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_NoTreePushOnOpen))
5982  TreePushRawID(id);
5983  return is_open;
5984  }
5985 
5986  // Flags that affects opening behavior:
5987  // - 0(default) ..................... single-click anywhere to open
5988  // - OpenOnDoubleClick .............. double-click anywhere to open
5989  // - OpenOnArrow .................... single-click on arrow to open
5990  // - OpenOnDoubleClick|OpenOnArrow .. single-click on arrow or double-click anywhere to open
5991  ImGuiButtonFlags button_flags = ImGuiButtonFlags_NoKeyModifiers | ((flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_AllowOverlapMode) ? ImGuiButtonFlags_AllowOverlapMode : 0);
5992  if (flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_OpenOnDoubleClick)
5993  button_flags |= ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnDoubleClick | ((flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_OpenOnArrow) ? ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClickRelease : 0);
5994  bool hovered, held, pressed = ButtonBehavior(interact_bb, id, &hovered, &held, button_flags);
5995  if (pressed && !(flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_Leaf))
5996  {
5997  bool toggled = !(flags & (ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_OpenOnArrow | ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_OpenOnDoubleClick));
5998  if (flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_OpenOnArrow)
5999  toggled |= IsMouseHoveringRect(interact_bb.Min, ImVec2(interact_bb.Min.x + text_offset_x, interact_bb.Max.y));
6000  if (flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_OpenOnDoubleClick)
6001  toggled |= g.IO.MouseDoubleClicked[0];
6002  if (toggled)
6003  {
6004  is_open = !is_open;
6005  window->DC.StateStorage->SetInt(id, is_open);
6006  }
6007  }
6008  if (flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_AllowOverlapMode)
6009  SetItemAllowOverlap();
6010 
6011  // Render
6012  const ImU32 col = GetColorU32((held && hovered) ? ImGuiCol_HeaderActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_HeaderHovered : ImGuiCol_Header);
6013  const ImVec2 text_pos = bb.Min + ImVec2(text_offset_x, padding.y + text_base_offset_y);
6014  if (display_frame)
6015  {
6016  // Framed type
6017  RenderFrame(bb.Min, bb.Max, col, true, style.FrameRounding);
6018  RenderCollapseTriangle(bb.Min + padding + ImVec2(0.0f, text_base_offset_y), is_open, 1.0f);
6019  if (g.LogEnabled)
6020  {
6021  // NB: '##' is normally used to hide text (as a library-wide feature), so we need to specify the text range to make sure the ## aren't stripped out here.
6022  const char log_prefix[] = "\n##";
6023  const char log_suffix[] = "##";
6024  LogRenderedText(text_pos, log_prefix, log_prefix+3);
6025  RenderTextClipped(text_pos, bb.Max, label, label_end, &label_size);
6026  LogRenderedText(text_pos, log_suffix+1, log_suffix+3);
6027  }
6028  else
6029  {
6030  RenderTextClipped(text_pos, bb.Max, label, label_end, &label_size);
6031  }
6032  }
6033  else
6034  {
6035  // Unframed typed for tree nodes
6036  if (hovered || (flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_Selected))
6037  RenderFrame(bb.Min, bb.Max, col, false);
6038 
6039  if (flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_Bullet)
6040  RenderBullet(bb.Min + ImVec2(text_offset_x * 0.5f, g.FontSize*0.50f + text_base_offset_y));
6041  else if (!(flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_Leaf))
6042  RenderCollapseTriangle(bb.Min + ImVec2(padding.x, g.FontSize*0.15f + text_base_offset_y), is_open, 0.70f);
6043  if (g.LogEnabled)
6044  LogRenderedText(text_pos, ">");
6045  RenderText(text_pos, label, label_end, false);
6046  }
6047 
6048  if (is_open && !(flags & ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_NoTreePushOnOpen))
6049  TreePushRawID(id);
6050  return is_open;
6051 }
6052 
6053 // CollapsingHeader returns true when opened but do not indent nor push into the ID stack (because of the ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_NoTreePushOnOpen flag).
6054 // This is basically the same as calling TreeNodeEx(label, ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_CollapsingHeader | ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_NoTreePushOnOpen). You can remove the _NoTreePushOnOpen flag if you want behavior closer to normal TreeNode().
6055 bool ImGui::CollapsingHeader(const char* label, ImGuiTreeNodeFlags flags)
6056 {
6057  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
6058  if (window->SkipItems)
6059  return false;
6060 
6061  return TreeNodeBehavior(window->GetID(label), flags | ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_CollapsingHeader | ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_NoTreePushOnOpen, label);
6062 }
6063 
6064 bool ImGui::CollapsingHeader(const char* label, bool* p_open, ImGuiTreeNodeFlags flags)
6065 {
6066  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
6067  if (window->SkipItems)
6068  return false;
6069 
6070  if (p_open && !*p_open)
6071  return false;
6072 
6073  ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
6074  bool is_open = TreeNodeBehavior(id, flags | ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_CollapsingHeader | ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_NoTreePushOnOpen | (p_open ? ImGuiTreeNodeFlags_AllowOverlapMode : 0), label);
6075  if (p_open)
6076  {
6077  // Create a small overlapping close button // FIXME: We can evolve this into user accessible helpers to add extra buttons on title bars, headers, etc.
6078  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
6079  float button_sz = g.FontSize * 0.5f;
6080  if (CloseButton(window->GetID((void*)(intptr_t)(id+1)), ImVec2(ImMin(window->DC.LastItemRect.Max.x, window->ClipRect.Max.x) - g.Style.FramePadding.x - button_sz, window->DC.LastItemRect.Min.y + g.Style.FramePadding.y + button_sz), button_sz))
6081  *p_open = false;
6082  }
6083 
6084  return is_open;
6085 }

6192 void ImGui::PushID(const char* str_id)

6293 static inline void DataTypeFormatString(ImGuiDataType data_type, void* data_ptr, const char* display_format, char* buf, int buf_size)
6294 {
6295  if (data_type == ImGuiDataType_Int)
6296  ImFormatString(buf, buf_size, display_format, *(int*)data_ptr);
6297  else if (data_type == ImGuiDataType_Float)
6298  ImFormatString(buf, buf_size, display_format, *(float*)data_ptr);
6299 }
6300 
6301 static inline void DataTypeFormatString(ImGuiDataType data_type, void* data_ptr, int decimal_precision, char* buf, int buf_size)
6302 {
6303  if (data_type == ImGuiDataType_Int)
6304  {
6305  if (decimal_precision < 0)
6306  ImFormatString(buf, buf_size, "%d", *(int*)data_ptr);
6307  else
6308  ImFormatString(buf, buf_size, "%.*d", decimal_precision, *(int*)data_ptr);
6309  }
6310  else if (data_type == ImGuiDataType_Float)
6311  {
6312  if (decimal_precision < 0)
6313  ImFormatString(buf, buf_size, "%f", *(float*)data_ptr); // Ideally we'd have a minimum decimal precision of 1 to visually denote that it is a float, while hiding non-significant digits?
6314  else
6315  ImFormatString(buf, buf_size, "%.*f", decimal_precision, *(float*)data_ptr);
6316  }
6317 }
6318 
6319 static void DataTypeApplyOp(ImGuiDataType data_type, int op, void* value1, const void* value2)// Store into value1
6320 {
6321  if (data_type == ImGuiDataType_Int)
6322  {
6323  if (op == '+')
6324  *(int*)value1 = *(int*)value1 + *(const int*)value2;
6325  else if (op == '-')
6326  *(int*)value1 = *(int*)value1 - *(const int*)value2;
6327  }
6328  else if (data_type == ImGuiDataType_Float)
6329  {
6330  if (op == '+')
6331  *(float*)value1 = *(float*)value1 + *(const float*)value2;
6332  else if (op == '-')
6333  *(float*)value1 = *(float*)value1 - *(const float*)value2;
6334  }
6335 }
6336 
6337 // User can input math operators (e.g. +100) to edit a numerical values.
6338 static bool DataTypeApplyOpFromText(const char* buf, const char* initial_value_buf, ImGuiDataType data_type, void* data_ptr, const char* scalar_format)
6339 {
6340  while (ImCharIsSpace(*buf))
6341  buf++;
6342 
6343  // We don't support '-' op because it would conflict with inputing negative value.
6344  // Instead you can use +-100 to subtract from an existing value
6345  char op = buf[0];
6346  if (op == '+' || op == '*' || op == '/')
6347  {
6348  buf++;
6349  while (ImCharIsSpace(*buf))
6350  buf++;
6351  }
6352  else
6353  {
6354  op = 0;
6355  }
6356  if (!buf[0])
6357  return false;
6358 
6359  if (data_type == ImGuiDataType_Int)
6360  {
6361  if (!scalar_format)
6362  scalar_format = "%d";
6363  int* v = (int*)data_ptr;
6364  const int old_v = *v;
6365  int arg0 = *v;
6366  if (op && sscanf(initial_value_buf, scalar_format, &arg0) < 1)
6367  return false;
6368 
6369  // Store operand in a float so we can use fractional value for multipliers (*1.1), but constant always parsed as integer so we can fit big integers (e.g. 2000000003) past float precision
6370  float arg1 = 0.0f;
6371  if (op == '+') { if (sscanf(buf, "%f", &arg1) == 1) *v = (int)(arg0 + arg1); } // Add (use "+-" to subtract)
6372  else if (op == '*') { if (sscanf(buf, "%f", &arg1) == 1) *v = (int)(arg0 * arg1); } // Multiply
6373  else if (op == '/') { if (sscanf(buf, "%f", &arg1) == 1 && arg1 != 0.0f) *v = (int)(arg0 / arg1); }// Divide
6374  else { if (sscanf(buf, scalar_format, &arg0) == 1) *v = arg0; } // Assign constant
6375  return (old_v != *v);
6376  }
6377  else if (data_type == ImGuiDataType_Float)
6378  {
6379  // For floats we have to ignore format with precision (e.g. "%.2f") because sscanf doesn't take them in
6380  scalar_format = "%f";
6381  float* v = (float*)data_ptr;
6382  const float old_v = *v;
6383  float arg0 = *v;
6384  if (op && sscanf(initial_value_buf, scalar_format, &arg0) < 1)
6385  return false;
6386 
6387  float arg1 = 0.0f;
6388  if (sscanf(buf, scalar_format, &arg1) < 1)
6389  return false;
6390  if (op == '+') { *v = arg0 + arg1; } // Add (use "+-" to subtract)
6391  else if (op == '*') { *v = arg0 * arg1; } // Multiply
6392  else if (op == '/') { if (arg1 != 0.0f) *v = arg0 / arg1; } // Divide
6393  else { *v = arg1; } // Assign constant
6394  return (old_v != *v);
6395  }
6396 
6397  return false;
6398 }

6400 // Create text input in place of a slider (when CTRL+Clicking on slider)
6401 bool ImGui::InputScalarAsWidgetReplacement(const ImRect& aabb, const char* label, ImGuiDataType data_type, void* data_ptr, ImGuiID id, int decimal_precision)
6402 {
6403  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
6404  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
6405 
6406  // Our replacement widget will override the focus ID (registered previously to allow for a TAB focus to happen)
6407  SetActiveID(g.ScalarAsInputTextId, window);
6408  SetHoveredID(0);
6409  FocusableItemUnregister(window);
6410 
6411  char buf[32];
6412  DataTypeFormatString(data_type, data_ptr, decimal_precision, buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(buf));
6413  bool text_value_changed = InputTextEx(label, buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(buf), aabb.GetSize(), ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsDecimal | ImGuiInputTextFlags_AutoSelectAll);
6414  if (g.ScalarAsInputTextId == 0)
6415  {
6416  // First frame
6417  IM_ASSERT(g.ActiveId == id); // InputText ID expected to match the Slider ID (else we'd need to store them both, which is also possible)
6418  g.ScalarAsInputTextId = g.ActiveId;
6419  SetHoveredID(id);
6420  }
6421  else if (g.ActiveId != g.ScalarAsInputTextId)
6422  {
6423  // Release
6424  g.ScalarAsInputTextId = 0;
6425  }
6426  if (text_value_changed)
6427  return DataTypeApplyOpFromText(buf, GImGui->InputTextState.InitialText.begin(), data_type, data_ptr, NULL);
6428  return false;
6429 }
6430 
6431 // Parse display precision back from the display format string
6432 int ImGui::ParseFormatPrecision(const char* fmt, int default_precision)
6433 {
6434  int precision = default_precision;
6435  while ((fmt = strchr(fmt, '%')) != NULL)
6436  {
6437  fmt++;
6438  if (fmt[0] == '%') { fmt++; continue; } // Ignore "%%"
6439  while (*fmt >= '0' && *fmt <= '9')
6440  fmt++;
6441  if (*fmt == '.')
6442  {
6443  precision = atoi(fmt + 1);
6444  if (precision < 0 || precision > 10)
6445  precision = default_precision;
6446  }
6447  break;
6448  }
6449  return precision;
6450 }
6451 
6452 float ImGui::RoundScalar(float value, int decimal_precision)
6453 {
6454  // Round past decimal precision
6455  // So when our value is 1.99999 with a precision of 0.001 we'll end up rounding to 2.0
6456  // FIXME: Investigate better rounding methods
6457  static const float min_steps[10] = { 1.0f, 0.1f, 0.01f, 0.001f, 0.0001f, 0.00001f, 0.000001f, 0.0000001f, 0.00000001f, 0.000000001f };
6458  float min_step = (decimal_precision >= 0 && decimal_precision < 10) ? min_steps[decimal_precision] : powf(10.0f, (float)-decimal_precision);
6459  bool negative = value < 0.0f;
6460  value = fabsf(value);
6461  float remainder = fmodf(value, min_step);
6462  if (remainder <= min_step*0.5f)
6463  value -= remainder;
6464  else
6465  value += (min_step - remainder);
6466  return negative ? -value : value;
6467 }
6468 
6469 static inline float SliderBehaviorCalcRatioFromValue(float v, float v_min, float v_max, float power, float linear_zero_pos)
6470 {
6471  if (v_min == v_max)
6472  return 0.0f;
6473 
6474  const bool is_non_linear = (power < 1.0f-0.00001f) || (power > 1.0f+0.00001f);
6475  const float v_clamped = (v_min < v_max) ? ImClamp(v, v_min, v_max) : ImClamp(v, v_max, v_min);
6476  if (is_non_linear)
6477  {
6478  if (v_clamped < 0.0f)
6479  {
6480  const float f = 1.0f - (v_clamped - v_min) / (ImMin(0.0f,v_max) - v_min);
6481  return (1.0f - powf(f, 1.0f/power)) * linear_zero_pos;
6482  }
6483  else
6484  {
6485  const float f = (v_clamped - ImMax(0.0f,v_min)) / (v_max - ImMax(0.0f,v_min));
6486  return linear_zero_pos + powf(f, 1.0f/power) * (1.0f - linear_zero_pos);
6487  }
6488  }
6489 
6490  // Linear slider
6491  return (v_clamped - v_min) / (v_max - v_min);
6492 }
6493 
6494 bool ImGui::SliderBehavior(const ImRect& frame_bb, ImGuiID id, float* v, float v_min, float v_max, float power, int decimal_precision, ImGuiSliderFlags flags)
6495 {
6496  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
6497  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
6498  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
6499 
6500  // Draw frame
6501  RenderFrame(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_FrameBg), true, style.FrameRounding);
6502 
6503  const bool is_non_linear = (power < 1.0f-0.00001f) || (power > 1.0f+0.00001f);
6504  const bool is_horizontal = (flags & ImGuiSliderFlags_Vertical) == 0;
6505 
6506  const float grab_padding = 2.0f;
6507  const float slider_sz = is_horizontal ? (frame_bb.GetWidth() - grab_padding * 2.0f) : (frame_bb.GetHeight() - grab_padding * 2.0f);
6508  float grab_sz;
6509  if (decimal_precision > 0)
6510  grab_sz = ImMin(style.GrabMinSize, slider_sz);
6511  else
6512  grab_sz = ImMin(ImMax(1.0f * (slider_sz / ((v_min < v_max ? v_max - v_min : v_min - v_max) + 1.0f)), style.GrabMinSize), slider_sz); // Integer sliders, if possible have the grab size represent 1 unit
6513  const float slider_usable_sz = slider_sz - grab_sz;
6514  const float slider_usable_pos_min = (is_horizontal ? frame_bb.Min.x : frame_bb.Min.y) + grab_padding + grab_sz*0.5f;
6515  const float slider_usable_pos_max = (is_horizontal ? frame_bb.Max.x : frame_bb.Max.y) - grab_padding - grab_sz*0.5f;
6516 
6517  // For logarithmic sliders that cross over sign boundary we want the exponential increase to be symmetric around 0.0f
6518  float linear_zero_pos = 0.0f; // 0.0->1.0f
6519  if (v_min * v_max < 0.0f)
6520  {
6521  // Different sign
6522  const float linear_dist_min_to_0 = powf(fabsf(0.0f - v_min), 1.0f/power);
6523  const float linear_dist_max_to_0 = powf(fabsf(v_max - 0.0f), 1.0f/power);
6524  linear_zero_pos = linear_dist_min_to_0 / (linear_dist_min_to_0+linear_dist_max_to_0);
6525  }
6526  else
6527  {
6528  // Same sign
6529  linear_zero_pos = v_min < 0.0f ? 1.0f : 0.0f;
6530  }
6531 
6532  // Process clicking on the slider
6533  bool value_changed = false;
6534  if (g.ActiveId == id)
6535  {
6536  if (g.IO.MouseDown[0])
6537  {
6538  const float mouse_abs_pos = is_horizontal ? g.IO.MousePos.x : g.IO.MousePos.y;
6539  float clicked_t = (slider_usable_sz > 0.0f) ? ImClamp((mouse_abs_pos - slider_usable_pos_min) / slider_usable_sz, 0.0f, 1.0f) : 0.0f;
6540  if (!is_horizontal)
6541  clicked_t = 1.0f - clicked_t;
6542 
6543  float new_value;
6544  if (is_non_linear)
6545  {
6546  // Account for logarithmic scale on both sides of the zero
6547  if (clicked_t < linear_zero_pos)
6548  {
6549  // Negative: rescale to the negative range before powering
6550  float a = 1.0f - (clicked_t / linear_zero_pos);
6551  a = powf(a, power);
6552  new_value = ImLerp(ImMin(v_max,0.0f), v_min, a);
6553  }
6554  else
6555  {
6556  // Positive: rescale to the positive range before powering
6557  float a;
6558  if (fabsf(linear_zero_pos - 1.0f) > 1.e-6f)
6559  a = (clicked_t - linear_zero_pos) / (1.0f - linear_zero_pos);
6560  else
6561  a = clicked_t;
6562  a = powf(a, power);
6563  new_value = ImLerp(ImMax(v_min,0.0f), v_max, a);
6564  }
6565  }
6566  else
6567  {
6568  // Linear slider
6569  new_value = ImLerp(v_min, v_max, clicked_t);
6570  }
6571 
6572  // Round past decimal precision
6573  new_value = RoundScalar(new_value, decimal_precision);
6574  if (*v != new_value)
6575  {
6576  *v = new_value;
6577  value_changed = true;
6578  }
6579  }
6580  else
6581  {
6582  ClearActiveID();
6583  }
6584  }
6585 
6586  // Calculate slider grab positioning
6587  float grab_t = SliderBehaviorCalcRatioFromValue(*v, v_min, v_max, power, linear_zero_pos);
6588 
6589  // Draw
6590  if (!is_horizontal)
6591  grab_t = 1.0f - grab_t;
6592  const float grab_pos = ImLerp(slider_usable_pos_min, slider_usable_pos_max, grab_t);
6593  ImRect grab_bb;
6594  if (is_horizontal)
6595  grab_bb = ImRect(ImVec2(grab_pos - grab_sz*0.5f, frame_bb.Min.y + grab_padding), ImVec2(grab_pos + grab_sz*0.5f, frame_bb.Max.y - grab_padding));
6596  else
6597  grab_bb = ImRect(ImVec2(frame_bb.Min.x + grab_padding, grab_pos - grab_sz*0.5f), ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x - grab_padding, grab_pos + grab_sz*0.5f));
6598  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(grab_bb.Min, grab_bb.Max, GetColorU32(g.ActiveId == id ? ImGuiCol_SliderGrabActive : ImGuiCol_SliderGrab), style.GrabRounding);
6599 
6600  return value_changed;
6601 }
6602 
6603 // Use power!=1.0 for logarithmic sliders.
6604 // Adjust display_format to decorate the value with a prefix or a suffix.
6605 // "%.3f" 1.234
6606 // "%5.2f secs" 01.23 secs
6607 // "Gold: %.0f" Gold: 1
6608 bool ImGui::SliderFloat(const char* label, float* v, float v_min, float v_max, const char* display_format, float power)
6609 {
6610  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
6611  if (window->SkipItems)
6612  return false;
6613 
6614  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
6615  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
6616  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
6617  const float w = CalcItemWidth();
6618 
6619  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
6620  const ImRect frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(w, label_size.y + style.FramePadding.y*2.0f));
6621  const ImRect total_bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max + ImVec2(label_size.x > 0.0f ? style.ItemInnerSpacing.x + label_size.x : 0.0f, 0.0f));
6622 
6623  // NB- we don't call ItemSize() yet because we may turn into a text edit box below
6624  if (!ItemAdd(total_bb, &id))
6625  {
6626  ItemSize(total_bb, style.FramePadding.y);
6627  return false;
6628  }
6629 
6630  const bool hovered = IsHovered(frame_bb, id);
6631  if (hovered)
6632  SetHoveredID(id);
6633 
6634  if (!display_format)
6635  display_format = "%.3f";
6636  int decimal_precision = ParseFormatPrecision(display_format, 3);
6637 
6638  // Tabbing or CTRL-clicking on Slider turns it into an input box
6639  bool start_text_input = false;
6640  const bool tab_focus_requested = FocusableItemRegister(window, g.ActiveId == id);
6641  if (tab_focus_requested || (hovered && g.IO.MouseClicked[0]))
6642  {
6643  SetActiveID(id, window);
6644  FocusWindow(window);
6645 
6646  if (tab_focus_requested || g.IO.KeyCtrl)
6647  {
6648  start_text_input = true;
6649  g.ScalarAsInputTextId = 0;
6650  }
6651  }
6652  if (start_text_input || (g.ActiveId == id && g.ScalarAsInputTextId == id))
6653  return InputScalarAsWidgetReplacement(frame_bb, label, ImGuiDataType_Float, v, id, decimal_precision);
6654 
6655  ItemSize(total_bb, style.FramePadding.y);
6656 
6657  // Actual slider behavior + render grab
6658  const bool value_changed = SliderBehavior(frame_bb, id, v, v_min, v_max, power, decimal_precision);
6659 
6660  // Display value using user-provided display format so user can add prefix/suffix/decorations to the value.
6661  char value_buf[64];
6662  const char* value_buf_end = value_buf + ImFormatString(value_buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(value_buf), display_format, *v);
6663  RenderTextClipped(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max, value_buf, value_buf_end, NULL, ImVec2(0.5f,0.5f));
6664 
6665  if (label_size.x > 0.0f)
6666  RenderText(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, frame_bb.Min.y + style.FramePadding.y), label);
6667 
6668  return value_changed;
6669 }
6670 
6671 bool ImGui::VSliderFloat(const char* label, const ImVec2& size, float* v, float v_min, float v_max, const char* display_format, float power)
6672 {
6673  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
6674  if (window->SkipItems)
6675  return false;
6676 
6677  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
6678  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
6679  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
6680 
6681  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
6682  const ImRect frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + size);
6683  const ImRect bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max + ImVec2(label_size.x > 0.0f ? style.ItemInnerSpacing.x + label_size.x : 0.0f, 0.0f));
6684 
6685  ItemSize(bb, style.FramePadding.y);
6686  if (!ItemAdd(frame_bb, &id))
6687  return false;
6688 
6689  const bool hovered = IsHovered(frame_bb, id);
6690  if (hovered)
6691  SetHoveredID(id);
6692 
6693  if (!display_format)
6694  display_format = "%.3f";
6695  int decimal_precision = ParseFormatPrecision(display_format, 3);
6696 
6697  if (hovered && g.IO.MouseClicked[0])
6698  {
6699  SetActiveID(id, window);
6700  FocusWindow(window);
6701  }
6702 
6703  // Actual slider behavior + render grab
6704  bool value_changed = SliderBehavior(frame_bb, id, v, v_min, v_max, power, decimal_precision, ImGuiSliderFlags_Vertical);
6705 
6706  // Display value using user-provided display format so user can add prefix/suffix/decorations to the value.
6707  // For the vertical slider we allow centered text to overlap the frame padding
6708  char value_buf[64];
6709  char* value_buf_end = value_buf + ImFormatString(value_buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(value_buf), display_format, *v);
6710  RenderTextClipped(ImVec2(frame_bb.Min.x, frame_bb.Min.y + style.FramePadding.y), frame_bb.Max, value_buf, value_buf_end, NULL, ImVec2(0.5f,0.0f));
6711  if (label_size.x > 0.0f)
6712  RenderText(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, frame_bb.Min.y + style.FramePadding.y), label);
6713 
6714  return value_changed;
6715 }

6829 
6830 bool ImGui::DragBehavior(const ImRect& frame_bb, ImGuiID id, float* v, float v_speed, float v_min, float v_max, int decimal_precision, float power)
6831 {
6832  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
6833  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
6834 
6835  // Draw frame
6836  const ImU32 frame_col = GetColorU32(g.ActiveId == id ? ImGuiCol_FrameBgActive : g.HoveredId == id ? ImGuiCol_FrameBgHovered : ImGuiCol_FrameBg);
6837  RenderFrame(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max, frame_col, true, style.FrameRounding);
6838 
6839  bool value_changed = false;
6840 
6841  // Process clicking on the drag
6842  if (g.ActiveId == id)
6843  {
6844  if (g.IO.MouseDown[0])
6845  {
6846  if (g.ActiveIdIsJustActivated)
6847  {
6848  // Lock current value on click
6849  g.DragCurrentValue = *v;
6850  g.DragLastMouseDelta = ImVec2(0.f, 0.f);
6851  }
6852 
6853  float v_cur = g.DragCurrentValue;
6854  const ImVec2 mouse_drag_delta = GetMouseDragDelta(0, 1.0f);
6855  if (fabsf(mouse_drag_delta.x - g.DragLastMouseDelta.x) > 0.0f)
6856  {
6857  float speed = v_speed;
6858  if (speed == 0.0f && (v_max - v_min) != 0.0f && (v_max - v_min) < FLT_MAX)
6859  speed = (v_max - v_min) * g.DragSpeedDefaultRatio;
6860  if (g.IO.KeyShift && g.DragSpeedScaleFast >= 0.0f)
6861  speed = speed * g.DragSpeedScaleFast;
6862  if (g.IO.KeyAlt && g.DragSpeedScaleSlow >= 0.0f)
6863  speed = speed * g.DragSpeedScaleSlow;
6864 
6865  float delta = (mouse_drag_delta.x - g.DragLastMouseDelta.x) * speed;
6866  if (fabsf(power - 1.0f) > 0.001f)
6867  {
6868  // Logarithmic curve on both side of 0.0
6869  float v0_abs = v_cur >= 0.0f ? v_cur : -v_cur;
6870  float v0_sign = v_cur >= 0.0f ? 1.0f : -1.0f;
6871  float v1 = powf(v0_abs, 1.0f / power) + (delta * v0_sign);
6872  float v1_abs = v1 >= 0.0f ? v1 : -v1;
6873  float v1_sign = v1 >= 0.0f ? 1.0f : -1.0f; // Crossed sign line
6874  v_cur = powf(v1_abs, power) * v0_sign * v1_sign; // Reapply sign
6875  }
6876  else
6877  {
6878  v_cur += delta;
6879  }
6880  g.DragLastMouseDelta.x = mouse_drag_delta.x;
6881 
6882  // Clamp
6883  if (v_min < v_max)
6884  v_cur = ImClamp(v_cur, v_min, v_max);
6885  g.DragCurrentValue = v_cur;
6886  }
6887 
6888  // Round to user desired precision, then apply
6889  v_cur = RoundScalar(v_cur, decimal_precision);
6890  if (*v != v_cur)
6891  {
6892  *v = v_cur;
6893  value_changed = true;
6894  }
6895  }
6896  else
6897  {
6898  ClearActiveID();
6899  }
6900  }
6901 
6902  return value_changed;
6903 }
6904 
6905 bool ImGui::DragFloat(const char* label, float* v, float v_speed, float v_min, float v_max, const char* display_format, float power)
6906 {
6907  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
6908  if (window->SkipItems)
6909  return false;
6910 
6911  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
6912  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
6913  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
6914  const float w = CalcItemWidth();
6915 
6916  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
6917  const ImRect frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(w, label_size.y + style.FramePadding.y*2.0f));
6918  const ImRect inner_bb(frame_bb.Min + style.FramePadding, frame_bb.Max - style.FramePadding);
6919  const ImRect total_bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max + ImVec2(label_size.x > 0.0f ? style.ItemInnerSpacing.x + label_size.x : 0.0f, 0.0f));
6920 
6921  // NB- we don't call ItemSize() yet because we may turn into a text edit box below
6922  if (!ItemAdd(total_bb, &id))
6923  {
6924  ItemSize(total_bb, style.FramePadding.y);
6925  return false;
6926  }
6927 
6928  const bool hovered = IsHovered(frame_bb, id);
6929  if (hovered)
6930  SetHoveredID(id);
6931 
6932  if (!display_format)
6933  display_format = "%.3f";
6934  int decimal_precision = ParseFormatPrecision(display_format, 3);
6935 
6936  // Tabbing or CTRL-clicking on Drag turns it into an input box
6937  bool start_text_input = false;
6938  const bool tab_focus_requested = FocusableItemRegister(window, g.ActiveId == id);
6939  if (tab_focus_requested || (hovered && (g.IO.MouseClicked[0] | g.IO.MouseDoubleClicked[0])))
6940  {
6941  SetActiveID(id, window);
6942  FocusWindow(window);
6943 
6944  if (tab_focus_requested || g.IO.KeyCtrl || g.IO.MouseDoubleClicked[0])
6945  {
6946  start_text_input = true;
6947  g.ScalarAsInputTextId = 0;
6948  }
6949  }
6950  if (start_text_input || (g.ActiveId == id && g.ScalarAsInputTextId == id))
6951  return InputScalarAsWidgetReplacement(frame_bb, label, ImGuiDataType_Float, v, id, decimal_precision);
6952 
6953  // Actual drag behavior
6954  ItemSize(total_bb, style.FramePadding.y);
6955  const bool value_changed = DragBehavior(frame_bb, id, v, v_speed, v_min, v_max, decimal_precision, power);
6956 
6957  // Display value using user-provided display format so user can add prefix/suffix/decorations to the value.
6958  char value_buf[64];
6959  const char* value_buf_end = value_buf + ImFormatString(value_buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(value_buf), display_format, *v);
6960  RenderTextClipped(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max, value_buf, value_buf_end, NULL, ImVec2(0.5f,0.5f));
6961 
6962  if (label_size.x > 0.0f)
6963  RenderText(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, inner_bb.Min.y), label);
6964 
6965  return value_changed;
6966 }

7112 
7113 void ImGui::PlotEx(ImGuiPlotType plot_type, const char* label, float (*values_getter)(void* data, int idx), void* data, int values_count, int values_offset, const char* overlay_text, float scale_min, float scale_max, ImVec2 graph_size)
7114 {
7115  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
7116  if (window->SkipItems)
7117  return;
7118 
7119  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
7120  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
7121 
7122  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
7123  if (graph_size.x == 0.0f)
7124  graph_size.x = CalcItemWidth();
7125  if (graph_size.y == 0.0f)
7126  graph_size.y = label_size.y + (style.FramePadding.y * 2);
7127 
7128  const ImRect frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(graph_size.x, graph_size.y));
7129  const ImRect inner_bb(frame_bb.Min + style.FramePadding, frame_bb.Max - style.FramePadding);
7130  const ImRect total_bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max + ImVec2(label_size.x > 0.0f ? style.ItemInnerSpacing.x + label_size.x : 0.0f, 0));
7131  ItemSize(total_bb, style.FramePadding.y);
7132  if (!ItemAdd(total_bb, NULL))
7133  return;
7134 
7135  // Determine scale from values if not specified
7136  if (scale_min == FLT_MAX || scale_max == FLT_MAX)
7137  {
7138  float v_min = FLT_MAX;
7139  float v_max = -FLT_MAX;
7140  for (int i = 0; i < values_count; i++)
7141  {
7142  const float v = values_getter(data, i);
7143  v_min = ImMin(v_min, v);
7144  v_max = ImMax(v_max, v);
7145  }
7146  if (scale_min == FLT_MAX)
7147  scale_min = v_min;
7148  if (scale_max == FLT_MAX)
7149  scale_max = v_max;
7150  }
7151 
7152  RenderFrame(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_FrameBg), true, style.FrameRounding);
7153 
7154  if (values_count > 0)
7155  {
7156  int res_w = ImMin((int)graph_size.x, values_count) + ((plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines) ? -1 : 0);
7157  int item_count = values_count + ((plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines) ? -1 : 0);
7158 
7159  // Tooltip on hover
7160  int v_hovered = -1;
7161  if (IsHovered(inner_bb, 0))
7162  {
7163  const float t = ImClamp((g.IO.MousePos.x - inner_bb.Min.x) / (inner_bb.Max.x - inner_bb.Min.x), 0.0f, 0.9999f);
7164  const int v_idx = (int)(t * item_count);
7165  IM_ASSERT(v_idx >= 0 && v_idx < values_count);
7166 
7167  const float v0 = values_getter(data, (v_idx + values_offset) % values_count);
7168  const float v1 = values_getter(data, (v_idx + 1 + values_offset) % values_count);
7169  if (plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines)
7170  SetTooltip("%d: %8.4g\n%d: %8.4g", v_idx, v0, v_idx+1, v1);
7171  else if (plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Histogram)
7172  SetTooltip("%d: %8.4g", v_idx, v0);
7173  v_hovered = v_idx;
7174  }
7175 
7176  const float t_step = 1.0f / (float)res_w;
7177 
7178  float v0 = values_getter(data, (0 + values_offset) % values_count);
7179  float t0 = 0.0f;
7180  ImVec2 tp0 = ImVec2( t0, 1.0f - ImSaturate((v0 - scale_min) / (scale_max - scale_min)) ); // Point in the normalized space of our target rectangle
7181 
7182  const ImU32 col_base = GetColorU32((plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines) ? ImGuiCol_PlotLines : ImGuiCol_PlotHistogram);
7183  const ImU32 col_hovered = GetColorU32((plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines) ? ImGuiCol_PlotLinesHovered : ImGuiCol_PlotHistogramHovered);
7184 
7185  for (int n = 0; n < res_w; n++)
7186  {
7187  const float t1 = t0 + t_step;
7188  const int v1_idx = (int)(t0 * item_count + 0.5f);
7189  IM_ASSERT(v1_idx >= 0 && v1_idx < values_count);
7190  const float v1 = values_getter(data, (v1_idx + values_offset + 1) % values_count);
7191  const ImVec2 tp1 = ImVec2( t1, 1.0f - ImSaturate((v1 - scale_min) / (scale_max - scale_min)) );
7192 
7193  // NB: Draw calls are merged together by the DrawList system. Still, we should render our batch are lower level to save a bit of CPU.
7194  ImVec2 pos0 = ImLerp(inner_bb.Min, inner_bb.Max, tp0);
7195  ImVec2 pos1 = ImLerp(inner_bb.Min, inner_bb.Max, (plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines) ? tp1 : ImVec2(tp1.x, 1.0f));
7196  if (plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines)
7197  {
7198  window->DrawList->AddLine(pos0, pos1, v_hovered == v1_idx ? col_hovered : col_base);
7199  }
7200  else if (plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Histogram)
7201  {
7202  if (pos1.x >= pos0.x + 2.0f)
7203  pos1.x -= 1.0f;
7204  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(pos0, pos1, v_hovered == v1_idx ? col_hovered : col_base);
7205  }
7206 
7207  t0 = t1;
7208  tp0 = tp1;
7209  }
7210  }
7211 
7212  // Text overlay
7213  if (overlay_text)
7214  RenderTextClipped(ImVec2(frame_bb.Min.x, frame_bb.Min.y + style.FramePadding.y), frame_bb.Max, overlay_text, NULL, NULL, ImVec2(0.5f,0.0f));
7215 
7216  if (label_size.x > 0.0f)
7217  RenderText(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, inner_bb.Min.y), label);
7218 }

7257 // size_arg (for each axis) < 0.0f: align to end, 0.0f: auto, > 0.0f: specified size
7258 void ImGui::ProgressBar(float fraction, const ImVec2& size_arg, const char* overlay)
7259 {
7260  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
7261  if (window->SkipItems)
7262  return;
7263 
7264  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
7265  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
7266 
7267  ImVec2 pos = window->DC.CursorPos;
7268  ImRect bb(pos, pos + CalcItemSize(size_arg, CalcItemWidth(), g.FontSize + style.FramePadding.y*2.0f));
7269  ItemSize(bb, style.FramePadding.y);
7270  if (!ItemAdd(bb, NULL))
7271  return;
7272 
7273  // Render
7274  fraction = ImSaturate(fraction);
7275  RenderFrame(bb.Min, bb.Max, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_FrameBg), true, style.FrameRounding);
7276  bb.Reduce(ImVec2(window->BorderSize, window->BorderSize));
7277  const ImVec2 fill_br = ImVec2(ImLerp(bb.Min.x, bb.Max.x, fraction), bb.Max.y);
7278  RenderFrame(bb.Min, fill_br, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_PlotHistogram), false, style.FrameRounding);
7279 
7280  // Default displaying the fraction as percentage string, but user can override it
7281  char overlay_buf[32];
7282  if (!overlay)
7283  {
7284  ImFormatString(overlay_buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(overlay_buf), "%.0f%%", fraction*100+0.01f);
7285  overlay = overlay_buf;
7286  }
7287 
7288  ImVec2 overlay_size = CalcTextSize(overlay, NULL);
7289  if (overlay_size.x > 0.0f)
7290  RenderTextClipped(ImVec2(ImClamp(fill_br.x + style.ItemSpacing.x, bb.Min.x, bb.Max.x - overlay_size.x - style.ItemInnerSpacing.x), bb.Min.y), bb.Max, overlay, NULL, &overlay_size, ImVec2(0.0f,0.5f), &bb);
7291 }

7293 bool ImGui::Checkbox(const char* label, bool* v)
7294 {
7295  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
7296  if (window->SkipItems)
7297  return false;
7298 
7299  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
7300  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
7301  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
7302  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
7303 
7304  const ImRect check_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(label_size.y + style.FramePadding.y*2, label_size.y + style.FramePadding.y*2));
7305  ItemSize(check_bb, style.FramePadding.y);
7306 
7307  ImRect total_bb = check_bb;
7308  if (label_size.x > 0)
7309  SameLine(0, style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
7310  const ImRect text_bb(window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(0,style.FramePadding.y), window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(0,style.FramePadding.y) + label_size);
7311  if (label_size.x > 0)
7312  {
7313  ItemSize(ImVec2(text_bb.GetWidth(), check_bb.GetHeight()), style.FramePadding.y);
7314  total_bb = ImRect(ImMin(check_bb.Min, text_bb.Min), ImMax(check_bb.Max, text_bb.Max));
7315  }
7316 
7317  if (!ItemAdd(total_bb, &id))
7318  return false;
7319 
7320  bool hovered, held;
7321  bool pressed = ButtonBehavior(total_bb, id, &hovered, &held);
7322  if (pressed)
7323  *v = !(*v);
7324 
7325  RenderFrame(check_bb.Min, check_bb.Max, GetColorU32((held && hovered) ? ImGuiCol_FrameBgActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_FrameBgHovered : ImGuiCol_FrameBg), true, style.FrameRounding);
7326  if (*v)
7327  {
7328  const float check_sz = ImMin(check_bb.GetWidth(), check_bb.GetHeight());
7329  const float pad = ImMax(1.0f, (float)(int)(check_sz / 6.0f));
7330  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(check_bb.Min+ImVec2(pad,pad), check_bb.Max-ImVec2(pad,pad), GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_CheckMark), style.FrameRounding);
7331  }
7332 
7333  if (g.LogEnabled)
7334  LogRenderedText(text_bb.GetTL(), *v ? "[x]" : "[ ]");
7335  if (label_size.x > 0.0f)
7336  RenderText(text_bb.GetTL(), label);
7337 
7338  return pressed;
7339 }

7402  window->DrawList->AddCircle(center, radius, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Border), 16);
7403  }
7404 
7405  if (g.LogEnabled)
7406  LogRenderedText(text_bb.GetTL(), active ? "(x)" : "( )");
7407  if (label_size.x > 0.0f)
7408  RenderText(text_bb.GetTL(), label);

7423 static int InputTextCalcTextLenAndLineCount(const char* text_begin, const char** out_text_end)
7424 {
7425  int line_count = 0;
7426  const char* s = text_begin;
7427  while (char c = *s++) // We are only matching for \n so we can ignore UTF-8 decoding
7428  if (c == '\n')
7429  line_count++;
7430  s--;
7431  if (s[0] != '\n' && s[0] != '\r')
7432  line_count++;
7433  *out_text_end = s;
7434  return line_count;
7435 }
7436 
7437 static ImVec2 InputTextCalcTextSizeW(const ImWchar* text_begin, const ImWchar* text_end, const ImWchar** remaining, ImVec2* out_offset, bool stop_on_new_line)
7438 {
7439  ImFont* font = GImGui->Font;
7440  const float line_height = GImGui->FontSize;
7441  const float scale = line_height / font->FontSize;
7442 
7443  ImVec2 text_size = ImVec2(0,0);
7444  float line_width = 0.0f;
7445 
7446  const ImWchar* s = text_begin;
7447  while (s < text_end)
7448  {
7449  unsigned int c = (unsigned int)(*s++);
7450  if (c == '\n')
7451  {
7452  text_size.x = ImMax(text_size.x, line_width);
7453  text_size.y += line_height;
7454  line_width = 0.0f;
7455  if (stop_on_new_line)
7456  break;
7457  continue;
7458  }
7459  if (c == '\r')
7460  continue;
7461 
7462  const float char_width = font->GetCharAdvance((unsigned short)c) * scale;
7463  line_width += char_width;
7464  }
7465 
7466  if (text_size.x < line_width)
7467  text_size.x = line_width;
7468 
7469  if (out_offset)
7470  *out_offset = ImVec2(line_width, text_size.y + line_height); // offset allow for the possibility of sitting after a trailing \n
7471 
7472  if (line_width > 0 || text_size.y == 0.0f) // whereas size.y will ignore the trailing \n
7473  text_size.y += line_height;
7474 
7475  if (remaining)
7476  *remaining = s;
7477 
7478  return text_size;
7479 }

7481 // Wrapper for stb_textedit.h to edit text (our wrapper is for: statically sized buffer, single-line, wchar characters. InputText converts between UTF-8 and wchar)
7482 namespace ImGuiStb
7483 {
7484 
7485 static int STB_TEXTEDIT_STRINGLEN(const STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj) { return obj->CurLenW; }
7486 static ImWchar STB_TEXTEDIT_GETCHAR(const STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int idx) { return obj->Text[idx]; }
7487 static float STB_TEXTEDIT_GETWIDTH(STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int line_start_idx, int char_idx) { ImWchar c = obj->Text[line_start_idx+char_idx]; if (c == '\n') return STB_TEXTEDIT_GETWIDTH_NEWLINE; return GImGui->Font->GetCharAdvance(c) * (GImGui->FontSize / GImGui->Font->FontSize); }
7488 static int STB_TEXTEDIT_KEYTOTEXT(int key) { return key >= 0x10000 ? 0 : key; }
7489 static ImWchar STB_TEXTEDIT_NEWLINE = '\n';
7490 static void STB_TEXTEDIT_LAYOUTROW(StbTexteditRow* r, STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int line_start_idx)
7491 {
7492  const ImWchar* text = obj->Text.Data;
7493  const ImWchar* text_remaining = NULL;
7494  const ImVec2 size = InputTextCalcTextSizeW(text + line_start_idx, text + obj->CurLenW, &text_remaining, NULL, true);
7495  r->x0 = 0.0f;
7496  r->x1 = size.x;
7497  r->baseline_y_delta = size.y;
7498  r->ymin = 0.0f;
7499  r->ymax = size.y;
7500  r->num_chars = (int)(text_remaining - (text + line_start_idx));
7501 }

7503 static bool is_separator(unsigned int c) { return ImCharIsSpace(c) || c==',' || c==';' || c=='(' || c==')' || c=='{' || c=='}' || c=='[' || c==']' || c=='|'; }
7504 static int is_word_boundary_from_right(STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int idx) { return idx > 0 ? (is_separator( obj->Text[idx-1] ) && !is_separator( obj->Text[idx] ) ) : 1; }
7505 static int STB_TEXTEDIT_MOVEWORDLEFT_IMPL(STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int idx) { idx--; while (idx >= 0 && !is_word_boundary_from_right(obj, idx)) idx--; return idx < 0 ? 0 : idx; }
7506 #ifdef __APPLE__ // FIXME: Move setting to IO structure
7507 static int is_word_boundary_from_left(STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int idx) { return idx > 0 ? (!is_separator( obj->Text[idx-1] ) && is_separator( obj->Text[idx] ) ) : 1; }
7508 static int STB_TEXTEDIT_MOVEWORDRIGHT_IMPL(STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int idx) { idx++; int len = obj->CurLenW; while (idx < len && !is_word_boundary_from_left(obj, idx)) idx++; return idx > len ? len : idx; }
7509 #else
7510 static int STB_TEXTEDIT_MOVEWORDRIGHT_IMPL(STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int idx) { idx++; int len = obj->CurLenW; while (idx < len && !is_word_boundary_from_right(obj, idx)) idx++; return idx > len ? len : idx; }
7511 #endif
7512 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_MOVEWORDLEFT STB_TEXTEDIT_MOVEWORDLEFT_IMPL // They need to be #define for stb_textedit.h
7513 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_MOVEWORDRIGHT STB_TEXTEDIT_MOVEWORDRIGHT_IMPL
7514 
7515 static void STB_TEXTEDIT_DELETECHARS(STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int pos, int n)
7516 {
7517  ImWchar* dst = obj->Text.Data + pos;
7518 
7519  // We maintain our buffer length in both UTF-8 and wchar formats
7520  obj->CurLenA -= ImTextCountUtf8BytesFromStr(dst, dst + n);
7521  obj->CurLenW -= n;
7522 
7523  // Offset remaining text
7524  const ImWchar* src = obj->Text.Data + pos + n;
7525  while (ImWchar c = *src++)
7526  *dst++ = c;
7527  *dst = '\0';
7528 }
7529 
7530 static bool STB_TEXTEDIT_INSERTCHARS(STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int pos, const ImWchar* new_text, int new_text_len)
7531 {
7532  const int text_len = obj->CurLenW;
7533  IM_ASSERT(pos <= text_len);
7534  if (new_text_len + text_len + 1 > obj->Text.Size)
7535  return false;
7536 
7537  const int new_text_len_utf8 = ImTextCountUtf8BytesFromStr(new_text, new_text + new_text_len);
7538  if (new_text_len_utf8 + obj->CurLenA + 1 > obj->BufSizeA)
7539  return false;
7540 
7541  ImWchar* text = obj->Text.Data;
7542  if (pos != text_len)
7543  memmove(text + pos + new_text_len, text + pos, (size_t)(text_len - pos) * sizeof(ImWchar));
7544  memcpy(text + pos, new_text, (size_t)new_text_len * sizeof(ImWchar));
7545 
7546  obj->CurLenW += new_text_len;
7547  obj->CurLenA += new_text_len_utf8;
7548  obj->Text[obj->CurLenW] = '\0';
7549 
7550  return true;
7551 }

7553 // We don't use an enum so we can build even with conflicting symbols (if another user of stb_textedit.h leak their STB_TEXTEDIT_K_* symbols)

7555 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_RIGHT 0x10001 // keyboard input to move cursor right
7556 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_UP 0x10002 // keyboard input to move cursor up
7557 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_DOWN 0x10003 // keyboard input to move cursor down
7558 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LINESTART 0x10004 // keyboard input to move cursor to start of line
7559 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LINEEND 0x10005 // keyboard input to move cursor to end of line
7560 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_TEXTSTART 0x10006 // keyboard input to move cursor to start of text
7561 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_TEXTEND 0x10007 // keyboard input to move cursor to end of text
7562 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_DELETE 0x10008 // keyboard input to delete selection or character under cursor
7563 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_BACKSPACE 0x10009 // keyboard input to delete selection or character left of cursor
7564 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_UNDO 0x1000A // keyboard input to perform undo
7565 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_REDO 0x1000B // keyboard input to perform redo
7566 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_WORDLEFT 0x1000C // keyboard input to move cursor left one word
7567 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_WORDRIGHT 0x1000D // keyboard input to move cursor right one word
7568 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_K_SHIFT 0x20000
