7582 // Public API to manipulate UTF-8 text
7583 // We expose UTF-8 to the user (unlike the STB_TEXTEDIT_* functions which are manipulating wchar)
7584 // FIXME: The existence of this rarely exercised code path is a bit of a nuisance.
7585 void ImGuiTextEditCallbackData::DeleteChars(int pos, int bytes_count)
7586 {
7587  IM_ASSERT(pos + bytes_count <= BufTextLen);
7588  char* dst = Buf + pos;
7589  const char* src = Buf + pos + bytes_count;
7590  while (char c = *src++)
7591  *dst++ = c;
7592  *dst = '\0';
7593 
7594  if (CursorPos + bytes_count >= pos)
7595  CursorPos -= bytes_count;
7596  else if (CursorPos >= pos)
7597  CursorPos = pos;
7598  SelectionStart = SelectionEnd = CursorPos;
7599  BufDirty = true;
7600  BufTextLen -= bytes_count;
7601 }
7602 
7603 void ImGuiTextEditCallbackData::InsertChars(int pos, const char* new_text, const char* new_text_end)
7604 {
7605  const int new_text_len = new_text_end ? (int)(new_text_end - new_text) : (int)strlen(new_text);
7606  if (new_text_len + BufTextLen + 1 >= BufSize)
7607  return;
7608 
7609  if (BufTextLen != pos)
7610  memmove(Buf + pos + new_text_len, Buf + pos, (size_t)(BufTextLen - pos));
7611  memcpy(Buf + pos, new_text, (size_t)new_text_len * sizeof(char));
7612  Buf[BufTextLen + new_text_len] = '\0';
7613 
7614  if (CursorPos >= pos)
7615  CursorPos += new_text_len;
7616  SelectionStart = SelectionEnd = CursorPos;
7617  BufDirty = true;
7618  BufTextLen += new_text_len;
7619 }
7620 
7621 // Return false to discard a character.
7622 static bool InputTextFilterCharacter(unsigned int* p_char, ImGuiInputTextFlags flags, ImGuiTextEditCallback callback, void* user_data)
7623 {
7624  unsigned int c = *p_char;
7625 
7626  if (c < 128 && c != ' ' && !isprint((int)(c & 0xFF)))
7627  {
7628  bool pass = false;
7629  pass |= (c == '\n' && (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_Multiline));
7630  pass |= (c == '\t' && (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_AllowTabInput));
7631  if (!pass)
7632  return false;
7633  }
7634 
7635  if (c >= 0xE000 && c <= 0xF8FF) // Filter private Unicode range. I don't imagine anybody would want to input them. GLFW on OSX seems to send private characters for special keys like arrow keys.
7636  return false;
7637 
7638  if (flags & (ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsDecimal | ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsHexadecimal | ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsUppercase | ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsNoBlank))
7639  {
7640  if (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsDecimal)
7641  if (!(c >= '0' && c <= '9') && (c != '.') && (c != '-') && (c != '+') && (c != '*') && (c != '/'))
7642  return false;
7643 
7644  if (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsHexadecimal)
7645  if (!(c >= '0' && c <= '9') && !(c >= 'a' && c <= 'f') && !(c >= 'A' && c <= 'F'))
7646  return false;
7647 
7648  if (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsUppercase)
7649  if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z')
7650  *p_char = (c += (unsigned int)('A'-'a'));
7651 
7652  if (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsNoBlank)
7653  if (ImCharIsSpace(c))
7654  return false;
7655  }
7656 
7657  if (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackCharFilter)
7658  {
7659  ImGuiTextEditCallbackData callback_data;
7660  memset(&callback_data, 0, sizeof(ImGuiTextEditCallbackData));
7661  callback_data.EventFlag = ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackCharFilter;
7662  callback_data.EventChar = (ImWchar)c;
7663  callback_data.Flags = flags;
7664  callback_data.UserData = user_data;
7665  if (callback(&callback_data) != 0)
7666  return false;
7667  *p_char = callback_data.EventChar;
7668  if (!callback_data.EventChar)
7669  return false;
7670  }
7671 
7672  return true;
7673 }
7674 
7675 // Edit a string of text
7676 // NB: when active, hold on a privately held copy of the text (and apply back to 'buf'). So changing 'buf' while active has no effect.
7677 // FIXME: Rather messy function partly because we are doing UTF8 > u16 > UTF8 conversions on the go to more easily handle stb_textedit calls. Ideally we should stay in UTF-8 all the time. See https://github.com/nothings/stb/issues/188
7678 bool ImGui::InputTextEx(const char* label, char* buf, int buf_size, const ImVec2& size_arg, ImGuiInputTextFlags flags, ImGuiTextEditCallback callback, void* user_data)
7679 {
7680  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
7681  if (window->SkipItems)
7682  return false;
7683 
7684  IM_ASSERT(!((flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackHistory) && (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_Multiline))); // Can't use both together (they both use up/down keys)
7685  IM_ASSERT(!((flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackCompletion) && (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_AllowTabInput))); // Can't use both together (they both use tab key)
7686 
7687  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
7688  const ImGuiIO& io = g.IO;
7689  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
7690 
7691  const bool is_multiline = (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_Multiline) != 0;
7692  const bool is_editable = (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_ReadOnly) == 0;
7693  const bool is_password = (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_Password) != 0;
7694 
7695  if (is_multiline) // Open group before calling GetID() because groups tracks id created during their spawn
7696  BeginGroup();
7697  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
7698  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
7699  ImVec2 size = CalcItemSize(size_arg, CalcItemWidth(), (is_multiline ? GetTextLineHeight() * 8.0f : label_size.y) + style.FramePadding.y*2.0f); // Arbitrary default of 8 lines high for multi-line
7700  const ImRect frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + size);
7701  const ImRect total_bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max + ImVec2(label_size.x > 0.0f ? (style.ItemInnerSpacing.x + label_size.x) : 0.0f, 0.0f));
7702 
7703  ImGuiWindow* draw_window = window;
7704  if (is_multiline)
7705  {
7706  if (!BeginChildFrame(id, frame_bb.GetSize()))
7707  {
7708  EndChildFrame();
7709  EndGroup();
7710  return false;
7711  }
7712  draw_window = GetCurrentWindow();
7713  size.x -= draw_window->ScrollbarSizes.x;
7714  }
7715  else
7716  {
7717  ItemSize(total_bb, style.FramePadding.y);
7718  if (!ItemAdd(total_bb, &id))
7719  return false;
7720  }
7721 
7722  // Password pushes a temporary font with only a fallback glyph
7723  if (is_password)
7724  {
7725  const ImFont::Glyph* glyph = g.Font->FindGlyph('*');
7726  ImFont* password_font = &g.InputTextPasswordFont;
7727  password_font->FontSize = g.Font->FontSize;
7728  password_font->Scale = g.Font->Scale;
7729  password_font->DisplayOffset = g.Font->DisplayOffset;
7730  password_font->Ascent = g.Font->Ascent;
7731  password_font->Descent = g.Font->Descent;
7732  password_font->ContainerAtlas = g.Font->ContainerAtlas;
7733  password_font->FallbackGlyph = glyph;
7734  password_font->FallbackXAdvance = glyph->XAdvance;
7735  IM_ASSERT(password_font->Glyphs.empty() && password_font->IndexXAdvance.empty() && password_font->IndexLookup.empty());
7736  PushFont(password_font);
7737  }
7738 
7739  // NB: we are only allowed to access 'edit_state' if we are the active widget.
7740  ImGuiTextEditState& edit_state = g.InputTextState;
7741 
7742  const bool focus_requested = FocusableItemRegister(window, g.ActiveId == id, (flags & (ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackCompletion|ImGuiInputTextFlags_AllowTabInput)) == 0); // Using completion callback disable keyboard tabbing
7743  const bool focus_requested_by_code = focus_requested && (window->FocusIdxAllCounter == window->FocusIdxAllRequestCurrent);
7744  const bool focus_requested_by_tab = focus_requested && !focus_requested_by_code;
7745 
7746  const bool hovered = IsHovered(frame_bb, id);
7747  if (hovered)
7748  {
7749  SetHoveredID(id);
7750  g.MouseCursor = ImGuiMouseCursor_TextInput;
7751  }
7752  const bool user_clicked = hovered && io.MouseClicked[0];
7753  const bool user_scrolled = is_multiline && g.ActiveId == 0 && edit_state.Id == id && g.ActiveIdPreviousFrame == draw_window->GetIDNoKeepAlive("#SCROLLY");
7754 
7755  bool select_all = (g.ActiveId != id) && (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_AutoSelectAll) != 0;
7756  if (focus_requested || user_clicked || user_scrolled)
7757  {
7758  if (g.ActiveId != id)
7759  {
7760  // Start edition
7761  // Take a copy of the initial buffer value (both in original UTF-8 format and converted to wchar)
7762  // From the moment we focused we are ignoring the content of 'buf' (unless we are in read-only mode)
7763  const int prev_len_w = edit_state.CurLenW;
7764  edit_state.Text.resize(buf_size+1); // wchar count <= UTF-8 count. we use +1 to make sure that .Data isn't NULL so it doesn't crash.
7765  edit_state.InitialText.resize(buf_size+1); // UTF-8. we use +1 to make sure that .Data isn't NULL so it doesn't crash.
7766  ImStrncpy(edit_state.InitialText.Data, buf, edit_state.InitialText.Size);
7767  const char* buf_end = NULL;
7768  edit_state.CurLenW = ImTextStrFromUtf8(edit_state.Text.Data, edit_state.Text.Size, buf, NULL, &buf_end);
7769  edit_state.CurLenA = (int)(buf_end - buf); // We can't get the result from ImFormatString() above because it is not UTF-8 aware. Here we'll cut off malformed UTF-8.
7770  edit_state.CursorAnimReset();
7771 
7772  // Preserve cursor position and undo/redo stack if we come back to same widget
7773  // FIXME: We should probably compare the whole buffer to be on the safety side. Comparing buf (utf8) and edit_state.Text (wchar).
7774  const bool recycle_state = (edit_state.Id == id) && (prev_len_w == edit_state.CurLenW);
7775  if (recycle_state)
7776  {
7777  // Recycle existing cursor/selection/undo stack but clamp position
7778  // Note a single mouse click will override the cursor/position immediately by calling stb_textedit_click handler.
7779  edit_state.CursorClamp();
7780  }
7781  else
7782  {
7783  edit_state.Id = id;
7784  edit_state.ScrollX = 0.0f;
7785  stb_textedit_initialize_state(&edit_state.StbState, !is_multiline);
7786  if (!is_multiline && focus_requested_by_code)
7787  select_all = true;
7788  }
7789  if (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_AlwaysInsertMode)
7790  edit_state.StbState.insert_mode = true;
7791  if (!is_multiline && (focus_requested_by_tab || (user_clicked && io.KeyCtrl)))
7792  select_all = true;
7793  }
7794  SetActiveID(id, window);
7795  FocusWindow(window);
7796  }
7797  else if (io.MouseClicked[0])
7798  {
7799  // Release focus when we click outside
7800  if (g.ActiveId == id)
7801  ClearActiveID();
7802  }
7803 
7804  bool value_changed = false;
7805  bool enter_pressed = false;
7806 
7807  if (g.ActiveId == id)
7808  {
7809  if (!is_editable && !g.ActiveIdIsJustActivated)
7810  {
7811  // When read-only we always use the live data passed to the function
7812  edit_state.Text.resize(buf_size+1);
7813  const char* buf_end = NULL;
7814  edit_state.CurLenW = ImTextStrFromUtf8(edit_state.Text.Data, edit_state.Text.Size, buf, NULL, &buf_end);
7815  edit_state.CurLenA = (int)(buf_end - buf);
7816  edit_state.CursorClamp();
7817  }
7818 
7819  edit_state.BufSizeA = buf_size;
7820 
7821  // Although we are active we don't prevent mouse from hovering other elements unless we are interacting right now with the widget.
7822  // Down the line we should have a cleaner library-wide concept of Selected vs Active.
7823  g.ActiveIdAllowOverlap = !io.MouseDown[0];
7824 
7825  // Edit in progress
7826  const float mouse_x = (io.MousePos.x - frame_bb.Min.x - style.FramePadding.x) + edit_state.ScrollX;
7827  const float mouse_y = (is_multiline ? (io.MousePos.y - draw_window->DC.CursorPos.y - style.FramePadding.y) : (g.FontSize*0.5f));
7828 
7829  const bool osx_double_click_selects_words = io.OSXBehaviors; // OS X style: Double click selects by word instead of selecting whole text
7830  if (select_all || (hovered && !osx_double_click_selects_words && io.MouseDoubleClicked[0]))
7831  {
7832  edit_state.SelectAll();
7833  edit_state.SelectedAllMouseLock = true;
7834  }
7835  else if (hovered && osx_double_click_selects_words && io.MouseDoubleClicked[0])
7836  {
7837  // Select a word only, OS X style (by simulating keystrokes)
7838  edit_state.OnKeyPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_WORDLEFT);
7839  edit_state.OnKeyPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_WORDRIGHT | STB_TEXTEDIT_K_SHIFT);
7840  }
7841  else if (io.MouseClicked[0] && !edit_state.SelectedAllMouseLock)
7842  {
7843  stb_textedit_click(&edit_state, &edit_state.StbState, mouse_x, mouse_y);
7844  edit_state.CursorAnimReset();
7845  }
7846  else if (io.MouseDown[0] && !edit_state.SelectedAllMouseLock && (io.MouseDelta.x != 0.0f || io.MouseDelta.y != 0.0f))
7847  {
7848  stb_textedit_drag(&edit_state, &edit_state.StbState, mouse_x, mouse_y);
7849  edit_state.CursorAnimReset();
7850  edit_state.CursorFollow = true;
7851  }
7852  if (edit_state.SelectedAllMouseLock && !io.MouseDown[0])
7853  edit_state.SelectedAllMouseLock = false;
7854 
7855  if (io.InputCharacters[0])
7856  {
7857  // Process text input (before we check for Return because using some IME will effectively send a Return?)
7858  // We ignore CTRL inputs, but need to allow CTRL+ALT as some keyboards (e.g. German) use AltGR - which is Alt+Ctrl - to input certain characters.
7859  if (!(io.KeyCtrl && !io.KeyAlt) && is_editable)
7860  {
7861  for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(io.InputCharacters) && io.InputCharacters[n]; n++)
7862  if (unsigned int c = (unsigned int)io.InputCharacters[n])
7863  {
7864  // Insert character if they pass filtering
7865  if (!InputTextFilterCharacter(&c, flags, callback, user_data))
7866  continue;
7867  edit_state.OnKeyPressed((int)c);
7868  }
7869  }
7870 
7871  // Consume characters
7872  memset(g.IO.InputCharacters, 0, sizeof(g.IO.InputCharacters));
7873  }
7874 
7875  // Handle various key-presses
7876  bool cancel_edit = false;
7877  const int k_mask = (io.KeyShift ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_SHIFT : 0);
7878  const bool is_shortcut_key_only = (io.OSXBehaviors ? (io.KeySuper && !io.KeyCtrl) : (io.KeyCtrl && !io.KeySuper)) && !io.KeyAlt && !io.KeyShift; // OS X style: Shortcuts using Cmd/Super instead of Ctrl
7879  const bool is_wordmove_key_down = io.OSXBehaviors ? io.KeyAlt : io.KeyCtrl; // OS X style: Text editing cursor movement using Alt instead of Ctrl
7880  const bool is_startend_key_down = io.OSXBehaviors && io.KeySuper && !io.KeyCtrl && !io.KeyAlt; // OS X style: Line/Text Start and End using Cmd+Arrows instead of Home/End
7881 
7882  if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_LeftArrow)) { edit_state.OnKeyPressed((is_startend_key_down ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LINESTART : is_wordmove_key_down ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_WORDLEFT : STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LEFT) | k_mask); }
7883  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_RightArrow)) { edit_state.OnKeyPressed((is_startend_key_down ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LINEEND : is_wordmove_key_down ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_WORDRIGHT : STB_TEXTEDIT_K_RIGHT) | k_mask); }
7884  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_UpArrow) && is_multiline) { if (io.KeyCtrl) SetWindowScrollY(draw_window, ImMax(draw_window->Scroll.y - g.FontSize, 0.0f)); else edit_state.OnKeyPressed((is_startend_key_down ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_TEXTSTART : STB_TEXTEDIT_K_UP) | k_mask); }
7885  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_DownArrow) && is_multiline) { if (io.KeyCtrl) SetWindowScrollY(draw_window, ImMin(draw_window->Scroll.y + g.FontSize, GetScrollMaxY())); else edit_state.OnKeyPressed((is_startend_key_down ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_TEXTEND : STB_TEXTEDIT_K_DOWN) | k_mask); }
7886  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Home)) { edit_state.OnKeyPressed(io.KeyCtrl ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_TEXTSTART | k_mask : STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LINESTART | k_mask); }
7887  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_End)) { edit_state.OnKeyPressed(io.KeyCtrl ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_TEXTEND | k_mask : STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LINEEND | k_mask); }
7888  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Delete) && is_editable) { edit_state.OnKeyPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_DELETE | k_mask); }
7889  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Backspace) && is_editable)
7890  {
7891  if (!edit_state.HasSelection())
7892  {
7893  if (is_wordmove_key_down) edit_state.OnKeyPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_WORDLEFT|STB_TEXTEDIT_K_SHIFT);
7894  else if (io.OSXBehaviors && io.KeySuper && !io.KeyAlt && !io.KeyCtrl) edit_state.OnKeyPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LINESTART|STB_TEXTEDIT_K_SHIFT);
7895  }
7896  edit_state.OnKeyPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_BACKSPACE | k_mask);
7897  }
7898  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Enter))
7899  {
7900  bool ctrl_enter_for_new_line = (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CtrlEnterForNewLine) != 0;
7901  if (!is_multiline || (ctrl_enter_for_new_line && !io.KeyCtrl) || (!ctrl_enter_for_new_line && io.KeyCtrl))
7902  {
7903  ClearActiveID();
7904  enter_pressed = true;
7905  }
7906  else if (is_editable)
7907  {
7908  unsigned int c = '\n'; // Insert new line
7909  if (InputTextFilterCharacter(&c, flags, callback, user_data))
7910  edit_state.OnKeyPressed((int)c);
7911  }
7912  }
7913  else if ((flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_AllowTabInput) && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Tab) && !io.KeyCtrl && !io.KeyShift && !io.KeyAlt && is_editable)
7914  {
7915  unsigned int c = '\t'; // Insert TAB
7916  if (InputTextFilterCharacter(&c, flags, callback, user_data))
7917  edit_state.OnKeyPressed((int)c);
7918  }
7919  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Escape)) { ClearActiveID(); cancel_edit = true; }
7920  else if (is_shortcut_key_only && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Z) && is_editable) { edit_state.OnKeyPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_UNDO); edit_state.ClearSelection(); }
7921  else if (is_shortcut_key_only && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Y) && is_editable) { edit_state.OnKeyPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_REDO); edit_state.ClearSelection(); }
7922  else if (is_shortcut_key_only && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_A)) { edit_state.SelectAll(); edit_state.CursorFollow = true; }
7923  else if (is_shortcut_key_only && !is_password && ((IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_X) && is_editable) || IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_C)) && (!is_multiline || edit_state.HasSelection()))
7924  {
7925  // Cut, Copy
7926  const bool cut = IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_X);
7927  if (cut && !edit_state.HasSelection())
7928  edit_state.SelectAll();
7929 
7930  if (io.SetClipboardTextFn)
7931  {
7932  const int ib = edit_state.HasSelection() ? ImMin(edit_state.StbState.select_start, edit_state.StbState.select_end) : 0;
7933  const int ie = edit_state.HasSelection() ? ImMax(edit_state.StbState.select_start, edit_state.StbState.select_end) : edit_state.CurLenW;
7934  edit_state.TempTextBuffer.resize((ie-ib) * 4 + 1);
7935  ImTextStrToUtf8(edit_state.TempTextBuffer.Data, edit_state.TempTextBuffer.Size, edit_state.Text.Data+ib, edit_state.Text.Data+ie);
7936  SetClipboardText(edit_state.TempTextBuffer.Data);
7937  }
7938 
7939  if (cut)
7940  {
7941  edit_state.CursorFollow = true;
7942  stb_textedit_cut(&edit_state, &edit_state.StbState);
7943  }
7944  }
7945  else if (is_shortcut_key_only && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_V) && is_editable)
7946  {
7947  // Paste
7948  if (const char* clipboard = GetClipboardText())
7949  {
7950  // Filter pasted buffer
7951  const int clipboard_len = (int)strlen(clipboard);
7952  ImWchar* clipboard_filtered = (ImWchar*)ImGui::MemAlloc((clipboard_len+1) * sizeof(ImWchar));
7953  int clipboard_filtered_len = 0;
7954  for (const char* s = clipboard; *s; )
7955  {
7956  unsigned int c;
7957  s += ImTextCharFromUtf8(&c, s, NULL);
7958  if (c == 0)
7959  break;
7960  if (c >= 0x10000 || !InputTextFilterCharacter(&c, flags, callback, user_data))
7961  continue;
7962  clipboard_filtered[clipboard_filtered_len++] = (ImWchar)c;
7963  }
7964  clipboard_filtered[clipboard_filtered_len] = 0;
7965  if (clipboard_filtered_len > 0) // If everything was filtered, ignore the pasting operation
7966  {
7967  stb_textedit_paste(&edit_state, &edit_state.StbState, clipboard_filtered, clipboard_filtered_len);
7968  edit_state.CursorFollow = true;
7969  }
7970  ImGui::MemFree(clipboard_filtered);
7971  }
7972  }
7973 
7974  if (cancel_edit)
7975  {
7976  // Restore initial value
7977  if (is_editable)
7978  {
7979  ImStrncpy(buf, edit_state.InitialText.Data, buf_size);
7980  value_changed = true;
7981  }
7982  }
7983  else
7984  {
7985  // Apply new value immediately - copy modified buffer back
7986  // Note that as soon as the input box is active, the in-widget value gets priority over any underlying modification of the input buffer
7987  // FIXME: We actually always render 'buf' when calling DrawList->AddText, making the comment above incorrect.
7988  // FIXME-OPT: CPU waste to do this every time the widget is active, should mark dirty state from the stb_textedit callbacks.
7989  if (is_editable)
7990  {
7991  edit_state.TempTextBuffer.resize(edit_state.Text.Size * 4);
7992  ImTextStrToUtf8(edit_state.TempTextBuffer.Data, edit_state.TempTextBuffer.Size, edit_state.Text.Data, NULL);
7993  }
7994 
7995  // User callback
7996  if ((flags & (ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackCompletion | ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackHistory | ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackAlways)) != 0)
7997  {
7998  IM_ASSERT(callback != NULL);
7999 
8000  // The reason we specify the usage semantic (Completion/History) is that Completion needs to disable keyboard TABBING at the moment.
8001  ImGuiInputTextFlags event_flag = 0;
8002  ImGuiKey event_key = ImGuiKey_COUNT;
8003  if ((flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackCompletion) != 0 && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Tab))
8004  {
8005  event_flag = ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackCompletion;
8006  event_key = ImGuiKey_Tab;
8007  }
8008  else if ((flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackHistory) != 0 && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_UpArrow))
8009  {
8010  event_flag = ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackHistory;
8011  event_key = ImGuiKey_UpArrow;
8012  }
8013  else if ((flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackHistory) != 0 && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_DownArrow))
8014  {
8015  event_flag = ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackHistory;
8016  event_key = ImGuiKey_DownArrow;
8017  }
8018  else if (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackAlways)
8019  event_flag = ImGuiInputTextFlags_CallbackAlways;
8020 
8021  if (event_flag)
8022  {
8023  ImGuiTextEditCallbackData callback_data;
8024  memset(&callback_data, 0, sizeof(ImGuiTextEditCallbackData));
8025  callback_data.EventFlag = event_flag;
8026  callback_data.Flags = flags;
8027  callback_data.UserData = user_data;
8028  callback_data.ReadOnly = !is_editable;
8029 
8030  callback_data.EventKey = event_key;
8031  callback_data.Buf = edit_state.TempTextBuffer.Data;
8032  callback_data.BufTextLen = edit_state.CurLenA;
8033  callback_data.BufSize = edit_state.BufSizeA;
8034  callback_data.BufDirty = false;
8035 
8036  // We have to convert from wchar-positions to UTF-8-positions, which can be pretty slow (an incentive to ditch the ImWchar buffer, see https://github.com/nothings/stb/issues/188)
8037  ImWchar* text = edit_state.Text.Data;
8038  const int utf8_cursor_pos = callback_data.CursorPos = ImTextCountUtf8BytesFromStr(text, text + edit_state.StbState.cursor);
8039  const int utf8_selection_start = callback_data.SelectionStart = ImTextCountUtf8BytesFromStr(text, text + edit_state.StbState.select_start);
8040  const int utf8_selection_end = callback_data.SelectionEnd = ImTextCountUtf8BytesFromStr(text, text + edit_state.StbState.select_end);
8041 
8042  // Call user code
8043  callback(&callback_data);
8044 
8045  // Read back what user may have modified
8046  IM_ASSERT(callback_data.Buf == edit_state.TempTextBuffer.Data); // Invalid to modify those fields
8047  IM_ASSERT(callback_data.BufSize == edit_state.BufSizeA);
8048  IM_ASSERT(callback_data.Flags == flags);
8049  if (callback_data.CursorPos != utf8_cursor_pos) edit_state.StbState.cursor = ImTextCountCharsFromUtf8(callback_data.Buf, callback_data.Buf + callback_data.CursorPos);
8050  if (callback_data.SelectionStart != utf8_selection_start) edit_state.StbState.select_start = ImTextCountCharsFromUtf8(callback_data.Buf, callback_data.Buf + callback_data.SelectionStart);
8051  if (callback_data.SelectionEnd != utf8_selection_end) edit_state.StbState.select_end = ImTextCountCharsFromUtf8(callback_data.Buf, callback_data.Buf + callback_data.SelectionEnd);
8052  if (callback_data.BufDirty)
8053  {
8054  IM_ASSERT(callback_data.BufTextLen == (int)strlen(callback_data.Buf)); // You need to maintain BufTextLen if you change the text!
8055  edit_state.CurLenW = ImTextStrFromUtf8(edit_state.Text.Data, edit_state.Text.Size, callback_data.Buf, NULL);
8056  edit_state.CurLenA = callback_data.BufTextLen; // Assume correct length and valid UTF-8 from user, saves us an extra strlen()
8057  edit_state.CursorAnimReset();
8058  }
8059  }
8060  }
8061 
8062  // Copy back to user buffer
8063  if (is_editable && strcmp(edit_state.TempTextBuffer.Data, buf) != 0)
8064  {
8065  ImStrncpy(buf, edit_state.TempTextBuffer.Data, buf_size);
8066  value_changed = true;
8067  }
8068  }
8069  }
8070 
8071  // Render
8072  // Select which buffer we are going to display. When ImGuiInputTextFlags_NoLiveEdit is set 'buf' might still be the old value. We set buf to NULL to prevent accidental usage from now on.
8073  const char* buf_display = (g.ActiveId == id && is_editable) ? edit_state.TempTextBuffer.Data : buf; buf = NULL;
8074 
8075  if (!is_multiline)
8076  RenderFrame(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_FrameBg), true, style.FrameRounding);
8077 
8078  const ImVec4 clip_rect(frame_bb.Min.x, frame_bb.Min.y, frame_bb.Min.x + size.x, frame_bb.Min.y + size.y); // Not using frame_bb.Max because we have adjusted size
8079  ImVec2 render_pos = is_multiline ? draw_window->DC.CursorPos : frame_bb.Min + style.FramePadding;
8080  ImVec2 text_size(0.f, 0.f);
8081  const bool is_currently_scrolling = (edit_state.Id == id && is_multiline && g.ActiveId == draw_window->GetIDNoKeepAlive("#SCROLLY"));
8082  if (g.ActiveId == id || is_currently_scrolling)
8083  {
8084  edit_state.CursorAnim += io.DeltaTime;
8085 
8086  // This is going to be messy. We need to:
8087  // - Display the text (this alone can be more easily clipped)
8088  // - Handle scrolling, highlight selection, display cursor (those all requires some form of 1d->2d cursor position calculation)
8089  // - Measure text height (for scrollbar)
8090  // We are attempting to do most of that in **one main pass** to minimize the computation cost (non-negligible for large amount of text) + 2nd pass for selection rendering (we could merge them by an extra refactoring effort)
8091  // FIXME: This should occur on buf_display but we'd need to maintain cursor/select_start/select_end for UTF-8.
8092  const ImWchar* text_begin = edit_state.Text.Data;
8093  ImVec2 cursor_offset, select_start_offset;
8094 
8095  {
8096  // Count lines + find lines numbers straddling 'cursor' and 'select_start' position.
8097  const ImWchar* searches_input_ptr[2];
8098  searches_input_ptr[0] = text_begin + edit_state.StbState.cursor;
8099  searches_input_ptr[1] = NULL;
8100  int searches_remaining = 1;
8101  int searches_result_line_number[2] = { -1, -999 };
8102  if (edit_state.StbState.select_start != edit_state.StbState.select_end)
8103  {
8104  searches_input_ptr[1] = text_begin + ImMin(edit_state.StbState.select_start, edit_state.StbState.select_end);
8105  searches_result_line_number[1] = -1;
8106  searches_remaining++;
8107  }
8108 
8109  // Iterate all lines to find our line numbers
8110  // In multi-line mode, we never exit the loop until all lines are counted, so add one extra to the searches_remaining counter.
8111  searches_remaining += is_multiline ? 1 : 0;
8112  int line_count = 0;
8113  for (const ImWchar* s = text_begin; *s != 0; s++)
8114  if (*s == '\n')
8115  {
8116  line_count++;
8117  if (searches_result_line_number[0] == -1 && s >= searches_input_ptr[0]) { searches_result_line_number[0] = line_count; if (--searches_remaining <= 0) break; }
8118  if (searches_result_line_number[1] == -1 && s >= searches_input_ptr[1]) { searches_result_line_number[1] = line_count; if (--searches_remaining <= 0) break; }
8119  }
8120  line_count++;
8121  if (searches_result_line_number[0] == -1) searches_result_line_number[0] = line_count;
8122  if (searches_result_line_number[1] == -1) searches_result_line_number[1] = line_count;
8123 
8124  // Calculate 2d position by finding the beginning of the line and measuring distance
8125  cursor_offset.x = InputTextCalcTextSizeW(ImStrbolW(searches_input_ptr[0], text_begin), searches_input_ptr[0]).x;
8126  cursor_offset.y = searches_result_line_number[0] * g.FontSize;
8127  if (searches_result_line_number[1] >= 0)
8128  {
8129  select_start_offset.x = InputTextCalcTextSizeW(ImStrbolW(searches_input_ptr[1], text_begin), searches_input_ptr[1]).x;
8130  select_start_offset.y = searches_result_line_number[1] * g.FontSize;
8131  }
8132 
8133  // Calculate text height
8134  if (is_multiline)
8135  text_size = ImVec2(size.x, line_count * g.FontSize);
8136  }
8137 
8138  // Scroll
8139  if (edit_state.CursorFollow)
8140  {
8141  // Horizontal scroll in chunks of quarter width
8142  if (!(flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_NoHorizontalScroll))
8143  {
8144  const float scroll_increment_x = size.x * 0.25f;
8145  if (cursor_offset.x < edit_state.ScrollX)
8146  edit_state.ScrollX = (float)(int)ImMax(0.0f, cursor_offset.x - scroll_increment_x);
8147  else if (cursor_offset.x - size.x >= edit_state.ScrollX)
8148  edit_state.ScrollX = (float)(int)(cursor_offset.x - size.x + scroll_increment_x);
8149  }
8150  else
8151  {
8152  edit_state.ScrollX = 0.0f;
8153  }
8154 
8155  // Vertical scroll
8156  if (is_multiline)
8157  {
8158  float scroll_y = draw_window->Scroll.y;
8159  if (cursor_offset.y - g.FontSize < scroll_y)
8160  scroll_y = ImMax(0.0f, cursor_offset.y - g.FontSize);
8161  else if (cursor_offset.y - size.y >= scroll_y)
8162  scroll_y = cursor_offset.y - size.y;
8163  draw_window->DC.CursorPos.y += (draw_window->Scroll.y - scroll_y); // To avoid a frame of lag
8164  draw_window->Scroll.y = scroll_y;
8165  render_pos.y = draw_window->DC.CursorPos.y;
8166  }
8167  }
8168  edit_state.CursorFollow = false;
8169  const ImVec2 render_scroll = ImVec2(edit_state.ScrollX, 0.0f);
8170 
8171  // Draw selection
8172  if (edit_state.StbState.select_start != edit_state.StbState.select_end)
8173  {
8174  const ImWchar* text_selected_begin = text_begin + ImMin(edit_state.StbState.select_start, edit_state.StbState.select_end);
8175  const ImWchar* text_selected_end = text_begin + ImMax(edit_state.StbState.select_start, edit_state.StbState.select_end);
8176 
8177  float bg_offy_up = is_multiline ? 0.0f : -1.0f; // FIXME: those offsets should be part of the style? they don't play so well with multi-line selection.
8178  float bg_offy_dn = is_multiline ? 0.0f : 2.0f;
8179  ImU32 bg_color = GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_TextSelectedBg);
8180  ImVec2 rect_pos = render_pos + select_start_offset - render_scroll;
8181  for (const ImWchar* p = text_selected_begin; p < text_selected_end; )
8182  {
8183  if (rect_pos.y > clip_rect.w + g.FontSize)
8184  break;
8185  if (rect_pos.y < clip_rect.y)
8186  {
8187  while (p < text_selected_end)
8188  if (*p++ == '\n')
8189  break;
8190  }
8191  else
8192  {
8193  ImVec2 rect_size = InputTextCalcTextSizeW(p, text_selected_end, &p, NULL, true);
8194  if (rect_size.x <= 0.0f) rect_size.x = (float)(int)(g.Font->GetCharAdvance((unsigned short)' ') * 0.50f); // So we can see selected empty lines
8195  ImRect rect(rect_pos + ImVec2(0.0f, bg_offy_up - g.FontSize), rect_pos +ImVec2(rect_size.x, bg_offy_dn));
8196  rect.Clip(clip_rect);
8197  if (rect.Overlaps(clip_rect))
8198  draw_window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(rect.Min, rect.Max, bg_color);
8199  }
8200  rect_pos.x = render_pos.x - render_scroll.x;
8201  rect_pos.y += g.FontSize;
8202  }
8203  }
8204 
8205  draw_window->DrawList->AddText(g.Font, g.FontSize, render_pos - render_scroll, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Text), buf_display, buf_display + edit_state.CurLenA, 0.0f, is_multiline ? NULL : &clip_rect);
8206 
8207  // Draw blinking cursor
8208  bool cursor_is_visible = (g.InputTextState.CursorAnim <= 0.0f) || fmodf(g.InputTextState.CursorAnim, 1.20f) <= 0.80f;
8209  ImVec2 cursor_screen_pos = render_pos + cursor_offset - render_scroll;
8210  ImRect cursor_screen_rect(cursor_screen_pos.x, cursor_screen_pos.y-g.FontSize+0.5f, cursor_screen_pos.x+1.0f, cursor_screen_pos.y-1.5f);
8211  if (cursor_is_visible && cursor_screen_rect.Overlaps(clip_rect))
8212  draw_window->DrawList->AddLine(cursor_screen_rect.Min, cursor_screen_rect.GetBL(), GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Text));
8213 
8214  // Notify OS of text input position for advanced IME (-1 x offset so that Windows IME can cover our cursor. Bit of an extra nicety.)
8215  if (is_editable)
8216  g.OsImePosRequest = ImVec2(cursor_screen_pos.x - 1, cursor_screen_pos.y - g.FontSize);
8217  }
8218  else
8219  {
8220  // Render text only
8221  const char* buf_end = NULL;
8222  if (is_multiline)
8223  text_size = ImVec2(size.x, InputTextCalcTextLenAndLineCount(buf_display, &buf_end) * g.FontSize); // We don't need width
8224  draw_window->DrawList->AddText(g.Font, g.FontSize, render_pos, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Text), buf_display, buf_end, 0.0f, is_multiline ? NULL : &clip_rect);
8225  }
8226 
8227  if (is_multiline)
8228  {
8229  Dummy(text_size + ImVec2(0.0f, g.FontSize)); // Always add room to scroll an extra line
8230  EndChildFrame();
8231  EndGroup();
8232  }
8233 
8234  if (is_password)
8235  PopFont();
8236 
8237  // Log as text
8238  if (g.LogEnabled && !is_password)
8239  LogRenderedText(render_pos, buf_display, NULL);
8240 
8241  if (label_size.x > 0)
8242  RenderText(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, frame_bb.Min.y + style.FramePadding.y), label);
8243 
8244  if ((flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_EnterReturnsTrue) != 0)
8245  return enter_pressed;
8246  else
8247  return value_changed;
8248 }
8249

8251 {
8252  IM_ASSERT(!(flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_Multiline)); // call InputTextMultiline()

8254 }

8261 // NB: scalar_format here must be a simple "%xx" format string with no prefix/suffix (unlike the Drag/Slider functions "display_format" argument)
8262 bool ImGui::InputScalarEx(const char* label, ImGuiDataType data_type, void* data_ptr, void* step_ptr, void* step_fast_ptr, const char* scalar_format, ImGuiInputTextFlags extra_flags)
8263 {
8264  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
8265  if (window->SkipItems)
8266  return false;
8267 
8268  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
8269  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
8270  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
8271 
8272  BeginGroup();
8273  PushID(label);
8274  const ImVec2 button_sz = ImVec2(g.FontSize, g.FontSize) + style.FramePadding*2.0f;
8275  if (step_ptr)
8276  PushItemWidth(ImMax(1.0f, CalcItemWidth() - (button_sz.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x)*2));
8277 
8278  char buf[64];
8279  DataTypeFormatString(data_type, data_ptr, scalar_format, buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(buf));
8280 
8281  bool value_changed = false;
8282  if (!(extra_flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsHexadecimal))
8283  extra_flags |= ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsDecimal;
8284  extra_flags |= ImGuiInputTextFlags_AutoSelectAll;
8285  if (InputText("", buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(buf), extra_flags)) // PushId(label) + "" gives us the expected ID from outside point of view
8286  value_changed = DataTypeApplyOpFromText(buf, GImGui->InputTextState.InitialText.begin(), data_type, data_ptr, scalar_format);
8287 
8288  // Step buttons
8289  if (step_ptr)
8290  {
8291  PopItemWidth();
8292  SameLine(0, style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
8293  if (ButtonEx("-", button_sz, ImGuiButtonFlags_Repeat | ImGuiButtonFlags_DontClosePopups))
8294  {
8295  DataTypeApplyOp(data_type, '-', data_ptr, g.IO.KeyCtrl && step_fast_ptr ? step_fast_ptr : step_ptr);
8296  value_changed = true;
8297  }
8298  SameLine(0, style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
8299  if (ButtonEx("+", button_sz, ImGuiButtonFlags_Repeat | ImGuiButtonFlags_DontClosePopups))
8300  {
8301  DataTypeApplyOp(data_type, '+', data_ptr, g.IO.KeyCtrl && step_fast_ptr ? step_fast_ptr : step_ptr);
8302  value_changed = true;
8303  }
8304  }
8305  PopID();
8306 
8307  if (label_size.x > 0)
8308  {
8309  SameLine(0, style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
8310  RenderText(ImVec2(window->DC.CursorPos.x, window->DC.CursorPos.y + style.FramePadding.y), label);
8311  ItemSize(label_size, style.FramePadding.y);
8312  }
8313  EndGroup();
8314 
8315  return value_changed;
8316 }

8318 bool ImGui::InputFloat(const char* label, float* v, float step, float step_fast, int decimal_precision, ImGuiInputTextFlags extra_flags)
8319 {
8320  char display_format[16];
8321  if (decimal_precision < 0)
8322  strcpy(display_format, "%f"); // Ideally we'd have a minimum decimal precision of 1 to visually denote that this is a float, while hiding non-significant digits? %f doesn't have a minimum of 1
8323  else
8324  ImFormatString(display_format, IM_ARRAYSIZE(display_format), "%%.%df", decimal_precision);
8325  return InputScalarEx(label, ImGuiDataType_Float, (void*)v, (void*)(step>0.0f ? &step : NULL), (void*)(step_fast>0.0f ? &step_fast : NULL), display_format, extra_flags);
8326 }

8328 bool ImGui::InputInt(const char* label, int* v, int step, int step_fast, ImGuiInputTextFlags extra_flags)
8329 {
8330  // Hexadecimal input provided as a convenience but the flag name is awkward. Typically you'd use InputText() to parse your own data, if you want to handle prefixes.
8331  const char* scalar_format = (extra_flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsHexadecimal) ? "%08X" : "%d";
8332  return InputScalarEx(label, ImGuiDataType_Int, (void*)v, (void*)(step>0.0f ? &step : NULL), (void*)(step_fast>0.0f ? &step_fast : NULL), scalar_format, extra_flags);
8333 }

8361 }

8421 static bool Items_ArrayGetter(void* data, int idx, const char** out_text)
8422 {
8423  const char* const* items = (const char* const*)data;
8424  if (out_text)
8425  *out_text = items[idx];
8426  return true;
8427 }
8428 
8429 static bool Items_SingleStringGetter(void* data, int idx, const char** out_text)
8430 {
8431  // FIXME-OPT: we could pre-compute the indices to fasten this. But only 1 active combo means the waste is limited.
8432  const char* items_separated_by_zeros = (const char*)data;
8433  int items_count = 0;
8434  const char* p = items_separated_by_zeros;
8435  while (*p)
8436  {
8437  if (idx == items_count)
8438  break;
8439  p += strlen(p) + 1;
8440  items_count++;
8441  }
8442  if (!*p)
8443  return false;
8444  if (out_text)
8445  *out_text = p;
8446  return true;
8447 }

8449 // Combo box helper allowing to pass an array of strings.
8450 bool ImGui::Combo(const char* label, int* current_item, const char* const* items, int items_count, int height_in_items)
8451 {
8452  const bool value_changed = Combo(label, current_item, Items_ArrayGetter, (void*)items, items_count, height_in_items);
8453  return value_changed;
8454 }
8455 
8456 // Combo box helper allowing to pass all items in a single string.
8457 bool ImGui::Combo(const char* label, int* current_item, const char* items_separated_by_zeros, int height_in_items)
8458 {
8459  int items_count = 0;
8460  const char* p = items_separated_by_zeros; // FIXME-OPT: Avoid computing this, or at least only when combo is open
8461  while (*p)
8462  {
8463  p += strlen(p) + 1;
8464  items_count++;
8465  }
8466  bool value_changed = Combo(label, current_item, Items_SingleStringGetter, (void*)items_separated_by_zeros, items_count, height_in_items);
8467  return value_changed;
8468 }
8469 
8470 // Combo box function.
8471 bool ImGui::Combo(const char* label, int* current_item, bool (*items_getter)(void*, int, const char**), void* data, int items_count, int height_in_items)
8472 {
8473  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
8474  if (window->SkipItems)
8475  return false;
8476 
8477  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
8478  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
8479  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
8480  const float w = CalcItemWidth();
8481 
8482  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
8483  const ImRect frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(w, label_size.y + style.FramePadding.y*2.0f));
8484  const ImRect total_bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max + ImVec2(label_size.x > 0.0f ? style.ItemInnerSpacing.x + label_size.x : 0.0f, 0.0f));
8485  ItemSize(total_bb, style.FramePadding.y);
8486  if (!ItemAdd(total_bb, &id))
8487  return false;
8488 
8489  const float arrow_size = (g.FontSize + style.FramePadding.x * 2.0f);
8490  const bool hovered = IsHovered(frame_bb, id);
8491  bool popup_open = IsPopupOpen(id);
8492  bool popup_opened_now = false;
8493 
8494  const ImRect value_bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max - ImVec2(arrow_size, 0.0f));
8495  RenderFrame(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max, GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_FrameBg), true, style.FrameRounding);
8496  RenderFrame(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x-arrow_size, frame_bb.Min.y), frame_bb.Max, GetColorU32(popup_open || hovered ? ImGuiCol_ButtonHovered : ImGuiCol_Button), true, style.FrameRounding); // FIXME-ROUNDING
8497  RenderCollapseTriangle(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x-arrow_size, frame_bb.Min.y) + style.FramePadding, true);
8498 
8499  if (*current_item >= 0 && *current_item < items_count)
8500  {
8501  const char* item_text;
8502  if (items_getter(data, *current_item, &item_text))
8503  RenderTextClipped(frame_bb.Min + style.FramePadding, value_bb.Max, item_text, NULL, NULL, ImVec2(0.0f,0.0f));
8504  }
8505 
8506  if (label_size.x > 0)
8507  RenderText(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, frame_bb.Min.y + style.FramePadding.y), label);
8508 
8509  if (hovered)
8510  {
8511  SetHoveredID(id);
8512  if (g.IO.MouseClicked[0])
8513  {
8514  ClearActiveID();
8515  if (IsPopupOpen(id))
8516  {
8517  ClosePopup(id);
8518  }
8519  else
8520  {
8521  FocusWindow(window);
8522  OpenPopup(label);
8523  popup_open = popup_opened_now = true;
8524  }
8525  }
8526  }
8527 
8528  bool value_changed = false;
8529  if (IsPopupOpen(id))
8530  {
8531  // Size default to hold ~7 items
8532  if (height_in_items < 0)
8533  height_in_items = 7;
8534 
8535  float popup_height = (label_size.y + style.ItemSpacing.y) * ImMin(items_count, height_in_items) + (style.FramePadding.y * 3);
8536  float popup_y1 = frame_bb.Max.y;
8537  float popup_y2 = ImClamp(popup_y1 + popup_height, popup_y1, g.IO.DisplaySize.y - style.DisplaySafeAreaPadding.y);
8538  if ((popup_y2 - popup_y1) < ImMin(popup_height, frame_bb.Min.y - style.DisplaySafeAreaPadding.y))
8539  {
8540  // Position our combo ABOVE because there's more space to fit! (FIXME: Handle in Begin() or use a shared helper. We have similar code in Begin() for popup placement)
8541  popup_y1 = ImClamp(frame_bb.Min.y - popup_height, style.DisplaySafeAreaPadding.y, frame_bb.Min.y);
8542  popup_y2 = frame_bb.Min.y;
8543  }
8544  ImRect popup_rect(ImVec2(frame_bb.Min.x, popup_y1), ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x, popup_y2));
8545  SetNextWindowPos(popup_rect.Min);
8546  SetNextWindowSize(popup_rect.GetSize());
8547  PushStyleVar(ImGuiStyleVar_WindowPadding, style.FramePadding);
8548 
8549  const ImGuiWindowFlags flags = ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox | ((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders) ? ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders : 0);
8550  if (BeginPopupEx(label, flags))
8551  {
8552  // Display items
8553  Spacing();
8554  for (int i = 0; i < items_count; i++)
8555  {
8556  PushID((void*)(intptr_t)i);
8557  const bool item_selected = (i == *current_item);
8558  const char* item_text;
8559  if (!items_getter(data, i, &item_text))
8560  item_text = "*Unknown item*";
8561  if (Selectable(item_text, item_selected))
8562  {
8563  ClearActiveID();
8564  value_changed = true;
8565  *current_item = i;
8566  }
8567  if (item_selected && popup_opened_now)
8568  SetScrollHere();
8569  PopID();
8570  }
8571  EndPopup();
8572  }
8573  PopStyleVar();
8574  }
8575  return value_changed;
8576 }
8577 
8578 // Tip: pass an empty label (e.g. "##dummy") then you can use the space to draw other text or image.
8579 // But you need to make sure the ID is unique, e.g. enclose calls in PushID/PopID.
8580 bool ImGui::Selectable(const char* label, bool selected, ImGuiSelectableFlags flags, const ImVec2& size_arg)
8581 {
8582  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
8583  if (window->SkipItems)
8584  return false;
8585 
8586  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
8587  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
8588 
8589  if ((flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_SpanAllColumns) && window->DC.ColumnsCount > 1)
8590  PopClipRect();
8591 
8592  ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
8593  ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
8594  ImVec2 size(size_arg.x != 0.0f ? size_arg.x : label_size.x, size_arg.y != 0.0f ? size_arg.y : label_size.y);
8595  ImVec2 pos = window->DC.CursorPos;
8596  pos.y += window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset;
8597  ImRect bb(pos, pos + size);
8598  ItemSize(bb);
8599 
8600  // Fill horizontal space.
8601  ImVec2 window_padding = window->WindowPadding;
8602  float max_x = (flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_SpanAllColumns) ? GetWindowContentRegionMax().x : GetContentRegionMax().x;
8603  float w_draw = ImMax(label_size.x, window->Pos.x + max_x - window_padding.x - window->DC.CursorPos.x);
8604  ImVec2 size_draw((size_arg.x != 0 && !(flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_DrawFillAvailWidth)) ? size_arg.x : w_draw, size_arg.y != 0.0f ? size_arg.y : size.y);
8605  ImRect bb_with_spacing(pos, pos + size_draw);
8606  if (size_arg.x == 0.0f || (flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_DrawFillAvailWidth))
8607  bb_with_spacing.Max.x += window_padding.x;
8608 
8609  // Selectables are tightly packed together, we extend the box to cover spacing between selectable.
8610  float spacing_L = (float)(int)(style.ItemSpacing.x * 0.5f);
8611  float spacing_U = (float)(int)(style.ItemSpacing.y * 0.5f);
8612  float spacing_R = style.ItemSpacing.x - spacing_L;
8613  float spacing_D = style.ItemSpacing.y - spacing_U;
8614  bb_with_spacing.Min.x -= spacing_L;
8615  bb_with_spacing.Min.y -= spacing_U;
8616  bb_with_spacing.Max.x += spacing_R;
8617  bb_with_spacing.Max.y += spacing_D;
8618  if (!ItemAdd(bb_with_spacing, &id))
8619  {
8620  if ((flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_SpanAllColumns) && window->DC.ColumnsCount > 1)
8621  PushColumnClipRect();
8622  return false;
8623  }
8624 
8625  ImGuiButtonFlags button_flags = 0;
8626  if (flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_Menu) button_flags |= ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClick;
8627  if (flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_MenuItem) button_flags |= ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClick|ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnRelease;
8628  if (flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_Disabled) button_flags |= ImGuiButtonFlags_Disabled;
8629  if (flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_AllowDoubleClick) button_flags |= ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClickRelease | ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnDoubleClick;
8630  bool hovered, held;
8631  bool pressed = ButtonBehavior(bb_with_spacing, id, &hovered, &held, button_flags);
8632  if (flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_Disabled)
8633  selected = false;
8634 
8635  // Render
8636  if (hovered || selected)
8637  {
8638  const ImU32 col = GetColorU32((held && hovered) ? ImGuiCol_HeaderActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_HeaderHovered : ImGuiCol_Header);
8639  RenderFrame(bb_with_spacing.Min, bb_with_spacing.Max, col, false, 0.0f);
8640  }
8641 
8642  if ((flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_SpanAllColumns) && window->DC.ColumnsCount > 1)
8643  {
8644  PushColumnClipRect();
8645  bb_with_spacing.Max.x -= (GetContentRegionMax().x - max_x);
8646  }
8647 
8648  if (flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_Disabled) PushStyleColor(ImGuiCol_Text, g.Style.Colors[ImGuiCol_TextDisabled]);
8649  RenderTextClipped(bb.Min, bb_with_spacing.Max, label, NULL, &label_size, ImVec2(0.0f,0.0f));
8650  if (flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_Disabled) PopStyleColor();
8651 
8652  // Automatically close popups
8653  if (pressed && !(flags & ImGuiSelectableFlags_DontClosePopups) && (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup))
8654  CloseCurrentPopup();
8655  return pressed;
8656 }

8658 bool ImGui::Selectable(const char* label, bool* p_selected, ImGuiSelectableFlags flags, const ImVec2& size_arg)
8659 {
8660  if (Selectable(label, *p_selected, flags, size_arg))
8661  {
8662  *p_selected = !*p_selected;
8663  return true;
8664  }
8665  return false;
8666 }

8668 // Helper to calculate the size of a listbox and display a label on the right.
8669 // Tip: To have a list filling the entire window width, PushItemWidth(-1) and pass an empty label "##empty"
8670 bool ImGui::ListBoxHeader(const char* label, const ImVec2& size_arg)
8671 {
8672  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
8673  if (window->SkipItems)
8674  return false;
8675 
8676  const ImGuiStyle& style = GetStyle();
8677  const ImGuiID id = GetID(label);
8678  const ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
8679 
8680  // Size default to hold ~7 items. Fractional number of items helps seeing that we can scroll down/up without looking at scrollbar.
8681  ImVec2 size = CalcItemSize(size_arg, CalcItemWidth(), GetTextLineHeightWithSpacing() * 7.4f + style.ItemSpacing.y);
8682  ImVec2 frame_size = ImVec2(size.x, ImMax(size.y, label_size.y));
8683  ImRect frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + frame_size);
8684  ImRect bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max + ImVec2(label_size.x > 0.0f ? style.ItemInnerSpacing.x + label_size.x : 0.0f, 0.0f));
8685  window->DC.LastItemRect = bb;
8686 
8687  BeginGroup();
8688  if (label_size.x > 0)
8689  RenderText(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, frame_bb.Min.y + style.FramePadding.y), label);
8690 
8691  BeginChildFrame(id, frame_bb.GetSize());
8692  return true;
8693 }
8694 
8695 bool ImGui::ListBoxHeader(const char* label, int items_count, int height_in_items)
8696 {
8697  // Size default to hold ~7 items. Fractional number of items helps seeing that we can scroll down/up without looking at scrollbar.
8698  // However we don't add +0.40f if items_count <= height_in_items. It is slightly dodgy, because it means a dynamic list of items will make the widget resize occasionally when it crosses that size.
8699  // I am expecting that someone will come and complain about this behavior in a remote future, then we can advise on a better solution.
8700  if (height_in_items < 0)
8701  height_in_items = ImMin(items_count, 7);
8702  float height_in_items_f = height_in_items < items_count ? (height_in_items + 0.40f) : (height_in_items + 0.00f);
8703 
8704  // We include ItemSpacing.y so that a list sized for the exact number of items doesn't make a scrollbar appears. We could also enforce that by passing a flag to BeginChild().
8705  ImVec2 size;
8706  size.x = 0.0f;
8707  size.y = GetTextLineHeightWithSpacing() * height_in_items_f + GetStyle().ItemSpacing.y;
8708  return ListBoxHeader(label, size);
8709 }
8710 
8711 void ImGui::ListBoxFooter()
8712 {
8713  ImGuiWindow* parent_window = GetParentWindow();
8714  const ImRect bb = parent_window->DC.LastItemRect;
8715  const ImGuiStyle& style = GetStyle();
8716 
8717  EndChildFrame();
8718 
8719  // Redeclare item size so that it includes the label (we have stored the full size in LastItemRect)
8720  // We call SameLine() to restore DC.CurrentLine* data
8721  SameLine();
8722  parent_window->DC.CursorPos = bb.Min;
8723  ItemSize(bb, style.FramePadding.y);
8724  EndGroup();
8725 }

8732 
8733 bool ImGui::ListBox(const char* label, int* current_item, bool (*items_getter)(void*, int, const char**), void* data, int items_count, int height_in_items)
8734 {
8735  if (!ListBoxHeader(label, items_count, height_in_items))
8736  return false;
8737 
8738  // Assume all items have even height (= 1 line of text). If you need items of different or variable sizes you can create a custom version of ListBox() in your code without using the clipper.
8739  bool value_changed = false;
8740  ImGuiListClipper clipper(items_count, GetTextLineHeightWithSpacing());
8741  while (clipper.Step())
8742  for (int i = clipper.DisplayStart; i < clipper.DisplayEnd; i++)
8743  {
8744  const bool item_selected = (i == *current_item);
8745  const char* item_text;
8746  if (!items_getter(data, i, &item_text))
8747  item_text = "*Unknown item*";
8748 
8749  PushID(i);
8750  if (Selectable(item_text, item_selected))
8751  {
8752  *current_item = i;
8753  value_changed = true;
8754  }
8755  PopID();
8756  }
8757  ListBoxFooter();
8758  return value_changed;
8759 }

8772  float extra_w = ImMax(0.0f, GetContentRegionAvail().x - w);
8773

8779  PopStyleColor();
8780  }
8781 
8782  if (selected)
8783  RenderCheckMark(pos + ImVec2(window->MenuColumns.Pos[2] + extra_w + g.FontSize * 0.20f, 0.0f), GetColorU32(enabled ? ImGuiCol_Text : ImGuiCol_TextDisabled));
8784 
8785  return pressed;

8824 bool ImGui::BeginMenuBar()
8825 {
8826  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
8827  if (window->SkipItems)
8828  return false;
8829  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_MenuBar))
8830  return false;
8831 
8832  IM_ASSERT(!window->DC.MenuBarAppending);
8833  BeginGroup(); // Save position
8834  PushID("##menubar");
8835  ImRect rect = window->MenuBarRect();
8836  PushClipRect(ImVec2(ImFloor(rect.Min.x+0.5f), ImFloor(rect.Min.y + window->BorderSize + 0.5f)), ImVec2(ImFloor(rect.Max.x+0.5f), ImFloor(rect.Max.y+0.5f)), false);
8837  window->DC.CursorPos = ImVec2(rect.Min.x + window->DC.MenuBarOffsetX, rect.Min.y);// + g.Style.FramePadding.y);
8838  window->DC.LayoutType = ImGuiLayoutType_Horizontal;
8839  window->DC.MenuBarAppending = true;
8840  AlignFirstTextHeightToWidgets();
8841  return true;
8842 }

8844 void ImGui::EndMenuBar()
8845 {

8847  if (window->SkipItems)
8848  return;
8849

8851  IM_ASSERT(window->DC.MenuBarAppending);
8852  PopClipRect();
8853  PopID();
8854  window->DC.MenuBarOffsetX = window->DC.CursorPos.x - window->MenuBarRect().Min.x;
8855  window->DC.GroupStack.back().AdvanceCursor = false;
8856  EndGroup();
8857  window->DC.LayoutType = ImGuiLayoutType_Vertical;
8858  window->DC.MenuBarAppending = false;
8859 }
8860 
8861 bool ImGui::BeginMenu(const char* label, bool enabled)
8862 {
8863  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
8864  if (window->SkipItems)
8865  return false;
8866 
8867  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
8868  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
8869  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
8870 
8871  ImVec2 label_size = CalcTextSize(label, NULL, true);
8872  ImGuiWindow* backed_focused_window = g.FocusedWindow;
8873 
8874  bool pressed;
8875  bool menu_is_open = IsPopupOpen(id);
8876  bool menuset_is_open = !(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) && (g.OpenPopupStack.Size > g.CurrentPopupStack.Size && g.OpenPopupStack[g.CurrentPopupStack.Size].ParentMenuSet == window->GetID("##menus"));
8877  if (menuset_is_open)
8878  g.FocusedWindow = window;
8879 
8880  // The reference position stored in popup_pos will be used by Begin() to find a suitable position for the child menu (using FindBestPopupWindowPos).
8881  ImVec2 popup_pos, pos = window->DC.CursorPos;
8882  if (window->DC.LayoutType == ImGuiLayoutType_Horizontal)
8883  {
8884  popup_pos = ImVec2(pos.x - window->WindowPadding.x, pos.y - style.FramePadding.y + window->MenuBarHeight());
8885  window->DC.CursorPos.x += (float)(int)(style.ItemSpacing.x * 0.5f);
8886  PushStyleVar(ImGuiStyleVar_ItemSpacing, style.ItemSpacing * 2.0f);
8887  float w = label_size.x;
8888  pressed = Selectable(label, menu_is_open, ImGuiSelectableFlags_Menu | ImGuiSelectableFlags_DontClosePopups | (!enabled ? ImGuiSelectableFlags_Disabled : 0), ImVec2(w, 0.0f));
8889  PopStyleVar();
8890  SameLine();
8891  window->DC.CursorPos.x += (float)(int)(style.ItemSpacing.x * 0.5f);
8892  }
8893  else
8894  {
8895  popup_pos = ImVec2(pos.x, pos.y - style.WindowPadding.y);
8896  float w = window->MenuColumns.DeclColumns(label_size.x, 0.0f, (float)(int)(g.FontSize * 1.20f)); // Feedback to next frame
8897  float extra_w = ImMax(0.0f, GetContentRegionAvail().x - w);
8898  pressed = Selectable(label, menu_is_open, ImGuiSelectableFlags_Menu | ImGuiSelectableFlags_DontClosePopups | ImGuiSelectableFlags_DrawFillAvailWidth | (!enabled ? ImGuiSelectableFlags_Disabled : 0), ImVec2(w, 0.0f));
8899  if (!enabled) PushStyleColor(ImGuiCol_Text, g.Style.Colors[ImGuiCol_TextDisabled]);
8900  RenderCollapseTriangle(pos + ImVec2(window->MenuColumns.Pos[2] + extra_w + g.FontSize * 0.20f, 0.0f), false);
8901  if (!enabled) PopStyleColor();
8902  }
8903 
8904  bool hovered = enabled && IsHovered(window->DC.LastItemRect, id);
8905  if (menuset_is_open)
8906  g.FocusedWindow = backed_focused_window;
8907 
8908  bool want_open = false, want_close = false;
8909  if (window->Flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup|ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu))
8910  {
8911  // Implement http://bjk5.com/post/44698559168/breaking-down-amazons-mega-dropdown to avoid using timers, so menus feels more reactive.
8912  bool moving_within_opened_triangle = false;
8913  if (g.HoveredWindow == window && g.OpenPopupStack.Size > g.CurrentPopupStack.Size && g.OpenPopupStack[g.CurrentPopupStack.Size].ParentWindow == window)
8914  {
8915  if (ImGuiWindow* next_window = g.OpenPopupStack[g.CurrentPopupStack.Size].Window)
8916  {
8917  ImRect next_window_rect = next_window->Rect();
8918  ImVec2 ta = g.IO.MousePos - g.IO.MouseDelta;
8919  ImVec2 tb = (window->Pos.x < next_window->Pos.x) ? next_window_rect.GetTL() : next_window_rect.GetTR();
8920  ImVec2 tc = (window->Pos.x < next_window->Pos.x) ? next_window_rect.GetBL() : next_window_rect.GetBR();
8921  float extra = ImClamp(fabsf(ta.x - tb.x) * 0.30f, 5.0f, 30.0f); // add a bit of extra slack.
8922  ta.x += (window->Pos.x < next_window->Pos.x) ? -0.5f : +0.5f; // to avoid numerical issues
8923  tb.y = ta.y + ImMax((tb.y - extra) - ta.y, -100.0f); // triangle is maximum 200 high to limit the slope and the bias toward large sub-menus // FIXME: Multiply by fb_scale?
8924  tc.y = ta.y + ImMin((tc.y + extra) - ta.y, +100.0f);
8925  moving_within_opened_triangle = ImIsPointInTriangle(g.IO.MousePos, ta, tb, tc);
8926  //window->DrawList->PushClipRectFullScreen(); window->DrawList->AddTriangleFilled(ta, tb, tc, moving_within_opened_triangle ? IM_COL32(0,128,0,128) : IM_COL32(128,0,0,128)); window->DrawList->PopClipRect(); // Debug
8927  }
8928  }
8929 
8930  want_close = (menu_is_open && !hovered && g.HoveredWindow == window && g.HoveredIdPreviousFrame != 0 && g.HoveredIdPreviousFrame != id && !moving_within_opened_triangle);
8931  want_open = (!menu_is_open && hovered && !moving_within_opened_triangle) || (!menu_is_open && hovered && pressed);
8932  }
8933  else if (menu_is_open && pressed && menuset_is_open) // menu-bar: click open menu to close
8934  {
8935  want_close = true;
8936  want_open = menu_is_open = false;
8937  }
8938  else if (pressed || (hovered && menuset_is_open && !menu_is_open)) // menu-bar: first click to open, then hover to open others
8939  want_open = true;
8940  if (!enabled) // explicitly close if an open menu becomes disabled, facilitate users code a lot in pattern such as 'if (BeginMenu("options", has_object)) { ..use object.. }'
8941  want_close = true;
8942  if (want_close && IsPopupOpen(id))
8943  ClosePopupToLevel(GImGui->CurrentPopupStack.Size);
8944 
8945  if (!menu_is_open && want_open && g.OpenPopupStack.Size > g.CurrentPopupStack.Size)
8946  {
8947  // Don't recycle same menu level in the same frame, first close the other menu and yield for a frame.
8948  OpenPopup(label);
8949  return false;
8950  }
8951 
8952  menu_is_open |= want_open;
8953  if (want_open)
8954  OpenPopup(label);
8955 
8956  if (menu_is_open)
8957  {
8958  SetNextWindowPos(popup_pos, ImGuiSetCond_Always);
8959  ImGuiWindowFlags flags = ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders | ((window->Flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup|ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu)) ? ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu|ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow : ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu);
8960  menu_is_open = BeginPopupEx(label, flags); // menu_is_open can be 'false' when the popup is completely clipped (e.g. zero size display)
8961  }
8962 
8963  return menu_is_open;
8964 }
8965 
8966 void ImGui::EndMenu()
8967 {
8968  EndPopup();
8969 }
8970 
8971 // A little colored square. Return true when clicked.
8972 // FIXME: May want to display/ignore the alpha component in the color display? Yet show it in the tooltip.
8973 bool ImGui::ColorButton(const ImVec4& col, bool small_height, bool outline_border)
8974 {
8975  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
8976  if (window->SkipItems)
8977  return false;
8978 
8979  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
8980  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
8981  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID("#colorbutton");
8982  const float square_size = g.FontSize;
8983  const ImRect bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(square_size + style.FramePadding.y*2, square_size + (small_height ? 0 : style.FramePadding.y*2)));
8984  ItemSize(bb, small_height ? 0.0f : style.FramePadding.y);
8985  if (!ItemAdd(bb, &id))
8986  return false;
8987 
8988  bool hovered, held;
8989  bool pressed = ButtonBehavior(bb, id, &hovered, &held);
8990  RenderFrame(bb.Min, bb.Max, GetColorU32(col), outline_border, style.FrameRounding);
8991 
8992  if (hovered)
8993  SetTooltip("Color:\n(%.2f,%.2f,%.2f,%.2f)\n#%02X%02X%02X%02X", col.x, col.y, col.z, col.w, IM_F32_TO_INT8_SAT(col.x), IM_F32_TO_INT8_SAT(col.y), IM_F32_TO_INT8_SAT(col.z), IM_F32_TO_INT8_SAT(col.w));
8994 
8995  return pressed;
8996 }

8998 bool ImGui::ColorEdit3(const char* label, float col[3])

9007  col[1] = col4[1];
9008  col[2] = col4[2];

9012 // Edit colors components (each component in 0.0f..1.0f range
9013 // Use CTRL-Click to input value and TAB to go to next item.
9014 bool ImGui::ColorEdit4(const char* label, float col[4], bool alpha)
9015 {
9016  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
9017  if (window->SkipItems)
9018  return false;
9019 
9020  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
9021  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
9022  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
9023  const float w_full = CalcItemWidth();
9024  const float square_sz = (g.FontSize + style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f);
9025 
9026  ImGuiColorEditMode edit_mode = window->DC.ColorEditMode;
9027  if (edit_mode == ImGuiColorEditMode_UserSelect || edit_mode == ImGuiColorEditMode_UserSelectShowButton)
9028  edit_mode = g.ColorEditModeStorage.GetInt(id, 0) % 3;
9029 
9030  float f[4] = { col[0], col[1], col[2], col[3] };
9031  if (edit_mode == ImGuiColorEditMode_HSV)
9032  ColorConvertRGBtoHSV(f[0], f[1], f[2], f[0], f[1], f[2]);
9033 
9034  int i[4] = { IM_F32_TO_INT8_UNBOUND(f[0]), IM_F32_TO_INT8_UNBOUND(f[1]), IM_F32_TO_INT8_UNBOUND(f[2]), IM_F32_TO_INT8_UNBOUND(f[3]) };
9035 
9036  int components = alpha ? 4 : 3;
9037  bool value_changed = false;
9038 
9039  BeginGroup();
9040  PushID(label);
9041 
9042  const bool hsv = (edit_mode == 1);
9043  switch (edit_mode)
9044  {
9045  case ImGuiColorEditMode_RGB:
9046  case ImGuiColorEditMode_HSV:
9047  {
9048  // RGB/HSV 0..255 Sliders
9049  const float w_items_all = w_full - (square_sz + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
9050  const float w_item_one = ImMax(1.0f, (float)(int)((w_items_all - (style.ItemInnerSpacing.x) * (components-1)) / (float)components));
9051  const float w_item_last = ImMax(1.0f, (float)(int)(w_items_all - (w_item_one + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x) * (components-1)));
9052 
9053  const bool hide_prefix = (w_item_one <= CalcTextSize("M:999").x);
9054  const char* ids[4] = { "##X", "##Y", "##Z", "##W" };
9055  const char* fmt_table[3][4] =
9056  {
9057  { "%3.0f", "%3.0f", "%3.0f", "%3.0f" },
9058  { "R:%3.0f", "G:%3.0f", "B:%3.0f", "A:%3.0f" },
9059  { "H:%3.0f", "S:%3.0f", "V:%3.0f", "A:%3.0f" }
9060  };
9061  const char** fmt = hide_prefix ? fmt_table[0] : hsv ? fmt_table[2] : fmt_table[1];
9062 
9063  PushItemWidth(w_item_one);
9064  for (int n = 0; n < components; n++)
9065  {
9066  if (n > 0)
9067  SameLine(0, style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
9068  if (n + 1 == components)
9069  PushItemWidth(w_item_last);
9070  value_changed |= DragInt(ids[n], &i[n], 1.0f, 0, 255, fmt[n]);
9071  }
9072  PopItemWidth();
9073  PopItemWidth();
9074  }
9075  break;
9076  case ImGuiColorEditMode_HEX:
9077  {
9078  // RGB Hexadecimal Input
9079  const float w_slider_all = w_full - square_sz;
9080  char buf[64];
9081  if (alpha)
9082  ImFormatString(buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(buf), "#%02X%02X%02X%02X", i[0], i[1], i[2], i[3]);
9083  else
9084  ImFormatString(buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(buf), "#%02X%02X%02X", i[0], i[1], i[2]);
9085  PushItemWidth(w_slider_all - style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
9086  if (InputText("##Text", buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(buf), ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsHexadecimal | ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsUppercase))
9087  {
9088  value_changed |= true;
9089  char* p = buf;
9090  while (*p == '#' || ImCharIsSpace(*p))
9091  p++;
9092  i[0] = i[1] = i[2] = i[3] = 0;
9093  if (alpha)
9094  sscanf(p, "%02X%02X%02X%02X", (unsigned int*)&i[0], (unsigned int*)&i[1], (unsigned int*)&i[2], (unsigned int*)&i[3]); // Treat at unsigned (%X is unsigned)
9095  else
9096  sscanf(p, "%02X%02X%02X", (unsigned int*)&i[0], (unsigned int*)&i[1], (unsigned int*)&i[2]);
9097  }
9098  PopItemWidth();
9099  }
9100  break;
9101  }
9102 
9103  SameLine(0, style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
9104 
9105  const ImVec4 col_display(col[0], col[1], col[2], 1.0f);
9106  if (ColorButton(col_display))
9107  g.ColorEditModeStorage.SetInt(id, (edit_mode + 1) % 3); // Don't set local copy of 'edit_mode' right away!
9108 
9109  // Recreate our own tooltip over's ColorButton() one because we want to display correct alpha here
9110  if (IsItemHovered())
9111  SetTooltip("Color:\n(%.2f,%.2f,%.2f,%.2f)\n#%02X%02X%02X%02X", col[0], col[1], col[2], col[3], IM_F32_TO_INT8_SAT(col[0]), IM_F32_TO_INT8_SAT(col[1]), IM_F32_TO_INT8_SAT(col[2]), IM_F32_TO_INT8_SAT(col[3]));
9112 
9113  if (window->DC.ColorEditMode == ImGuiColorEditMode_UserSelectShowButton)
9114  {
9115  SameLine(0, style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
9116  const char* button_titles[3] = { "RGB", "HSV", "HEX" };
9117  if (ButtonEx(button_titles[edit_mode], ImVec2(0,0), ImGuiButtonFlags_DontClosePopups))
9118  g.ColorEditModeStorage.SetInt(id, (edit_mode + 1) % 3); // Don't set local copy of 'edit_mode' right away!
9119  }
9120 
9121  const char* label_display_end = FindRenderedTextEnd(label);
9122  if (label != label_display_end)
9123  {
9124  SameLine(0, (window->DC.ColorEditMode == ImGuiColorEditMode_UserSelectShowButton) ? -1.0f : style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
9125  TextUnformatted(label, label_display_end);
9126  }
9127 
9128  // Convert back
9129  for (int n = 0; n < 4; n++)
9130  f[n] = i[n] / 255.0f;
9131  if (edit_mode == 1)
9132  ColorConvertHSVtoRGB(f[0], f[1], f[2], f[0], f[1], f[2]);
9133 
9134  if (value_changed)
9135  {
9136  col[0] = f[0];
9137  col[1] = f[1];
9138  col[2] = f[2];
9139  if (alpha)
9140  col[3] = f[3];
9141  }
9142 
9143  PopID();
9144  EndGroup();
9145 
9146  return value_changed;
9147 }

9155 // Horizontal separating line.
9156 void ImGui::Separator()
9157 {
9158  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
9159  if (window->SkipItems)
9160  return;
9161 
9162  if (window->DC.ColumnsCount > 1)
9163  PopClipRect();
9164 
9165  float x1 = window->Pos.x;
9166  float x2 = window->Pos.x + window->Size.x;
9167  if (!window->DC.GroupStack.empty())
9168  x1 += window->DC.IndentX;
9169 
9170  const ImRect bb(ImVec2(x1, window->DC.CursorPos.y), ImVec2(x2, window->DC.CursorPos.y+1.0f));
9171  ItemSize(ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f)); // NB: we don't provide our width so that it doesn't get feed back into AutoFit, we don't provide height to not alter layout.
9172  if (!ItemAdd(bb, NULL))
9173  {
9174  if (window->DC.ColumnsCount > 1)
9175  PushColumnClipRect();
9176  return;
9177  }
9178 
9179  window->DrawList->AddLine(bb.Min, ImVec2(bb.Max.x,bb.Min.y), GetColorU32(ImGuiCol_Border));
9180 
9181  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
9182  if (g.LogEnabled)
9183  LogText(IM_NEWLINE "--------------------------------");
9184 
9185  if (window->DC.ColumnsCount > 1)
9186  {
9187  PushColumnClipRect();
9188  window->DC.ColumnsCellMinY = window->DC.CursorPos.y;
9189  }
9190 }

9223 // Lock horizontal starting position + capture group bounding box into one "item" (so you can use IsItemHovered() or layout primitives such as SameLine() on whole group, etc.)
9224 void ImGui::BeginGroup()
9225 {
9226  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
9227 
9228  window->DC.GroupStack.resize(window->DC.GroupStack.Size + 1);
9229  ImGuiGroupData& group_data = window->DC.GroupStack.back();
9230  group_data.BackupCursorPos = window->DC.CursorPos;
9231  group_data.BackupCursorMaxPos = window->DC.CursorMaxPos;
9232  group_data.BackupIndentX = window->DC.IndentX;
9233  group_data.BackupGroupOffsetX = window->DC.GroupOffsetX;
9234  group_data.BackupCurrentLineHeight = window->DC.CurrentLineHeight;
9235  group_data.BackupCurrentLineTextBaseOffset = window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset;
9236  group_data.BackupLogLinePosY = window->DC.LogLinePosY;
9237  group_data.BackupActiveIdIsAlive = GImGui->ActiveIdIsAlive;
9238  group_data.AdvanceCursor = true;
9239 
9240  window->DC.GroupOffsetX = window->DC.CursorPos.x - window->Pos.x - window->DC.ColumnsOffsetX;
9241  window->DC.IndentX = window->DC.GroupOffsetX;
9242  window->DC.CursorMaxPos = window->DC.CursorPos;
9243  window->DC.CurrentLineHeight = 0.0f;
9244  window->DC.LogLinePosY = window->DC.CursorPos.y - 9999.0f;
9245 }
9246 
9247 void ImGui::EndGroup()
9248 {
9249  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
9250  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
9251 
9252  IM_ASSERT(!window->DC.GroupStack.empty()); // Mismatched BeginGroup()/EndGroup() calls
9253 
9254  ImGuiGroupData& group_data = window->DC.GroupStack.back();
9255 
9256  ImRect group_bb(group_data.BackupCursorPos, window->DC.CursorMaxPos);
9257  group_bb.Max.y -= g.Style.ItemSpacing.y; // Cancel out last vertical spacing because we are adding one ourselves.
9258  group_bb.Max = ImMax(group_bb.Min, group_bb.Max);
9259 
9260  window->DC.CursorPos = group_data.BackupCursorPos;
9261  window->DC.CursorMaxPos = ImMax(group_data.BackupCursorMaxPos, window->DC.CursorMaxPos);
9262  window->DC.CurrentLineHeight = group_data.BackupCurrentLineHeight;
9263  window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset = group_data.BackupCurrentLineTextBaseOffset;
9264  window->DC.IndentX = group_data.BackupIndentX;
9265  window->DC.GroupOffsetX = group_data.BackupGroupOffsetX;
9266  window->DC.LogLinePosY = window->DC.CursorPos.y - 9999.0f;
9267 
9268  if (group_data.AdvanceCursor)
9269  {
9270  window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset = ImMax(window->DC.PrevLineTextBaseOffset, group_data.BackupCurrentLineTextBaseOffset); // FIXME: Incorrect, we should grab the base offset from the *first line* of the group but it is hard to obtain now.
9271  ItemSize(group_bb.GetSize(), group_data.BackupCurrentLineTextBaseOffset);
9272  ItemAdd(group_bb, NULL);
9273  }
9274 
9275  // If the current ActiveId was declared within the boundary of our group, we copy it to LastItemId so IsItemActive() will function on the entire group.
9276  // It would be be neater if we replaced window.DC.LastItemId by e.g. 'bool LastItemIsActive', but if you search for LastItemId you'll notice it is only used in that context.
9277  const bool active_id_within_group = (!group_data.BackupActiveIdIsAlive && g.ActiveIdIsAlive && g.ActiveId && g.ActiveIdWindow->RootWindow == window->RootWindow);
9278  if (active_id_within_group)
9279  window->DC.LastItemId = g.ActiveId;
9280  if (active_id_within_group && g.HoveredId == g.ActiveId)
9281  window->DC.LastItemHoveredAndUsable = window->DC.LastItemHoveredRect = true;
9282 
9283  window->DC.GroupStack.pop_back();
9284 
9285  //window->DrawList->AddRect(group_bb.Min, group_bb.Max, IM_COL32(255,0,255,255)); // Debug
9286 }
9287 
9288 // Gets back to previous line and continue with horizontal layout
9289 // pos_x == 0 : follow right after previous item
9290 // pos_x != 0 : align to specified x position (relative to window/group left)
9291 // spacing_w < 0 : use default spacing if pos_x == 0, no spacing if pos_x != 0
9292 // spacing_w >= 0 : enforce spacing amount
9293 void ImGui::SameLine(float pos_x, float spacing_w)
9294 {
9295  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
9296  if (window->SkipItems)
9297  return;
9298 
9299  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
9300  if (pos_x != 0.0f)
9301  {
9302  if (spacing_w < 0.0f) spacing_w = 0.0f;
9303  window->DC.CursorPos.x = window->Pos.x - window->Scroll.x + pos_x + spacing_w + window->DC.GroupOffsetX + window->DC.ColumnsOffsetX;
9304  window->DC.CursorPos.y = window->DC.CursorPosPrevLine.y;
9305  }
9306  else
9307  {
9308  if (spacing_w < 0.0f) spacing_w = g.Style.ItemSpacing.x;
9309  window->DC.CursorPos.x = window->DC.CursorPosPrevLine.x + spacing_w;
9310  window->DC.CursorPos.y = window->DC.CursorPosPrevLine.y;
9311  }
9312  window->DC.CurrentLineHeight = window->DC.PrevLineHeight;
9313  window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset = window->DC.PrevLineTextBaseOffset;
9314 }

9316 void ImGui::NewLine()
9317 {
9318  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
9319  if (window->SkipItems)
9320  return;
9321  if (window->DC.CurrentLineHeight > 0.0f) // In the event that we are on a line with items that is smaller that FontSize high, we will preserve its height.
9322  ItemSize(ImVec2(0,0));
9323  else
9324  ItemSize(ImVec2(0.0f, GImGui->FontSize));
9325 }

9327 void ImGui::NextColumn()
9328 {
9329  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
9330  if (window->SkipItems || window->DC.ColumnsCount <= 1)
9331  return;
9332 
9333  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
9334  PopItemWidth();
9335  PopClipRect();
9336 
9337  window->DC.ColumnsCellMaxY = ImMax(window->DC.ColumnsCellMaxY, window->DC.CursorPos.y);
9338  if (++window->DC.ColumnsCurrent < window->DC.ColumnsCount)
9339  {
9340  // Columns 1+ cancel out IndentX
9341  window->DC.ColumnsOffsetX = GetColumnOffset(window->DC.ColumnsCurrent) - window->DC.IndentX + g.Style.ItemSpacing.x;
9342  window->DrawList->ChannelsSetCurrent(window->DC.ColumnsCurrent);
9343  }
9344  else
9345  {
9346  window->DC.ColumnsCurrent = 0;
9347  window->DC.ColumnsOffsetX = 0.0f;
9348  window->DC.ColumnsCellMinY = window->DC.ColumnsCellMaxY;
9349  window->DrawList->ChannelsSetCurrent(0);
9350  }
9351  window->DC.CursorPos.x = (float)(int)(window->Pos.x + window->DC.IndentX + window->DC.ColumnsOffsetX);
9352  window->DC.CursorPos.y = window->DC.ColumnsCellMinY;
9353  window->DC.CurrentLineHeight = 0.0f;
9354  window->DC.CurrentLineTextBaseOffset = 0.0f;
9355 
9356  PushColumnClipRect();
9357  PushItemWidth(GetColumnWidth() * 0.65f); // FIXME: Move on columns setup
9358 }

9372 static float GetDraggedColumnOffset(int column_index)
9373 {
9374  // Active (dragged) column always follow mouse. The reason we need this is that dragging a column to the right edge of an auto-resizing
9375  // window creates a feedback loop because we store normalized positions. So while dragging we enforce absolute positioning.
9376  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
9377  ImGuiWindow* window = ImGui::GetCurrentWindowRead();
9378  IM_ASSERT(column_index > 0); // We cannot drag column 0. If you get this assert you may have a conflict between the ID of your columns and another widgets.
9379  IM_ASSERT(g.ActiveId == window->DC.ColumnsSetId + ImGuiID(column_index));
9380 
9381  float x = g.IO.MousePos.x - g.ActiveIdClickOffset.x - window->Pos.x;
9382  x = ImClamp(x, ImGui::GetColumnOffset(column_index-1)+g.Style.ColumnsMinSpacing, ImGui::GetColumnOffset(column_index+1)-g.Style.ColumnsMinSpacing);
9383 
9384  return (float)(int)x;
9385 }
9386 
9387 float ImGui::GetColumnOffset(int column_index)
9388 {
9389  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
9390  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindowRead();
9391  if (column_index < 0)
9392  column_index = window->DC.ColumnsCurrent;
9393 
9394  if (g.ActiveId)
9395  {
9396  const ImGuiID column_id = window->DC.ColumnsSetId + ImGuiID(column_index);
9397  if (g.ActiveId == column_id)
9398  return GetDraggedColumnOffset(column_index);
9399  }
9400 
9401  IM_ASSERT(column_index < window->DC.ColumnsData.Size);
9402  const float t = window->DC.ColumnsData[column_index].OffsetNorm;
9403  const float x_offset = window->DC.ColumnsMinX + t * (window->DC.ColumnsMaxX - window->DC.ColumnsMinX);
9404  return (float)(int)x_offset;
9405 }
9406 
9407 void ImGui::SetColumnOffset(int column_index, float offset)
9408 {
9409  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
9410  if (column_index < 0)
9411  column_index = window->DC.ColumnsCurrent;
9412 
9413  IM_ASSERT(column_index < window->DC.ColumnsData.Size);
9414  const float t = (offset - window->DC.ColumnsMinX) / (window->DC.ColumnsMaxX - window->DC.ColumnsMinX);
9415  window->DC.ColumnsData[column_index].OffsetNorm = t;
9416 
9417  const ImGuiID column_id = window->DC.ColumnsSetId + ImGuiID(column_index);
9418  window->DC.StateStorage->SetFloat(column_id, t);
9419 }

9421 float ImGui::GetColumnWidth(int column_index)

9431 static void PushColumnClipRect(int column_index)
9432 {
9433  ImGuiWindow* window = ImGui::GetCurrentWindow();
9434  if (column_index < 0)
9435  column_index = window->DC.ColumnsCurrent;
9436

9438  float x2 = ImFloor(0.5f + window->Pos.x + ImGui::GetColumnOffset(column_index+1) - 1.0f);
9439  ImGui::PushClipRect(ImVec2(x1,-FLT_MAX), ImVec2(x2,+FLT_MAX), true);
