9441 
9442 void ImGui::Columns(int columns_count, const char* id, bool border)
9443 {
9444  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
9445  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
9446  IM_ASSERT(columns_count >= 1);
9447 
9448  if (window->DC.ColumnsCount != 1)
9449  {
9450  if (window->DC.ColumnsCurrent != 0)
9451  ItemSize(ImVec2(0,0)); // Advance to column 0
9452  PopItemWidth();
9453  PopClipRect();
9454  window->DrawList->ChannelsMerge();
9455 
9456  window->DC.ColumnsCellMaxY = ImMax(window->DC.ColumnsCellMaxY, window->DC.CursorPos.y);
9457  window->DC.CursorPos.y = window->DC.ColumnsCellMaxY;
9458  }
9459 
9460  // Draw columns borders and handle resize at the time of "closing" a columns set
9461  if (window->DC.ColumnsCount != columns_count && window->DC.ColumnsCount != 1 && window->DC.ColumnsShowBorders && !window->SkipItems)
9462  {
9463  const float y1 = window->DC.ColumnsStartPosY;
9464  const float y2 = window->DC.CursorPos.y;
9465  for (int i = 1; i < window->DC.ColumnsCount; i++)
9466  {
9467  float x = window->Pos.x + GetColumnOffset(i);
9468  const ImGuiID column_id = window->DC.ColumnsSetId + ImGuiID(i);
9469  const ImRect column_rect(ImVec2(x-4,y1),ImVec2(x+4,y2));
9470  if (IsClippedEx(column_rect, &column_id, false))
9471  continue;
9472 
9473  bool hovered, held;
9474  ButtonBehavior(column_rect, column_id, &hovered, &held);
9475  if (hovered || held)
9476  g.MouseCursor = ImGuiMouseCursor_ResizeEW;
9477 
9478  // Draw before resize so our items positioning are in sync with the line being drawn
9479  const ImU32 col = GetColorU32(held ? ImGuiCol_ColumnActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_ColumnHovered : ImGuiCol_Column);
9480  const float xi = (float)(int)x;
9481  window->DrawList->AddLine(ImVec2(xi, y1+1.0f), ImVec2(xi, y2), col);
9482 
9483  if (held)
9484  {
9485  if (g.ActiveIdIsJustActivated)
9486  g.ActiveIdClickOffset.x -= 4; // Store from center of column line (we used a 8 wide rect for columns clicking)
9487  x = GetDraggedColumnOffset(i);
9488  SetColumnOffset(i, x);
9489  }
9490  }
9491  }
9492 
9493  // Differentiate column ID with an arbitrary prefix for cases where users name their columns set the same as another widget.
9494  // In addition, when an identifier isn't explicitly provided we include the number of columns in the hash to make it uniquer.
9495  PushID(0x11223347 + (id ? 0 : columns_count));
9496  window->DC.ColumnsSetId = window->GetID(id ? id : "columns");
9497  PopID();
9498 
9499  // Set state for first column
9500  window->DC.ColumnsCurrent = 0;
9501  window->DC.ColumnsCount = columns_count;
9502  window->DC.ColumnsShowBorders = border;
9503 
9504  const float content_region_width = (window->SizeContentsExplicit.x != 0.0f) ? window->SizeContentsExplicit.x : window->Size.x;
9505  window->DC.ColumnsMinX = window->DC.IndentX; // Lock our horizontal range
9506  window->DC.ColumnsMaxX = content_region_width - window->Scroll.x - ((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollbar) ? 0 : g.Style.ScrollbarSize);// - window->WindowPadding().x;
9507  window->DC.ColumnsStartPosY = window->DC.CursorPos.y;
9508  window->DC.ColumnsCellMinY = window->DC.ColumnsCellMaxY = window->DC.CursorPos.y;
9509  window->DC.ColumnsOffsetX = 0.0f;
9510  window->DC.CursorPos.x = (float)(int)(window->Pos.x + window->DC.IndentX + window->DC.ColumnsOffsetX);
9511 
9512  if (window->DC.ColumnsCount != 1)
9513  {
9514  // Cache column offsets
9515  window->DC.ColumnsData.resize(columns_count + 1);
9516  for (int column_index = 0; column_index < columns_count + 1; column_index++)
9517  {
9518  const ImGuiID column_id = window->DC.ColumnsSetId + ImGuiID(column_index);
9519  KeepAliveID(column_id);
9520  const float default_t = column_index / (float)window->DC.ColumnsCount;
9521  const float t = window->DC.StateStorage->GetFloat(column_id, default_t); // Cheaply store our floating point value inside the integer (could store a union into the map?)
9522  window->DC.ColumnsData[column_index].OffsetNorm = t;
9523  }
9524  window->DrawList->ChannelsSplit(window->DC.ColumnsCount);
9525  PushColumnClipRect();
9526  PushItemWidth(GetColumnWidth() * 0.65f);
9527  }
9528  else
9529  {
9530  window->DC.ColumnsData.resize(0);
9531  }
9532 }

9548 }

9636 // Win32 API clipboard implementation
9637 #if defined(_WIN32) && !defined(IMGUI_DISABLE_WIN32_DEFAULT_CLIPBOARD_FUNCS)
9638 
9639 #ifdef _MSC_VER
9640 #pragma comment(lib, "user32")
9641 #endif
9642 
9643 static const char* GetClipboardTextFn_DefaultImpl(void*)
9644 {
9645  static ImVector<char> buf_local;
9646  buf_local.clear();
9647  if (!OpenClipboard(NULL))
9648  return NULL;
9649  HANDLE wbuf_handle = GetClipboardData(CF_UNICODETEXT);
9650  if (wbuf_handle == NULL)
9651  return NULL;
9652  if (ImWchar* wbuf_global = (ImWchar*)GlobalLock(wbuf_handle))
9653  {
9654  int buf_len = ImTextCountUtf8BytesFromStr(wbuf_global, NULL) + 1;
9655  buf_local.resize(buf_len);
9656  ImTextStrToUtf8(buf_local.Data, buf_len, wbuf_global, NULL);
9657  }
9658  GlobalUnlock(wbuf_handle);
9659  CloseClipboard();
9660  return buf_local.Data;
9661 }
9662 
9663 static void SetClipboardTextFn_DefaultImpl(void*, const char* text)
9664 {
9665  if (!OpenClipboard(NULL))
9666  return;
9667  const int wbuf_length = ImTextCountCharsFromUtf8(text, NULL) + 1;
9668  HGLOBAL wbuf_handle = GlobalAlloc(GMEM_MOVEABLE, (SIZE_T)wbuf_length * sizeof(ImWchar));
9669  if (wbuf_handle == NULL)
9670  return;
9671  ImWchar* wbuf_global = (ImWchar*)GlobalLock(wbuf_handle);
9672  ImTextStrFromUtf8(wbuf_global, wbuf_length, text, NULL);
9673  GlobalUnlock(wbuf_handle);
9674  EmptyClipboard();
9675  SetClipboardData(CF_UNICODETEXT, wbuf_handle);
9676  CloseClipboard();
9677 }
9678 
9679 #else
9680 
9681 // Local ImGui-only clipboard implementation, if user hasn't defined better clipboard handlers
9682 static const char* GetClipboardTextFn_DefaultImpl(void*)
9683 {
9684  return GImGui->PrivateClipboard;
9685 }
9686 
9687 // Local ImGui-only clipboard implementation, if user hasn't defined better clipboard handlers
9688 static void SetClipboardTextFn_DefaultImpl(void*, const char* text)
9689 {
9690  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui;
9691  if (g.PrivateClipboard)
9692  {
9693  ImGui::MemFree(g.PrivateClipboard);
9694  g.PrivateClipboard = NULL;
9695  }
9696  const char* text_end = text + strlen(text);
9697  g.PrivateClipboard = (char*)ImGui::MemAlloc((size_t)(text_end - text) + 1);
9698  memcpy(g.PrivateClipboard, text, (size_t)(text_end - text));
9699  g.PrivateClipboard[(int)(text_end - text)] = 0;
9700 }
9701 
9702 #endif

9736 void ImGui::ShowMetricsWindow(bool* p_open)
9737 {
9738  if (ImGui::Begin("ImGui Metrics", p_open))
9739  {
9740  ImGui::Text("ImGui %s", ImGui::GetVersion());
9741  ImGui::Text("Application average %.3f ms/frame (%.1f FPS)", 1000.0f / ImGui::GetIO().Framerate, ImGui::GetIO().Framerate);
9742  ImGui::Text("%d vertices, %d indices (%d triangles)", ImGui::GetIO().MetricsRenderVertices, ImGui::GetIO().MetricsRenderIndices, ImGui::GetIO().MetricsRenderIndices / 3);
9743  ImGui::Text("%d allocations", ImGui::GetIO().MetricsAllocs);
9744  static bool show_clip_rects = true;
9745  ImGui::Checkbox("Show clipping rectangles when hovering a ImDrawCmd", &show_clip_rects);
9746  ImGui::Separator();
9747 
9748  struct Funcs
9749  {
9750  static void NodeDrawList(ImDrawList* draw_list, const char* label)
9751  {
9752  bool node_open = ImGui::TreeNode(draw_list, "%s: '%s' %d vtx, %d indices, %d cmds", label, draw_list->_OwnerName ? draw_list->_OwnerName : "", draw_list->VtxBuffer.Size, draw_list->IdxBuffer.Size, draw_list->CmdBuffer.Size);
9753  if (draw_list == ImGui::GetWindowDrawList())
9754  {
9755  ImGui::SameLine();
9756  ImGui::TextColored(ImColor(255,100,100), "CURRENTLY APPENDING"); // Can't display stats for active draw list! (we don't have the data double-buffered)
9757  if (node_open) ImGui::TreePop();
9758  return;
9759  }
9760  if (!node_open)
9761  return;
9762 
9763  ImDrawList* overlay_draw_list = &GImGui->OverlayDrawList; // Render additional visuals into the top-most draw list
9764  overlay_draw_list->PushClipRectFullScreen();
9765  int elem_offset = 0;
9766  for (const ImDrawCmd* pcmd = draw_list->CmdBuffer.begin(); pcmd < draw_list->CmdBuffer.end(); elem_offset += pcmd->ElemCount, pcmd++)
9767  {
9768  if (pcmd->UserCallback)
9769  {
9770  ImGui::BulletText("Callback %p, user_data %p", pcmd->UserCallback, pcmd->UserCallbackData);
9771  continue;
9772  }
9773  ImDrawIdx* idx_buffer = (draw_list->IdxBuffer.Size > 0) ? draw_list->IdxBuffer.Data : NULL;
9774  bool pcmd_node_open = ImGui::TreeNode((void*)(pcmd - draw_list->CmdBuffer.begin()), "Draw %-4d %s vtx, tex = %p, clip_rect = (%.0f,%.0f)..(%.0f,%.0f)", pcmd->ElemCount, draw_list->IdxBuffer.Size > 0 ? "indexed" : "non-indexed", pcmd->TextureId, pcmd->ClipRect.x, pcmd->ClipRect.y, pcmd->ClipRect.z, pcmd->ClipRect.w);
9775  if (show_clip_rects && ImGui::IsItemHovered())
9776  {
9777  ImRect clip_rect = pcmd->ClipRect;
9778  ImRect vtxs_rect;
9779  for (int i = elem_offset; i < elem_offset + (int)pcmd->ElemCount; i++)
9780  vtxs_rect.Add(draw_list->VtxBuffer[idx_buffer ? idx_buffer[i] : i].pos);
9781  clip_rect.Floor(); overlay_draw_list->AddRect(clip_rect.Min, clip_rect.Max, IM_COL32(255,255,0,255));
9782  vtxs_rect.Floor(); overlay_draw_list->AddRect(vtxs_rect.Min, vtxs_rect.Max, IM_COL32(255,0,255,255));
9783  }
9784  if (!pcmd_node_open)
9785  continue;
9786  ImGuiListClipper clipper(pcmd->ElemCount/3); // Manually coarse clip our print out of individual vertices to save CPU, only items that may be visible.
9787  while (clipper.Step())
9788  for (int prim = clipper.DisplayStart, vtx_i = elem_offset + clipper.DisplayStart*3; prim < clipper.DisplayEnd; prim++)
9789  {
9790  char buf[300], *buf_p = buf;
9791  ImVec2 triangles_pos[3];
9792  for (int n = 0; n < 3; n++, vtx_i++)
9793  {
9794  ImDrawVert& v = draw_list->VtxBuffer[idx_buffer ? idx_buffer[vtx_i] : vtx_i];
9795  triangles_pos[n] = v.pos;
9796  buf_p += sprintf(buf_p, "%s %04d { pos = (%8.2f,%8.2f), uv = (%.6f,%.6f), col = %08X }\n", (n == 0) ? "vtx" : " ", vtx_i, v.pos.x, v.pos.y, v.uv.x, v.uv.y, v.col);
9797  }
9798  ImGui::Selectable(buf, false);
9799  if (ImGui::IsItemHovered())
9800  overlay_draw_list->AddPolyline(triangles_pos, 3, IM_COL32(255,255,0,255), true, 1.0f, false); // Add triangle without AA, more readable for large-thin triangle
9801  }
9802  ImGui::TreePop();
9803  }
9804  overlay_draw_list->PopClipRect();
9805  ImGui::TreePop();
9806  }
9807 
9808  static void NodeWindows(ImVector<ImGuiWindow*>& windows, const char* label)
9809  {
9810  if (!ImGui::TreeNode(label, "%s (%d)", label, windows.Size))
9811  return;
9812  for (int i = 0; i < windows.Size; i++)
9813  Funcs::NodeWindow(windows[i], "Window");
9814  ImGui::TreePop();
9815  }
9816 
9817  static void NodeWindow(ImGuiWindow* window, const char* label)
9818  {
9819  if (!ImGui::TreeNode(window, "%s '%s', %d @ 0x%p", label, window->Name, window->Active || window->WasActive, window))
9820  return;
9821  NodeDrawList(window->DrawList, "DrawList");
9822  ImGui::BulletText("Pos: (%.1f,%.1f)", window->Pos.x, window->Pos.y);
9823  ImGui::BulletText("Size: (%.1f,%.1f), SizeContents (%.1f,%.1f)", window->Size.x, window->Size.y, window->SizeContents.x, window->SizeContents.y);
9824  ImGui::BulletText("Scroll: (%.2f,%.2f)", window->Scroll.x, window->Scroll.y);
9825  if (window->RootWindow != window) NodeWindow(window->RootWindow, "RootWindow");
9826  if (window->DC.ChildWindows.Size > 0) NodeWindows(window->DC.ChildWindows, "ChildWindows");
9827  ImGui::BulletText("Storage: %d bytes", window->StateStorage.Data.Size * (int)sizeof(ImGuiStorage::Pair));
9828  ImGui::TreePop();
9829  }
9830  };
9831 
9832  ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; // Access private state
9833  Funcs::NodeWindows(g.Windows, "Windows");
9834  if (ImGui::TreeNode("DrawList", "Active DrawLists (%d)", g.RenderDrawLists[0].Size))
9835  {
9836  for (int i = 0; i < g.RenderDrawLists[0].Size; i++)
9837  Funcs::NodeDrawList(g.RenderDrawLists[0][i], "DrawList");
9838  ImGui::TreePop();
9839  }
9840  if (ImGui::TreeNode("Popups", "Open Popups Stack (%d)", g.OpenPopupStack.Size))
9841  {
9842  for (int i = 0; i < g.OpenPopupStack.Size; i++)
9843  {
9844  ImGuiWindow* window = g.OpenPopupStack[i].Window;
9845  ImGui::BulletText("PopupID: %08x, Window: '%s'%s%s", g.OpenPopupStack[i].PopupId, window ? window->Name : "NULL", window && (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) ? " ChildWindow" : "", window && (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu) ? " ChildMenu" : "");
9846  }
9847  ImGui::TreePop();
9848  }
9849  if (ImGui::TreeNode("Basic state"))
9850  {
9851  ImGui::Text("FocusedWindow: '%s'", g.FocusedWindow ? g.FocusedWindow->Name : "NULL");
9852  ImGui::Text("HoveredWindow: '%s'", g.HoveredWindow ? g.HoveredWindow->Name : "NULL");
9853  ImGui::Text("HoveredRootWindow: '%s'", g.HoveredRootWindow ? g.HoveredRootWindow->Name : "NULL");
9854  ImGui::Text("HoveredID: 0x%08X/0x%08X", g.HoveredId, g.HoveredIdPreviousFrame); // Data is "in-flight" so depending on when the Metrics window is called we may see current frame information or not
9855  ImGui::Text("ActiveID: 0x%08X/0x%08X", g.ActiveId, g.ActiveIdPreviousFrame);
9856  ImGui::TreePop();
9857  }
9858  }
9859  ImGui::End();
9860 }
